name: Gramercy Tavern
review:
We had lunch at Gramercy Tavern on Sunday with a group of four, seated in the Tavern area rather than the formal dining room. The cocktails were a fantastic start‚Äîabsolutely 5 out of 5. The staff was warm and attentive, and the atmosphere was lively and welcoming.

The flatbread was excellent, one oWe had dinner at Gramercy Tavern tonight, and it was a wonderful experience from start to finish. The atmosphere felt warm, cozy, and perfectly balanced between casual and elegant. Their wine list is outstanding‚Äîone of the most diverse and carefully curated we‚Äôve seen in a while. We ordered a BaroloPhenomenal meal. Credit to our server, Emmry, who was friendly, helpful, and made our meal that much better. We were celebrating a birthday and received complimentary champagne which was such a nice touch.

The food was exquisite, everything tasted fresh and was cooked to perfection. Highlights wereWe recently celebrated our wedding and reception in the private dinning room at Gramercy Tavern. The room, with its antique furniture, vegetable-themed wall d√©cor, a serene landscape painting, and beamed ceiling, created the most enchanting setting. The in-house florist, Roberta created breathtakingOne of my favorite restaurants in NYC. The service was warm but professional. The food was perfect. The wine pairings were to my very picky specs. The atmosphere was quiet and the tables were spaced far from each other as not to be cramped.
I‚Äôve been to most of the Michelin starred restaurants in NY
location: 42 E 20th St, New York, NY 10003, USA

name: Boucherie Union Square
review:
I wanted to treat my aunt to an amazing, fairly high end lunch as she is well traveled and highly intelligent. I made a reservation here and it was above my expectations. Food was amazing, fresh and well presented. Service top notch. Elena and Anais went above and beyond. They secured my luggage as Pretty classic restaurant that everything will be nice for all kinds of occasions. We can for a friend‚Äôs birthday and servers professionally helped us celebrate.

Dick leg was surprisingly delicious. It was a seasonal dish. The skin was crispy and the sides were flavored.

My friend‚Äôs burger was ok.Lunch at Boucherie Union Square was absolutely lovely! The Boucherie burger was excellent‚Äîjuicy, flavorful, and perfectly cooked. Our server, Ben, was awesome‚Äîfriendly, attentive, and made the experience even better. The mimosas were spot on, and the asparagus was delicious. On top of all that, I juWe stopped for brunch on a nice Sunday morning. The ambience and feel in the restaurant transports you to Europe. Our server, Ben was amazing and helped us with good recommendations. The coffee was amazing. I had the eggs Norwegian which was rich and flavorful but didn‚Äôt leave me feeling heavy afterI came here 3 years ago by myself and had an amazing dinner, however I recently brought my family and had a completely different experience. The food was just okay, and the service was TERRIBLE. My family and I did not feel welcomed at all during this past experience, our waiter had a horrible attit

name: Nobu Downtown
review:
This restaurant anywhere in the world will always be my favorite. I love it with all my heart. The service is spectacular. It was my first time at this location and it‚Äôs beautiful and very modern. The bar/lounge area is excellent; the bartenders are super attentive, and it‚Äôs perfect for a date nightAwesome service, excellent food in general and spacious atmosphere. Otoro sushi was the best. Scallop sushi, Snapper sushi and Wagyu sushi were really good. Sushi and sashimi were very fresh. Tuna off the bone was good. Cod was delicious. Squid was tasty and not chewy. Lobster was a little over battTook a client and client here for dinner.  Had a table at the bar and it did not disappoint.   We did the omakase and it was awesome.  Plenty of food and a great way to sample the best chef selections.  Great experience and will be back.   I have been to other Nobu locations and they are all good.  Every single dish we got was so good!! Fresh fish with yummy sauces. We asked for recommendations and our server suggested 2 specials which were both so üî•üî•üî• chutoro with truffle‚Ä¶ salmon with japanese pear‚Ä¶ and their signature miso cod. Worth the price! Will def be back!Interior is lovely, service was very friendly! We managed to get a table walking in on a Sunday, and it wasn‚Äôt too busy downstairs so wasn‚Äôt too loud either.

Food was good, especially the honey truffle corn and crispy rice! Tacos are small, but tasty. Baked Alaska dessert was surprisingly good, alt

name: The Dutch
review:
A solid brunch option - not the most unique menu but both plates we ordered tasted good and ok value. Fried chicken was tender and juicy, biscuits were fluffy, and the soft scrambled eggs were the perfect texture. Service was very efficient. Personally found the interior a little cramped and dark foWow! I love this place. The atmosphere was charming, the energy was electric, and the staff was warm and welcoming. The food was out of this world. We got the duck meatloaf, and some of the best fried chicken. I absolutely loved the elevated, modern twist. They took on classic food. To top it all ofA neighborhood vibe with fantastic service and great food. Carmellini has put together a menu with something for everyone even if you are looking for a suprise. Great bar scene, perfect for people watching and reliably the place we go to with our grown children or out of town guests. Chicken was delWe came to the Dutch last night and had a tasty, enjoyable dinner.

It was lovely evening out, so we chose to dine outside. It‚Äôs on the sidewalk with a lot of foot traffic, which was fine except for the occasional smell of smoke. Also, a bug flew into my ros√©, but the server kindly replaced it and gI'm a regular at The Dutch, and it continues to impress me with its delicious food, attentive service, and welcoming ambiance. For a recent birthday brunch, I mentioned the celebration in my reservation, and at the end of our meal, our server surprised us by bringing over a dessert with a sparkly ca

name: Manhatta
review:
Celebrated a friend‚Äôs birthday here and the views definitely made it a memorable spot! Had the steak (portion could have been better), the Gold Bar Squash with sauce ravigote side which was really really good,  Potato Chips with umami powder was lacking the umami powder so it ended up tasting like yThis restaurant has it all. It deserves a Michelin star or two as far as the food goes.  The flavors and the presentation are top notch. Add to that a knowledgeable and friendly staff, and that would be enough to make for a great dining experience. But wait, there's more! The view! 60 stories up witWe had an absolutely wonderful experience at Manhatta. We started the evening with drinks at the bar, and the view alone was worth the visit‚Äîpanoramic, breathtaking, and the perfect way to set the tone for dinner. The bar team was fantastic, and the atmosphere up there is just stunning.

We were celVisiting this restaurant was an unforgettable experience!
The breathtaking panoramic view of New York City alone is worth the visit ‚Äî it feels like you‚Äôre dining among the stars. The food was absolutely exquisite: every dish was a masterpiece, beautifully presented and bursting with flavor.
The servWhere do I start?

From the moment we arrived we were treated royally. Their selection of bourbon is phenomenal and they actually had Pappy 10 year in stock!

The food was exceptional. Service was excellent.

Not to mention the view!

I‚Äôll be back any time I‚Äôm in NYC!
location: 28 Liberty St 60th floor, New York, NY 10005, USA

name: Jack's Wife Freda
review:
The atmosphere was amazing and the waitstaff were absolutely lovely. Usually I wouldn't give such an expensive place 5 stars but the quality of their food made up for everything. Not huge portions, but enough to keep you full and delivers on taste. Also many options which makes it hard to choose butMy girlfriend and I visited Jack‚Äôs Wife Freda in SoHo for a late breakfast after reserving a 10:45am table, and it was the perfect brunch experience. We sat in the outdoor dining area. Seating was a bit cozy, but the atmosphere was lively and welcoming.

She ordered the Mediterranean Breakfast paireGood lunch in NYC, portions were balanced and everything tasted fresh and great.  Had Jacks breakfast and would have ate more had it been there but for $30 felt like a lot of value.  Jasmine tea was really good and brewed in pot.  Service was friendly and helpful.Good spot for brunch! The staff is kind and tries to be attentive, but the place gets very busy, so it‚Äôs hard to get consistent attention ‚Äî we were helped by three different servers during our visit. It‚Äôs also quite loud, which makes it a bit hard to relax.

The food was tasty ‚Äî the mains were delicA solid menu although I felt there could be a few more breakfast options and there are no a la carte options like scrambled eggs or a side of toast or sausage. Food was tasty and cappuccino was delicious. Service was prompt and the restaurant  is clean and cute.

name: Lindens
review:
I had such an incredible experience at Lindens! Fran, the bartender/mixologist, was absolutely amazing ‚Äî so patient and thoughtful in helping me choose a drink. I went with the Shishito Julep, and it was perfect.

The food was out of this world. The sausage breakfast sandwich, citrus salad, and summWe had a great early dinner on a warm Friday night. Our server Macky was charming, confident and attentive. He went thru the menu pointing out must haves and he wasn‚Äôt wrong - we had a delicious meal and the food came out quick! Get the raspberry ginger ale - so good! We were too full to get dessertWe normally do not frequent hotel restaurants as the menu is either limited or not of top quality.

This is NOT the case for Lindens.  A must go for atmosphere, service, and quality.

Whether a date, a business meeting or a large group fun-time out, this place is recommended.

name: Tatiana by Kwame Onwuachi
review: I went to Tatiana during my birthday trip to New York, and honestly, it ended up being one of the best dining experiences I‚Äôve ever had! We showed up on a Saturday around 3:50 with no reservation, and there was already a line forming. By 4:30, the staff came out with complimentary tea for everyone wgreat service friendly and knowledgeable staff and very accommodating. Great place for special event the food is eclectic and delicious! Get their riff on pastrami ruben and all the appys!  The Jamaican patties were just out of this world. It's an original take on Caribbean cuisine that's sophisticaTatiana by Kwame Onwuachi is a culinary triumph. More than a meal, it is a celebration of African American culture and cuisine uniquely interpreted through the lens of New York. The food here is bold, thoughtful and reverent with each dish telling a unique story. Its more than nostalgia, but heritagTo answer your question, yes, Tatiana is worth the challenge of getting a reservation. It‚Äôs one of the most memorable dining experiences I‚Äôve ever had. The food, service, sexy ambiance and incredible hospitality make this one of New York‚Äôs best restaurants. We went against most reviews and didn‚Äôt orI‚Äôve heard mixed reviews but I loved it! The food was imaginative and delicious. The space was lush and lively and they were playing all the R&B hits from the late 90‚Äôs. Our server, Beatrice, was a gem - always ready to top off my wine and bring us little extras. Glad I finally made it in!
location: 10 Lincoln Center Plaza, New York, NY 10023, USA

name: Craft New York
review:
Another excellent experience at the bar at Craft.  They do it right from the moment you walk in - I had a lovely chat with their maitre d Anita before settling in at the bar.  Fabricio took great care of me, and I overheard him charming both regulars and new guests as more folks trickled in.

The orCraft was everything I hoped for and more. From the moment we walked in, to when we left with banana bread muffins as a parting gift, every element was perfection.  We were celebrating our 10th wedding anniversary and the staff went out of their way to make us feel special.

The service was top notcThe interior of the restaurant was very nice. We enjoyed the industrial vibe. We came on a slower night so the service was pretty fast and the food was delicious. My favorite dishes are the scallop crudo, eggplant agnolotti and the Pekin Duck.Celebrating our cousin Kyle‚Äôs belated BIG 2-O Birthday at Top Chef‚Äôs head judge Tom Colicchio‚Äôs restaurant Craftsteak in NY! Great service & they‚Äôve surprised our daughter & her Uncle Kyle a custom menu with a special message at the top for each of them. We ordered the 40 oz. Ribeye Dry-aged Steak bCraft
Est. 2001

Layout/atmosphere
*Fine dining; bar area off to right (racks of wine bottles extending to the ceiling; Edison bulbs); tables (one large room)

Food/drink
*The Peacemaker (Gin, Forthave Yellow, Cucumber, Lemon, Absinthe) - solid
*Short Rib Au Poivre (roasted mushrooms, green pepperco

name: The Tyger
review:
Great Foody experience, went there with 5 of my friends, one of them is a French food tour guide we all loved the food.
Pan Asian kitchen very flavorful and well designed on the plate which really open our appetite. we started with chicken skewers , Fried chicken Papaya salad  and beef tartare, we hI really wanted to like the spot, but the fusion aspect left me very confused about each dish. Everything just tasted a little bit different than I expected or wanted it to, and I felt like the flavors just didn‚Äôt jive for me. The service was very nice and the restaurant is beautiful. It‚Äôs great forSuch a cute spot with good food and vibes! Our server was amazing - she knew the menu really well and gave great recommendations which we appreciated. We ordered several things she recommended, including the crab fried rice, which was 10/10! Drinks were really good as well.Love this place! Great vibes, flavorful food, and excellent service. The dishes are always interesting. I accidentally spilled my drink and they replaced it right away. The dessert was delicious too. I keep coming back!5 stars for Angela, she's very cool, friendly & accommodates us with the menu. Great service üëç

The food was OK. Some were not bad, and others were blends.
Papaya salad taste only limes, not enough seasoning.
Charred Octopus was not bad.
Crab fried rice was good, the Sambal Stingraay was OK, Branzin
location: 1 Howard St, New York, NY 10013, USA

name: Little Collins
review:
This place has such a nice vibe. Service is great and food is delicious! We had the breakfast salad and granola. Both dishes were well balanced. First time having fresh chili slices in my salad, gave it a nice kick. And the granola dish is the perfect combination of yogurt with crunchy granola, candWould be 5 stars but the server forgot my coffee. I had a delicious green omelette and croissant, and the server was very nice, but she forgot the pour over coffee we ordered. She actually forgot the croissant too until we asked for it. We waited until well after we were done eating and when we askeLittle Collins is a must-visit for brunch in NYC! The cafe has such a cute and charming atmosphere, and the staff are some of the friendliest you'll meet. Our food was delicious, and I especially loved my Shakshuka‚Äîit was packed with flavor. Great food, great people, and a great vibe. What more coulWe loved Little Collins, 10/10. My husband and I ate here 5 mornings while visiting New York.

The queue moves very quickly (15min wait) so don‚Äôt let that put you off eating here. The earlier you get here, the better‚Ä¶we were here before 10am each morning.

Recommend: eggs benny+bacon, scrambled eggsA must go for breakfast in the mid manhattan area. Phenomenal espresso and hand squeezed OJ. Breakfast menu is small and everything we had was fantastic. As normal extremely tight sitting quarters and very busy. Would love to go again!
location: 708 3rd Ave, New York, NY 10017, USA

name: Bibble & Sip
review: One of my absolute favorite dessert spots in NYC, and truly the best cream puffs you‚Äôll find in the city! Their cream puffs are always incredibly fresh, light, and filled with the most delicious, creamy fillings. I‚Äôve been a fan for a long time, but this year I also tried their mooncake gift box andBibble & Sip in the NYC Theater District is a real treat‚Äîespecially if you have a sweet tooth and a love for creative twists. Their baked goodies are uniquely clever and delicious: I totally fell for the ‚Äúsoup dumpling cake,‚Äù which looks like a savory snack but is actually a sweet, fluffy masterpiecI stopped by Bibble Coffee Shop right after my morning jog, and it was the perfect treat. Their iced latte totally hit the spot, and the pastry I grabbed was so fresh. Such a cozy place to relax and recharge ‚Äî I‚Äôll definitely be making this part of my routine!Got four puffs to share with friends. My favorite is the matcha one. You gotta try it. Oreo one is the least fav. The puff is so crunchy and full of flavor. Not too sweet and very delicious. Early grey is also amazing.Busy Asian bakery in the theatre district! You must stop by for a treat when you‚Äôre in the area. Desserts are beautifully decorated and not super sweet compared to American desserts. Drinks are also very unique. They can also make some custom off menu drinks. I was able to get a Hochija mango drink
location: 253 W 51st St, New York, NY 10019, USA

name: Coffee Project New York | East Village
review:
Coffee Project New York is hands down one of the best coffee spots I‚Äôve ever visited in the city! The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, with the aroma of freshly brewed coffee filling the air. Their baristas are incredibly skilled and friendly ‚Äî they truly care about every cup they serve. I tried thCoffee Project in the East Village is a small, modern spot with a Euro-caf√© vibe (bonus points for the no-laptop policy). Their medium-roast blend‚ÄîColombia meets Guatemala‚Äîhits a sweet spot: smooth milk-chocolate body with a caramel finish, zero bitterness, and plenty of flavor.

I ordered an almondI've tried a lot of coffee shops in NYC, and this place takes #1 for best tasting coffee/drinks! And don't get me started on the incredible latte art.

I go here about once per week, and it's always a treat. I've never had a drink I disliked, and can highly recommend the ube delight, cappuccino, vanWe ordered pour over and nitro flight. The special Colombia natural pour over had  watermelon and lollipop notes, but $15 is very pricy even compared to San Francisco. The nitro flight is interesting but the beans used is probably not the best, so the taste is a little flat.

Gave 4 stars for atmospGood coffee place. Got their seasonal pandan latte with salted coconut foam. Their coffee was not as flavorful as I was hoping for. The foam did balance the pandan flavoring. It was a good pandan drink but not coffee drink. Service was great and quick.

name: In Common NYC - A Breakfast & Brunch Restaurant
review:
Great breakfast spot. My kids and I were lucky, we came here early enough to not have to wait, around 9:20am on a Saturday. When we were leaving the line was very long.

Everything we ordered came quickly. The Shakshuka was not good at all, however everything else was really yummy. Next time i want We walked in at around 10 am and the wait time was 15 min inside or immediately outside ‚Ä¶ we were heading to the airport and decides to not risk it so we got sited outside and it was super windy that day so definitely we didn‚Äôt have the best time with all the dust flying around us and the food.

TheWe came here our first morning in the city. We liked everything so much we started each day here.
My son loved their breakfast sandwich and eggs benes with french ham. The lattes were so good and very good pretty. All of the staff was friendly and made us feel welcome.Fantastic experience! The food and drinks were all delicious, and the servers were all very friendly and attentive (especially Jacqueline!). Everything we got was beautifully plated and tasted wonderful. My boyfriend and I were in the city for 4 days and loved it so much we came back twice.I came all the way from Texas and chose In Common for brunch  and what a beautiful experience it was! Despite the long line outside, the service moved quickly and smoothly. The waitresses were efficient, kind, and full of good energy.

name: Caf√© Lyria
review:
This place represents perfectly the Greek vibe from Greece. Is a very well made aesthetically place, coffee is good and you can enjoy your coffee inside or outside (outdoors is beautiful as well). 100% worthy for 100% Greek standards.
It‚Äôs a place for coffee and beverages (it seems like has fresh anI first visited this spot two years ago, and since then, I‚Äôve tried to come by on weekends whenever I was in the mood, but it was always too crowded to get a seat. This time, I finally got a chance to visit on a weekday morning. Even then, most of the tables were full, but I didn‚Äôt have to wait.

I Busy morning with a 12ish person line at 10:30am and the team of three handled it well. Enjoyed an Iced Lyria at the little table in front of the register. Hope they get a chance to find a bigger space and expand!Nice vibe, and that's it. Horrible coffee! I am not a coffee expert, but this is the worst coffee I‚Äôve ever had in my life. The espresso was disgusting; I threw it away. Apart from the atmosphere of the place and the cashier, everything else is wrong here. name: 787 Coffee Co.
review:
Chill coffee shop with great espresso and plenty of areas to relax or work in. Big fan of the Coquito latte. Love the mix of coconut and cinnamon. Their chicken empanadas are a delicious snack. Love the tables up on the second floor. Super chill and I got to spend a couple hours working there. Will A cool place with lots of seating. Eclectic furniture on the first and second floors. I would come here way more often if it weren‚Äôt for their strange pricing. When you order a latte, they make you choose from one of the three specialty beans, even when you didn‚Äôt ask for it. It adds $3 to the bill.Walking by and in search of a great cup of coffee with a place I could sit, work, and enjoy the people - I stumbled across 787. It was exactly what I had hoped for.

The Puerto Rican coffee with rum was recommended to me by the barista - and it was delicious. Smooth, decadent, and fully-leaded (the LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS PLACE!!!! Their coffee is absolutely amazinggg and sooo smooth. I took home some of their coffee beans (of course not as good as they make it) and it made such a difference in my at home coffee routine! My favorite is their Coquito coffee!!I dropped by this coffee shop for a networking event hosted by the Women in Machine Learning and Data Science community. The location is prime‚Äînaturally drawing a steady crowd of people grabbing coffee, catching up, or working remotely. There‚Äôs ample seating, making it a convenient spot to hang out

name: Urban Backyard
review: A nice quaint coffee shop on the edge of Soho. Customer service is friendly and welcoming. More importantly, the coffee is great. Seating inside, downstairs and on the quiet street that it's on. Worthy of stopping in.Wonderful coffee and espresso drinks with a pastry selection.  They have absolutely adorable cupcakes that look like real succulents- so creative!  They have the typical flavors plus some originals like black sesame latte. The space is totally cute and they have a basement that you enter from outsidBest coffee in NYC. I ordered an oat iced latte. Good amount of milk (some places add too much and you can‚Äôt taste the coffee). Lovely seating area outside and friendly staff - come here for your morning iced latte!Such a cute place and with super sweet staff. Had a great iced latte and the sweets looked really good. A nice place to chill for a bit and get good coffee.It‚Äôs a small space but great vibes here! The iced latte was perfect, and the cookies are solid. There‚Äôs some seating, a lot of plants and well decorated.
location: 180 Mulberry St, New York, NY 10012, USA

name: Charlotte Cafe
review:
Lovely staff, great coffee and peaceful ambience. You can sit outside in nice weather or at a table inside right by the table for a nice view.
Update: Stopped in today again and had the Mixed Berry start. So delicious. Light as air and not overly sweet. Perfect iced coffee and a lovely l, cozy spot First and foremost, the staff were so friendly and kind! They were nice and patient with the kids running around the store and gave me a free replacement of my drinks when they fell on the floor.

Thank you so much! Super amazing service.

My friend said the iced cold brew is very strong, very good.A quick Google search led us to pop into Cafe Charlotte on our last morning of visiting NYC. We tried a couple of recommendations (from the friendliest owners) that ended up being some of the best coffee I‚Äôve ever had (pistachio latte, dirty chai, espresso shot). The coffee was spot on in flavor, goEveryone here is absolutely magnificent. The food is to die for and the drinks in the morning are fantastic. Everyone here is so friendly. Albana is fantastic she's a ray of sunshine. She's gets to know her customers very well and always does her best to make sure everyone feels fantastic while theySuch a wonderful hidden gem!! I was staying at a friend's apartment a few blocks away, so we headed here for a quick pick-me-up each morning I was visiting. The cafe is super cozy and way more spacious than I would've expected for NYC. There's ample seating available and free WiFi, making it perfect
location: 605 2nd Ave, New York, NY 10016, USA

name: Gold coffee
review:
I was walking around this area one day and decided to stop in at the Gold Coffee to check it out.  Online reviews were very positive.
I got an americano and a pastry and found a stool at the counter by the window.  Coffee was excellent and the pastry was good.  Reasonable number of small tables and Fantastic place to get breakfast. Lovely ambiance as well. We ordered avocado toast (the best ever!), nutella banana crepe and bagel sausage egg, and cheese sandwich with coffee. We really enjoyed the food.
Apart from the above mentioned, they have varieties of hot and cold coffees, matchas, bagels,It was a decent place. Light meals, coffees, and some sweets. Some seats available, good place for short stay.

Cappuccino was ok. Watery but the taste was good.

The donut-shaped croissant was soggy with oily taste. Still, I appreciate that they heated up.Fantastic local coffee and lunch shop. Awesome people and great atmosphere. The coffee especially is 1000x better than most other shops in the area.Best coffee in town. Perfect service and great tasting cappuccino. Im definitely making this my coffee spot for my morning coffee. ü§åü§åü§å
location: 491 3rd Ave, New York, NY 10016, USA

name: 787 Coffee
review: Sindy  was fantastic - helpful, energetic, generous, and knowledgeable. Her service truly enhanced my dining experience. The coffee served at the restaurant was the best I've ever had; I absolutely loved the 787 coffee they offered. The rich flavor and aroma made it a standout beverage. The overall Great atmosphere! And they had delicious homemade GF pastry! The supervisor Cindy was kind and knowledgeable. Not to mention the coffee was on point. I had the coquito coffe with dark chocolate, vinilla and whiskey infused bean. My wife had the one with rum infused beans.And it even had little coconThe coffee was phenomenal, my husband and I both got lattes with different beans and you could taste the difference. The bags for the iced coffee are unique and so fun. The staff was super friendly and excited to share their passion about the product. We sat in the swings by the window, it was a perI had such a great experience at 787 Coffee! I ordered the Dulce de Leche Latte and it was incredible ‚Äî smooth, rich, and perfectly balanced. Cindy was my barista and she made it with so much care; she was super friendly too. What really makes this place stand out is the atmosphere. They have swingsI ordered the Coquito Rum Latte and it was absolutely amazing‚Äîso rich and flavorful! The service was excellent as well; everyone was friendly and welcoming, which made the experience even better. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, making it the perfect spot to enjoy a coffee. Definitely recommend

name: The Dead Rabbit
review:
The Irish coffee is a must-try, you won‚Äôt be disappointed. The Old Fashioned was good, though a bit on the sweeter side for my taste. The fried chicken was just okay, nothing particularly special. The tiramisu was one of the best I‚Äôve had. We sat in the Parlour, which had great vibes and good servicDrank at the tap room.  I remember a time when the tap room only had beer. I am so pleased to know they have cocktails and food available now.

This place has always been impeccable.  I‚Äôve been here a handful of times and never left disappointed.  I can‚Äôt remember the names of the drinks but they haWhat a wonderful Saturday brunch treat in this classic yet modern Irish pub. The decor is really cool along with signed dollar bills and photos around the walls and ceiling, Irish frozen coffee machine, etc.  Their cocktails are delicious and eye pleasing. Their authentic Irish fares and drinks wereMy husband and I had an incredible time at The Dead Rabbit! It was a highlight of our bar crawl, and we were completely blown away by the unique experience. The place has a fantastic energy, and we loved that each floor offered a different vibe.

name: Dear Irving on Hudson Rooftop Bar
review:
Dear Irving on Hudson Rooftop is the perfect spot for city views, good vibes, and great cocktails. The atmosphere is lively, especially around sunset, and the skyline views are unbeatable. Our team celebrated a big milestone here, and everything‚Äîfrom the service to the setting‚Äîwas fantastic. Highly This place is a fantastic rooftop bar! üç∏ Dear Irving serves a wonderful selection of cocktails üçπ, wine üç∑, and alcoholic drinks! ü•É Staff is friendly and the service is quick. ‚è≤Ô∏è The place is beautifully decorated üõãÔ∏è, have incredible views ü™ü of the city üåÜ, ambience üé∂ is great, and the music üéµ is awesoDear Irving was a really nice experience overall. The ambience and view were top notch. The food was super tasty, big kudos to the chef. I did find it a little pricey though‚Ä¶ for example, $15 for just four tiny goat cheese croquettes felt a bit much (see picture). Drinks were amazing, every round weWhether one‚Äôs looking to get those perfect Instagrammable city skylines or a drink with friends or colleagues under the sun, rooftop bars are a warm-weather must in Gotham.

They are popular. So don‚Äôt expect a quiet, intimate evening. The crowds can sometimes take away from the relaxing vibe, but heThis place is amazing!!! The view is breathtaking!!! Drinks are so tasty that you just want to keep ordering. name: Death & Co East Village
review:
Amazing experience!!! 10/10 recommend. Especially if you sit at the bar! Everything was wonderful- the hostess was very friendly and professional, the bartenders really appreciate their craft, you can tell. You can‚Äôt go wrong with any drink. We walked in last minute, probably one hour before close aAtmosphere: 8.5/10
East Village. Classic Death & Co ambiance‚Äîdimly lit, intimate, and sleek. The space feels like an upscale basement speakeasy, with a moody, timeless design and a striking backbar. The crowd is diverse and lively, though the music volume can make conversation challenging at times.
Went for a last minute drink at 11pm on a Saturday. The wait for 2 was reasonable, given how busy the venue was inside.  As we sat down we were quickly given menus and spoken to by a bartender. Cocktails were nice with a generally interesting flavor profile. Cookies were delicious, and appeared to bHad a great time at Death & Co. The cocktails were top-notch - expertly crafted and full of unique flavours. The atmosphere was stylish and inviting, and the service was attentive without being intrusive. Definitely a must-visit for anyone who loves quality cocktails.I‚Äôve been waiting for years to come to Death & Co., ever since I randomly found and bought their first book in 2019. name: Dante NYC
review:
I had heard of this place but never thought to go UNTIL I was tasked with finding a restaurant for my work dinner. I was able to snag a resy for 6 people on a Monday night and WOW. Dante rocks!!! Such a charming interior, we all felt very cozy and classy at the same time. The drink menu is extensiveLovely spot. I recommend making a reservation in advance. I don‚Äôt normally recommend pasta dishes but they were really delicious with good textured noodles and bright sauces. The drinks were also good. I‚Äôm glad I tried one of the ‚Äòfluffy cocktails‚Äô but probably would get another cocktail in the futuA very well-known bar in NYC that truly lives up to the hype. It‚Äôs famous for its Negronis, offering a wide variety of creative options. All of our drinks were excellent, and the overall vibe was stylish and relaxed - the perfect spot for a great night out.Dante is a beautiful Italian restaurant with truly well-crafted dishes ‚Äî definitely a spot worth trying. Even on a weekday evening, it was quite noisy inside, which made it a bit hard to have a relaxed conversation. A quick tip: instead of their famous martinis, I‚Äôd recommend trying one of their sprHappy hour 15-17PM. $10 for the best Negroni in the city. We seat in the bar, and the bar mixer is giving a great service and the vibe is great.
We also had the smoked salmon toast, and it was amazing.
Would definitely recommend to give this a try especially on the Negroni happy hour!!!
location: 79-81 MacDougal St, New York, NY 10012, USA

name: The Campbell
review:
Perfect quick little stop and reset. Justin, our bartender was AMAZING! Nice atmosphere and good conversation. Will definitely make The Campbell Bar a stop next time we are visiting the City! Again, thank you Justin for a good time.Hidden Bar Champion! Hidden in the Grand Central station you find this amazing & stunning bar. It was not crowded when we arrived on Sunday afternoon. Few people stopped by to have a look. Drinks were delicious and pricing was good.
The bar is just amazing from a design point of view.Rumor has it that this used to be Vanderbilt office?   Din. Dark. High ceilinged!!!!  The vibe is mysteriously cool.   Bar is standing only.  Tables are stacked in neat rows

Drinks are made meticulously and the noise level is appropriate for conversation. Proximity to grand central a plus.

Will beAn amazing speakeasy in the heart of Grand Central Concourse. Hard to find on the inside, you have to go upstairs on the upper level near the restaurant. There's a special elevator if you can find it. Entrance from the street is easier. Top notch bar drinks and atmosphere. Dark and quiet, classy. name: Old Town Bar
review:
Old Town Bar is the perfect after-work hangout! The cocktails are delicious‚Äîwell-crafted and full of flavor. The atmosphere is lively yet relaxed, making it a great spot to unwind with friends or coworkers. Classic charm, good vibes, and great drinks‚Äîdefinitely a favorite in the area!This was my first visit and I have to give it a perfect score because the staff and the food was amazing. The cheeseburger was top-notch, and the coleslaw was definitely in the top five I've ever had! Next time you're in New York, make sure you visit this iconic spot and top off your meal with a ManWhen a place has been around since the 19th century is now both queer & vegan friendly, that says something! We enjoyed delicious local beer on tap and each person had the exact burger they wanted. The servers were attentive and kind - food came fast and was all made fresh. Definitely stop by here nNice late night spot. Kitchen closes at 11:30pm.

Buffalo wings were generous in portion but a little too spicy for our liking! It's otherwise pretty good.

Key lime pie (Thursday special) was pretty nice.

Overall great service though. Worth a stop by.

P.S. People aren't kidding about large urinalOne of the oldest pubs in NYC!
A blast from the past, chicken wings are great

name: Hide Rooftop
review:
On the reservation it ask if this was a special occasion.  Yes, our 60 th Wedding Anniversary!  Much to our surprise, they brought us champagne!  So sweet!  We had other drinks and food that was delicious!  Then they come out with two desserts that just topped the evening off!  Staying at the ArtezeThis is a great multi-story location with an intimate setting. Space is at a premium but very accommodating, if you have a party greater than 2 it is recommended to make a reservation. The food is a great quality and comes out quick and the drinks are incredible. The bartenders are masters at their Amazing experience in a stunning place!
I recently had the pleasure of hosting 20 of my friends here for my birthday, and it was truly unforgettable. Ashly, the event coordinator, was AMAZING! She‚Äôs one of the most professional and delightful people I‚Äôve ever worked with. The venue itself was beautiThis is hands down my favorite rooftop in the entire USA! The staff are incredibly kind, the food and drinks are top-notch, and the view is absolutely immaculate. Every visit is such a great experience, I can‚Äôt recommend it enough!!Wow! We celebrated our Grandson's wedding weekend breakfast at the Hyde with over 100 people. The atomosphere is cozy and inviting. The view is great. The food was very good, plentiful, and presented beautifully. The wait staff was helpful and friendly. I highly recommend the Hyde for a celebration
location: Artezen Hotel Lobby Entrance, 24 John St 20th Floor, New York, NY 10038, USA

name: Rooftop Bars NYC
review: It was stunning experience for me. The views and atmosphere were incredible-amazing people are super nice, great way to socialize with each others in a relaxed environment. Left me with a landmark in my heart ü§≠. In addition, people who come from different cultures -countries are more friendly and reWe had a good time here, we could enjoy spectacular view of New York city from Roof Top bar. We did not have any reservation, but were able to find a table. Place was busy, by the time we got our fries and nachos, it was kind of cold. Other than that it is a good place to visit to enjoy the view.Really nice place, just be sure to show up before kitchen close (10pm) if yo want to eat, the drinks are cute and taste ok. The view is amazing. And yo can take so many nice pictures. 9/10Great rooftop to go to and hang out whether it‚Äôs a date or just hanging with friends. There‚Äôs a dance floor downstairs, I never stay down there tho cause it‚Äôs always packed and I‚Äôm not about that mess but everyone seems to be having a good time. Drinks are mid. Vibes are on 10üëçüèΩThe view of this place is phenomenal! A must visit for sure. Very casual very nice place. Good drinks. I also saw that they offer pizza and small bites.

name: Slate
review:
Slate NYC ‚Äì A Whole Vibe from Start to Finish

Pulled up to Slate NYC for a birthday and had a time! From the jump, security was cool, cracked jokes‚Äîset the tone for the night.

Downstairs was spacious and vibey (FYI: AT&T users, signal might dip but there‚Äôs WiFi). Shoutout to Krissi, our waitress‚Äîsüî• A Spot You Just Can‚Äôt Miss! üî•
One visit and I was hooked ‚Äì this club has it all: amazing vibes, great music, crazy cool design, and tons of fun, unique games that take the experience to the next level.
Between dancing, laughing, and challenges ‚Äì there‚Äôs never a dull moment!

If you‚Äôre looking for Slate NY is an experience, not just a venue! üéâ
Came here for a work event and was seriously impressed ‚Äî where else can you enter via a slide üõù and immediately be surrounded by arcade games üéØ, multiple levels üÜô, and flexible event spaces that cater to any vibe?

Whether you‚Äôre hosting something corpoSlate was super fun! My friends and I got a table for my birthday and the service was fantastic as well as the set up of everything. The music was amazing, everyone was just having a blast. Thank you to Joe the Director and Eva our server! It was a wonderful time!We have a great night. Lot of fun and great food.
location: 54 W 21st St, New York, NY 10010, USA

name: Lazy Bear
review:
Returned for my birthday after a wonderful first experience, but Lazy Bear has changed dramatically - and not for the better.
The charming bear decor and communal tables are gone.

More concerning: we spent $1,700 for two people (including beverage pairing) and received no birthday acknowledgment beWow. One of the best restaurants I‚Äôve ever been to and easily the top one or two-star in SF (better than Californios).

Food: Exceptional across the board. The cioppino, bread and butter, trout, and wagyu were out of this world. The wine pairing was spot on - remarkable bottles and one of the best SOne of the best meals I've ever had.  The service was fun, friendly, and informative. Every detail was accounted for.  Each course was unique, fresh, and delicious.  The split pea soup was my favorite.  But everything from the tea at the start of the meal to the wine pairings to the bonus dessert waDining at Lazy Bear was one of the best culinary experiences we‚Äôve had in San Francisco. From start to finish, the pacing was perfect as the courses flowed naturally without ever feeling rushed or drawn out, which made the evening feel effortless and immersive. The staff was incredibly attentive andWhat an amazing restaurant! The food was absolutely spectacular. The bread, the meat and the corn dish! This would be a five star review if it was just about the food and the service, but it is a two star Michelin restaurant so the expectations are high.

We felt very rushed between the courses, eve

name: Waterbar Restaurant
review:
We went to their happy hour for the $1.55 oyster. We ordered a dozen first to try if the oysters are fresh. YES. They are so fresh and tasty, so we ordered another dozen. The location is very good, you can see the bay bridge from the window. The aquarium in the restaurant is a plus. We also had reseWe had dinner here on a special occasion and were delighted with the entire experience.
We had drinks and oyster starters and trout and lamb dishes as entrees. All items were well prepared and tasteful!
The service was very courteous, friendly and efficient. In fact I had a query about the origin ofI went there on my recent stay in San Francisco and was looking for somewhere that has great oysters. I went for the happy which pricing was reasonable from $10 - $25, oysters were amazing and fresh like they just caught them, I also had the crab cakes which were really good little bites, some marinSome of the best food in SF. The best oysters were amazing and branzino soft and buttery. First time having squab. Amazing first experience. It was tender and flavorful. The star of the show was the pork chop. I immediately asked our waiter how it was made - it was that good. Tender, nice crust, perReally enjoyed a happy hour snack here on the way from the airport. Highlight and what I‚Äôd go back for was the drinks and the oysters. The seafood bisque was rich and tasted of the sea but the crab cakes were pretty standard fried bar fare. The oysters and in particular the price on the oysters made

name: Rich Table
review:
Porcini donuts were great -- with the raclette üòãüòãüòã
Sea urchin spaghetti was also quite nice though I didnt notice the sea urchin too much. They also had watermelon with a tom kha sauce on it which made for a great combo. Chicken liver was too sweet for me. Everything else was mostly pretty good, exRich Table offers exceptional service, and every bite was a true delight. Everything we were served was a culinary adventure, paired with excellent wines. It‚Äôs not cheap, but absolutely worth the price. A wonderful experience with outstanding service, and we would love to return.Loved the food! Nothing was groundbreaking, but all of the flavors were fresh and delicious and seasonal w/ fun combinations. The atmosphere of the restaurant was a little more casual and rustic than I would‚Äôve liked, but I went for the earliest seating (maybe it‚Äôs more vibey in the dark?). Overall We took Michael to Rich Table for his birthday since it‚Äôs his favorite restaurant in SF.
We opted for the family menu, and every dish was delicious and generously portioned. The staff was also very thoughtful in accommodating our vegetarian friend‚Äîthey really made sure everyone was taken care of.

TAmazing experience! Was grateful that there was a table available. Interesting take on food that will leave you talking about your flavor experiences! I highly recommend trying as many items on the menu as possible and sharing them with your friends!
location: 199 Gough St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA

name: Bottega
review:
Their mushroom truffle pizza is a must-try! The mozzarella and truffle was magic on first bite. I added arugula and anchovy in mine which made it even more bomb. Love their ‚Äúbuild your own‚Äù pizza and pasta concept and the open seating made me feel like being in Europe.I absolutely adore this place! I walked in and immediately felt like I was transported to Italy. The gentleman that seated my friend and I was so kind and welcoming. All of the wait staff were helpful attentive throughout our dinner.

The food was excellent! We got the pizza with Kalamata olives on A solid authentic Italian eatery. Pasta is freshly made daily. We had the truffle croquettes and fried calamari to start. Both were good. The calamari was a bit chewy. I had the Potato Gnocchi with Vodka Pink sauce. It's hard to find great Gnocchi, this one is very good. Soft with a slight bite. Came here just for a drink and dessert (the red velvet cake) and it was perfect. The server was amazing, and the vibe was great for people-watching ‚Äîthey give you delicious free bread such a nice way to close out a Sunday night. I‚Äôd definitely come back!They took such a good care of us! Exceptional food quality, keeping the authentic Italian family atmosphere. You can truly taste the care in every ingredient. Can't wait go back!
location: 1132 Valencia St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA

name: Sotto Mare
review:
Absolutely stunning seafood bistro!!! Excellent service from hostess to Fabbie! Great recommendation on the white white Fabbie and thank you for your lovely and welcoming ways!!! Bravo to you!! The food was scrumptious. We ordered starters of octopus salad and shrimp cocktail salad which was refreshCame here because of many good reviews but left disappointed, perhaps my expectation was too high. Service is quick but the neither the host or server smiled at us once, the only one that did was the burst boy. The place definitely has a vibe but we just felt uncomfortable because everyone looked soBEST FOOD IN SF.

The food was incredibly delicious. We went like a week ago and I still dream about it till
now. We got the smoked salmon pasta (which was recommended to us) and it did not disappoint, my favourite dish for sure.
We also got the Seared scallops, linguini with promodoro and shrimp anSotto Mare is definitely worth going to while in San Francisco, but be prepared to wait during peak times! We waited over an hour, but it was well worth it. If you have a long wait time, I recommend trying a slice of pizza from Golden Boy next door while you wait. I could eat the Crab Louis salad anSecond time coming here and the food is still as incredible as the first time trying it!

The cioppino is so flavorful. The seafood tastes very fresh. I love dipping the (complimentary) bread in the sauces/broths as well.

location: 552 Green St, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA

name: Brenda's French Soul Food
review:
Came here on a Saturday afternoon for lunch and no wait at all. It's a bit pricey ($5 or ONE oyster!), but the food was delicious. Highly recommend the Catfish & Grits and watermelon iced tea. The beignets are filling. The fried chicken has good seasoning, but on the greasy side. Friendly staff and We had the catfish and fried chicken Benedict, grillades and grits and the bananas fosters french toast. The portions are all shareable, and that we did! Perfect texture and flavors from all menu items. Tomorrow we will be trying all of their famous beignets.My favorite was the beignets. They were sWe came here in the afternoon for beignets and they were absolutely delicious. Our favorites were the chocolate and ube ones!

We loved it so much that we came back the next morning to try their peach waffles but unfortunately it was a bit disappointing. The flavors were pretty good but the waffles Excellent food everything is absolutely delicious! Nothing is bad, everything is spectacular no exaggeration! The quality of the food exceeds my expectations. Even the coffee‚Ä¶ OMG, it‚Äôs amazing!
The service is always outstanding. The staff is incredible, from the kitchen to the servers; everyone is Wow, our server was so helpful and kind. The food spoke for itself. Absolutely delicious. We went on a Sunday morning in June. The vibe was chill lots of small groups and couples coming in and out. We tried several things on the menu. Great flavors in everything. üíØ Recommend.

name: ROOFTOP 25
review:
This was our second attempt visiting Rooftop 25, and it was absolutely worth the wait. Our first visit didn‚Äôt go as planned due to a miscommunication about a block-out date for a private event. However, the owner went above and beyond to make things right‚Äîand truly delivered on that promise.

When wNice, convenient location between parking and Oracle Park ü•πRecommend the linguine with clams (only $22). Pizza is unique (interesting veggies and lots of cheese). They have a great drink menu, nonalcoholic, soda, beers, wine & cocktails.I'll start with the positive.  Nice ambiance, good music, cool layout, and interesting looking drinks (I didn't have any).  Also, the Short Rib Calzone was easily the best thing I had, and one of the better items I've had that week.

That said, this place shouldn't be serving steak.  It was over priHad a great time at ROOFTOP 25! The food and drinks were tasty, and the young lady who served us was really friendly and attentive. The vibe was fun and lively, perfect for hanging out with friends. Only reason it‚Äôs not 5 stars is it got a bit crowded, but overall a solid spot!We went there for a quick drink and a small bite. The focaccia was so good and the sauce was really yummy!!
location: 25 Lusk St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA

name: Fog Harbor Fish House
review:
My husband and I made reservations while we were in town on our anniversary vacation. It was no hassle to make the reservations and our table was ready when we showed up. It is a busy place so if you want to guarantee a table, make the reservation. Haleigh was our server and she was phenomenal. VeryAfter a long walk at the wharf and window shopping, the decision was made to get a drink at the Fog Harbor Fish House at Pier 39.

My partner and I have been at Fog Harbor a few times before. We love the harbor view and the ambience. Lobby staff are friendly and inviting. Bartenders are all friendlyWe were in town for business and decided to give Fog Harbor a try‚Ä¶ we were not disappointed!  To start off, our servers Alex and Dom were amazing.  Friendly, knowledgeable, and efficient.

Because I had to, I tried their clam chowder. It was good, one of the better chowders I have had.

We had the rWhat an incredible dining experience! We were seated by a window with a breathtaking view of the ocean, made even more special by the sight of sea lions playing in the water.

The service was top-notch from start to finish. A special thank you to our server, David Q, who made our meal truly memorablOur second time here.  First time was more than nine years ago. Requested windows seats and were fortunate to get a table. Couldn‚Äôt believe we made it just in time before the sunset. Our server Jorge was so helpful with his recommendations.  Loved everything about our dinner including our server.  W

name: State Bird Provisions
review:
Fun experience with dim sum cart style dining. Service was great, staff were friendly.

Small bites were good but not memorable:
- Oysters: play of texture between the crunchy kohlrabi kraut and oyster
- Smoked trout dip: good balance of acidity, savory, and creamy
-Tofu and shiitake: loved the shiiLovely dining experience but unfortunately the food left much to be desired. I‚Äôm not in a rush to come back. If I do, I‚Äôd only order from the trays and make sure to get bubbly drinks. Although they do take walk-ins, I‚Äôd recommend making reservations.

+ Interesting concept, though they no longer useI love the concept, though a bit problematic. You can expect from the menu what they would serve carted out of the kitchen, but the eyes can be hungrier than your stomach at times. You got full from the first few dimsum style serving that didn‚Äôt really do it for you and you wonder if the last few onState Bird Provisions was a unique experience, although the price is high (over $60 per person) for the experience and food quality.

The Californian Japanese fusion with a dim sum style in a cool, relaxed atmosphere. Could be great for friends but might not be the best choice for a date.

It's a goI love bringing friends and family here so they can experience State Bird, and I‚Äôve been here four times. If you‚Äôve ever been to a dim sum place, it‚Äôs a similar concept where food is rolled around on carts, except instead of dumplings, you‚Äôll find things like oysters, garlic bread with burrata, and

name: Wayfare Tavern
review:
Our fifth anniversary was nothing short of magic, and Wayfare Tavern made it unforgettable. ‚ú®

From the moment we walked in, we were met with warmth and grace‚Äîthree heartfelt ‚ÄúHappy Anniversaries‚Äù from the host, our server, and even as we paid the bill. That kind of attention doesn‚Äôt just make a dinWayfare Tavern is such an incredible spot for a wedding reception ‚Äî timeless, cozy, and filled with that signature San Francisco charm. The atmosphere is warm and intimate, with the perfect mix of elegance and comfort. The food is phenomenal (truly some of the best I‚Äôve ever had at a wedding!), and I‚Äôve been to Wayfare Tavern several times before and have loved each experience until last night.

We were seated promptly at our reservation time which was great, however it then took took 10 minutes before anyone talked to us or got us any water. Not the end of the world, but things didn‚Äôt exactlyI had an amazing lunch at Wayfare Tavern‚Äôs new location on Pine street today with two colleagues who are also in the hospitality industry. They have made a more than successful move to their new space. The food was exceptional, service exceptional, and pricing reasonable. name: Doppio Coffee & Brunch
review: I loved coming here. Visiting from NY but we needed somewhere to get a bit of work done and this place was great. Genuinely the best bagel I‚Äôve had‚Ä¶ like ever. The prices r reasonable and the staff super nice. Highly recommend!Very nice place! Great atmosphere and friendly staff. The coffee was really good. We had the breakfast sandwich and it was delicious! Definitely recommend this place, good serviceThis place is fantastic. Excellent coffee options and brunch as well. We loved the savory and sweet crepes and the gents working here today put their heart and soul into their work. Thanks for a great experience. Hope to come again.Excellent service and food quality! I have enjoyed coming here quite a few times. The food is very fresh and delectable. The drinks are perfectly flavored. Not oversaturated with sugar unlike some coffee shops that over-rely on syrup flavorings. The flavor here is top notch.Everything about this place is amazing. The food, the coffee, the music, the atmosphere. It's a must try! All the coffees are good, the crepes are delicious (the picture is the bariatas favorite), the breakfast sandwiches amazing! You won't be disappointed. My husband goes here practically every day

name: Caffe Trieste
review:
This grill restaurant was an excellent experience. The food was very tasty, fresh, and cooked to perfection. The attention and service were warm and pleasant, making the whole visit even more enjoyable. A great place to enjoy delicious grilled food ‚Äî highly recommended!Came here because of its reputation, and I‚Äôm glad I did. Caffe Trieste has a timeless charm‚Äîwarm, slightly nostalgic, and full of character. The atmosphere invites you to slow down and enjoy your coffee, surrounded by photos and history. The espresso was rich and bold, just how it should be.

Just aCafe Trieste: A Personal Landmark in the Heart of North Beach

Having spent the last 30 years in North Beach, Cafe Trieste has become a significant part of my daily life. It was one of the first places I discovered when I moved into the neighborhood, and naturally, it quickly became one of my go-to So glad we decided to stop here after dinner in the North Beach. All the reviews led us here and they were spot on.

This is an icon in SF. We read that it‚Äôs been here for a long time and the original owner was a city celebrity. Walking in the shop we saw all the pics on the walls of the history, alLook no further! You‚Äôve found the best espresso in town. Vibes can‚Äôt be beat. Don‚Äôt even get me started on the cannolis, couldn‚Äôt get enough of these! I talk about them all the time. Loved everything about this place.

name: Scullery
review:
The pesto egg toast was absolutely delicious! A thick buttery slice of multigrain toast with a nicely cooked pesto egg on top was a hit. I had a seasonal lavender latte which was good, not too sweet with subtle hints of lavender. I felt a little overwhelmed dining inside by the amount of space proviThe food and coffee was absolutely amazing! We had avocado toast and PB&J toast, they were both put together with precision with fresh ingredients and homemade bread. The latte and cappuccino were also just perfect.

The staff were super friendly, and having fun while serving up greatness. The venueI recently visited this small cafe and was genuinely impressed by the warm and cozy atmosphere it offers. Despite its size, the space has a great vibe that makes you want to stay a while, perfect for a quiet break or catching up with a friend.

The staff were super friendly and helpful, which added If you don't want to pay for a big dining area but get some spot on breakfast this is your place. Some seats inside and chill music. Had the passion fruit and cream cheese Danish and Pesto and Egg. Was able to grab a Monster next door.Quaint little place for simple coffee and toast. The toast options are good with both vegan and regular options, and coffee definitely tastes better than what you get in the hotels. Was a large cuppa too when I had it for dine in.
Cashless payments preferred, and I think it was cos it is located in
location: 687 Geary St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA

name: Caffe Greco
review: Accidentally stumbled into this cafe, while waiting for our pizzas to cook in a nearby restaurant. This cafe transport you back to the last century. The decor is very 1960s. The space itself is huge though and has plenty of seats. They also have an outdoor area which is nice on a sunny day. UnfortunStep back in time or even into a little town in Italy and get a bite here. We got the breakfast panini and coffee. It was fantastic. As you can tell, they take their coffee seriously! It was super busy and we had to wait a few for our food, but it was worth it. Highly recommend this gem in Tiny ItalReally enjoyed this caf√© ‚Äî the service was excellent and the atmosphere was warm and inviting. It‚Äôs the perfect spot to start the day with a good breakfast and a nice coffee.Nice to see people reading books and having a coffee. Cash only but no expectation of tipping. $26 for coffee, cake and sandwich. You get what you expect, it was a good experience.Great for working, relaxing, or people-watching. They offer Wi-Fi (usually under the name OrderFirst, though it can change), and the coffee is excellent. Just a heads-up: it‚Äôs cash-only, so come prepared!
location: 423 Columbus Ave, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA

name: The Mill
review:
I can‚Äôt speak on the bread but I have only heard marvelous things about it. It smelled incredible. I already had a big lunch, so my stomach couldn‚Äôt fit any more solids. I got a coffee and enjoyed the ambiance. Light filled space with the perfect amount of background noise to focus. The smells are f10/10. Absolutely unbearable spot for brunch or bread. One of my friends in DC told me that I *had* to try The Mill when I moved to SF ‚Äî she would always come here every time she visited and take a few loaves of sourdough back to DC with her ‚Äî and I can absolutely see why. The bread is absurdly tastThe Mill is a sweet very bright cafe with a welcoming vibe. Prices are definitely in the higher range (espresso $5 and cappuccino $6,50) I‚Äôve decided to get an iced Americano with a salted chocolate pastry for my picnic because tables were occupied. Next time I‚Äôll come in the afternoon when it‚Äôs notThis review is about sustainability only! üåè

By 2050, there will be more plastic in the ocean than fish. And it means a lot to me as a customer to support cafes that are doing better by our local and global ecosystems by way of their dishware.

Namely, by not providing an excess of trashy, single usNot for me - the coffee is acidic, the coffee crumble is dry, and the almond toast was nothing out of the ordinary. And they were out of matcha. The interior of the shop is spacious and bright with enough space on the communal table if you want to work. Otherwise, not worth the hype and overpriced c
location: 736 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94117, USA

name: The Coffee Berry SF
review:
Very cute lil spot. I can't speak on the beverages, my goal was the pastries ($6.50) ü§≠ but they use Sight Glass beans, so I'm sure the coffee is fantastic.

I did takeaway, the seating spots are minimal, most patrons were sitting outside.
I've been wanting to try the Ube croissant so I could compareI‚Äôve been stopping by The Coffee Berry SF while staying nearby in SF, and it‚Äôs quickly become my go-to. The coffee is excellent‚Äîrich, smooth, and consistently well made. The pastries and food options are just as good, fresh and not overly sweet. The staff are friendly and efficient, which makes the If you are in SF and looking for a great place for a cup of coffee and a baked treat (sweet or savory), make sure to try the Coffee Berry. The workers (owners?) will immediately make you feel welcome and valued. The drinks and food are delicious and dogs are welcome. You‚Äôll find a lot of locals withWorthy of all the 5 stars. It is a small coffee shop right at the bottom of Lombard street. We really enjoyed our Nutella latte and lavender latte. The ube croissant was our favorite. The savory pull apart was ok. They have indoor seating for like 8 and a couple small tables outside.We had the savoury pull-apart bread and the twice-baked ube croissant and both were incredible. The pull-apart bread was moist throughout and super flavourful. The ube croissant was crispy, with creamy filling, and an amazing sweet crust. Coffees are also great, but the pastries are the true reason
location: 1410 Lombard St, San Francisco, CA 94123, USA

name: Delah Coffee
review:
It's always bustling with people and for good reason. This cozy, vibrant caf√© has earned a loyal following thanks to its exceptional drinks and authentic Middle Eastern treats. It‚Äôs my go-to spot, especially for their üåüpistachio latte ‚≠êÔ∏è, which is rich, creamy and perfectly balanced with just the riI really love Dallah Coffee, smooth, flavorful, and perfectly balance.
I want to thank the amazing ladies working at Dallah Coffee(Lynda and Lylia)! Their service is always excellent ‚Äî they‚Äôre friendly, professional, and make you feel so comfortable. I really appreciate their kindness and positive enThis gem in the rough serves super tasty, Middle Eastern coffee, with or without an array of spices. A wide range of unique pastries tasted fresh and homemade. Service is super helpful and patient.The place was abuzz with positive energy from people of all walks of life. It's everything a cafe shouI‚Äôve had Delah on my to-visit list for a while now, and I regret that I didn‚Äôt make it in sooner! Great atmosphere, amazing coffee, and helpful, friendly staff. The Turkish delight was incredible, as well. Hot tip: Have them put a little cardamom in the Turkish coffee. Sooo good!We are very lucky to have 2 count them 2 Yemeni coffee shops in this neighborhood. I refuse to pick favorites because they are both 5 star shops. Come to Delah for the amazing coffee, but stay for the pastries and attention to detail. Lots of seats and tables people working everywhere but also livel
location: 370 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA

name: Flywheel Coffee Roasters
review:
Loved the coffee and the vibe here, but guys‚Ä¶ the restroom completely ruined the experience. It‚Äôs so gross. It feels really disrespectful to customers to maintain it in such poor condition. It‚Äôs such a shame, because the shop itself is great.Flywheel Roasters on Stanyan is a true coffee paradise in SF. The moment you enter, an intriguing and distinct aroma of freshly roasted beans envelops you. Their commitment to same-day roasting is evident in every exceptional cup. The coffee is simply awesome ‚Äì vibrant, nuanced, and bursting with flExcellent coffee and latte art! I couldn‚Äôt believe it when I saw the swan come out. Great service too - they cleaned up a table for us right away when they realized the previous customers had left everything behind.Great work/study place IF YOU CAN GET A SEAT. Was pretty busy and crowded up until closing. Free wifi for 2 hours (I think you can extend this with an order). Outlets and good lighting. I ordered a chai latte with oatmilk and it was great. I‚Äôd definitely come back.

A cool, hip, relaxed coffee shop. Incredible coffee. Their cold brew had such clear smooth notes of flavor. Their matcha was smooth, delicious without any sweeter, which is how I know it is good matcha. Large selection of pastries, tried their vanilla earl grey donut and it was lovely. Location is r

name: Twisted St. Cafe
review:
First, the good: the people working there and the cleanliness and friendliness were great. The downside: for some reason, the two cortados I had were very weak. Also, the wait time was pretty long.A cute little gem tucked inside the Infinity Hotel SFO! Twisted Caf√© has a chill vibe with super friendly and polite staff that make you feel right at home. Everything I tried from the menu was honestly delicious. They‚Äôve clearly put effort into quality. My personal favorite? The salmon avocado toasWe stopped by this cozy little caf√© for our last breakfast in San Francisco and what a great choice it was! I ordered a breakfast bagel and a cappuccino, and my wife had the salmon avocado toast with green tea. Everything was delicious ‚Äî fresh, well-prepared, and beautifully served. The service was Overall vibe: small cafe
Matcha: tastes like grass and vegetables really did not like.
Golden Milk: it was good if you‚Äôre into the ingredients.
Avocado toast: lowkey was small but it was good.After spending the day in and around San Francisco I wanted to stop in at a local coffee shop before driving over an hour back to my hotel. Ordered the salmon bagel,  cappuccino and some gifts to take with me. The service and atmosphere of the shop are great,  very enjoyable abs wish i could've stay

name: Cable Car CoffeeSF
review:
The San Francisco sandwich was amazing. I added turkey. It was sooo good. Hummus cucumber tomato avocado sprouts red onion on an everything bagel. The bagel was toasted to perfection! 10/10 would recommend.Definitely a 5 stars for me! One of the best breakfast sandwiches we‚Äôve had üëèüòã Loved the pork&turkey sausage in bagel and bacon cheese croissant. Mocha and caramel macchiato were mmm mmm mmm. The vendor was really friendly and accommodating. She suggested for a croissant bread for my mom so it will What a find!
It‚Äôs located right at the station, you‚Äôll need to go down the escalator. They have a lot of options.
I got the bagel cheese avocado bacon with spicy mayo on the side. It was AMAZING!
So fresh, everything just felt like it was made on the spot.
Super tasty and full of flavors. I would deI don't often write a review, but the chibata breakfast sandwich (with pastrami rather than bacon) is absolutely magical. Will definitely have this again when I visit SF!Such a tasty breakfast sandwich in a cute setting (down the escalator). Atmosphere was great with the cable car turnaround right there and a local drummer playing good beats. Food was so good, I got a coffee with a sausage avocado bagel sammie.

name: Alchemist Bar & Lounge
review:
A true Hidden jam in downtown San Francisco

This themed bar had everything that I could‚Äôve ever hoped for! With a great selection of drink menus, I scurried in just after happy hour to sit down and enjoy quite a few drink drinks by the expert bartender Gerson

My waitress, Cindy took care of every Didn‚Äôt try the food on my visit so I cannot vouch for that. Great service & tasty cocktails. The atmosphere is quirky & reminded me of Tim Burton‚Äôs movies.good ambiance and date spot, however, slightly awkward crowd. music is alright and there‚Äôs weird (but slightly entertaining projections of things). interesting cocktails (actually quite overwhelming ‚Äî I couldn‚Äôt pick), and ‚Äúgood bar bites.‚Äù decent service. over all a 6.4/10 and i may go again.Ok, so I‚Äôm the worst only only captured the bathroom, but I mean look at that nice detail!

Anyways, this place had been a favorite of mine for years. Great atmosphere and energy with locals and visitors. Drink rotations super fun and the service is great!

The drinks are very interesting and the atmosphere is quite unique. I had a great time. Of the two drinks I tried, I loved one (It Takes Two to Tango) and didn't care for the other (Neuromancer). However, I took a risk and tried something out of my comfort zone, so I can't fault the bar for it!

name: Smuggler's Cove
review:
I don‚Äôt understand what the 1-star reviews talking about. The service was amazing. After telling the barkeeper once my name he called me after my name. Our drinks were done under 10min. Very friendly stuff.
I can recommend to come before the rush like around 9pm. It‚Äôs easy to spent there 3-4h.Worth dropping by for a drink, although not really designed to hang out. Strong drinks and limited seating kind of make you feel like you‚Äôre intended to move along. Drinks were really tasty and aesthetically presented, and the line outside moved pretty quickly, so I‚Äôd go again if in town, but wouldnThis is an amazing part of tiki history, worth visiting at least once. The service was good. The drinks were solid, though leaned sweeter than I expected, especially the Zombie (not pictured). My favorite was the Rum Barrel. The presentation of the drinks was somewhat understated.

I think ‚Äútiki culSome of the best tiki vibes you can find at a tiki bar. Even has a 2 story water fall!
Drinks are top notch across the board.
You do have to order at the bar at this establishment. They‚Äôll call your name when your drinks are ready. Many tiki bars I‚Äôve been to in the past will have someone wait on yoSmugglers cove is the cutest tiki bar! Beautiful decor

What a drink menu, it‚Äôs so good! Many cocktails to choose from and the bartenders are phenomenal. The drinks here are an art form and the presentation was excellent

Sat with our group in lower level it was pretty warm in there!

Must stop if y

name: Pacific Cocktail Haven
review:
Stopped by on a Sunday night and it did not disappoint. The place was lively with great music and a fun crowd. The bartenders were friendly, the service was on point, and the drinks were creative and well-made. Definitely a solid spot if you're looking for a high-energy cocktail bar with a great vibCame on a Thursday evening and there was no wait. Our party of 4 had 3 drinks each, and they were all phenomenal! Standouts were the numb and number, silky street, and pornstar martini. Service was fast, and our server made great recommendations!PCH was on our list of bars to hit during this trip to the city. What a fantastic choice we made! "T", our bartender, was awesome. Engaging, super knowledgeable, and just a pleasure to talk to. Made the visit THAT more enjoyable!
Incredible craft cocktails here at Pacific Cocktail Haven! If you're iIf you're not on a budget, and enjoy unique cocktails, then this place is for you. Visiting from Seattle, this bar was recommended as a place to try in the downtown SF area. Going on a Tuesday evening, it was not busy at all. We stuck with the Whiskey section of the menu, trying the Tropical GangstaA must if you visit SF and enjoy cocktails.

They have a long list of drinks and everyone would find one that they would enjoy. It gets crowded, but we were able to find seats a little late into the night.

Definitely a younger vibe, but not a crazy crowd.
location: 550 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA

name: Blackbird
review:
One of my favorite spots! Great happy hour and all the drinks are delicious. Friendly bartenders, quick service, good ambiance (lighting that‚Äôs moody but doesn‚Äôt make you feel like you need an eye exam), and plenty of seating. What‚Äôs not to love?This Bar is really nice .
Cocktails are good .
I ‚Äò m not drinking alcohol at moment and the bartender made me his favorite drink ,
a mohito without alcohol .
The bartender who helped me ,
I can tell that he love what he does.
Looking at him making drinks it could be almost hypnotic.
The perfect timiI wish I could say this bar felt like a safe, inclusive space, but my experience here the opposite. Blackbird may market itself as a gay-friendly bar, but that doesn‚Äôt prevent discrimination in other ways.

While participating in a bartending apprenticeship program (called The Cocktail Camp) hosWe went to this bar for a business mixer. The atmosphere is incredible. The staff is super friendly. name: Tunnel Top Lounge and Bar
review: What a great place to hang! I felt welcome from the moment I walked in. Turns out they only use premium liquors and make all of their own mixes in house - none of that fake sugary crap most bars use. This is apparently one of the oldest bars in SF but it has a warm new feel and none of that dive-barI visited this bar when I first got into the city, and the atmosphere was amazing and great vibe, friendly staff, and incredible drinks. I happened to lose my wallet here and was sure it was gone for good, but the staff went above and beyond to track me down on Facebook and return it all the way to Stopped in here on a whim. It was a Thursday evening, so it wasn‚Äôt very busy. The staff is friendly and the drinks are great. I asked for something irregular and off the menu, and with a quick explanation the bartender put it together and it was excellent. Highly recommended.we came here after our group sang karaoke nearby. the atmosphere, selection of drinks and a friendly staff made our first time here an unforgettable one. we will definitely come back. we didn't order food as we had just eaten. the price point was within range along that area. come visit the iconic tBartenders are so fun and the music is always bumping. Beer selection is amazing.

name: Cityscape
review:
I went there on a week day night. The bar wasn‚Äôt very crowded and it was open seating. I definitely felt like the view was a lot better than the one in the view lounge. There are a lot more seating that can see the view.
The waiter was super nice. He gave us good recommendation on the cocktails and Extremely beautiful views with delicious drink and (limited) food options. The service is great! Bartender Tommy was wonderful. He knows the area well, and is extremely helpful with travel tips. The atmosphere has a relaxed vibe. Highly recommend visiting right before sunset.After a full day of exploring the amazing city of San Francisco, we decided to end the evening with a relaxing drink at the Cityscape rooftop bar. Located high above the busy streets, it seemed like the perfect spot to enjoy a drink while taking in some stunning panoramic views of the city.

When weMy wife and I went here on a Tuesday night.

I ordered a Mont Gay Black Barell Rum and Coke. And my wife had a Coppola Director's Cut Red Wine. Both drinks were very good.

Beautiful view of San Francisco. Friendly servers. Relaxing atmosphere. We will definitely visit here again.This place was very cute! It had a gorgeous panoramic view of SF. Occasionally our views were distorted by classic SF fog, but for the most part it was beautiful during the day time. I can only imagine the night lights would be even better. The drinks were pricey and the food was appetisers only. I

name: Comstock Saloon
review:
Very unique place with a lot of history and some of the best craft cocktails I‚Äôve ever had. The bartender took his time with each drink, making sure each was just right. With two drinks, you get a free light lunch on Fridays. It was corn chowder the day we went, which was phenomenal, but not hearty Stopped in for beverage and light bite. Great service, interesting history. Live music several nights a week. Local crowd mostly, typical old SF bar vibe. Great neighborhood hangout.Unbelievable cocktail joint with a vintage vibe and excellent staff. Oysters were great and served with a delicious minionette or an awesome smokey home make hot sauce.

I make a point to stop in here every time I'm in San Francisco if I can make an excuse to do so!A wonderful bar offering a variety of drinks and special cocktails. We let the barkeeper choose our drink which is always fun to see the creativity flow. I have never been disappointed. On the contrary I was always delighted.

We also went for some delicious Kaviar and oysters. Fresh and breathtakinComstock Saloon is easily one of the best spots in a neighborhood stacked with great bars and restaurants. Great happy hour, great food, great staff, and a great atmosphere, often featuring live music.
