name: Aba
review:
We went to Aba for brunch and it was such a great experience! They recommend at least 4 items for 2 people, and every dish we tried was excellent and absolutely mouthwatering. The Mediterranean cuisine with a California influence makes the flavors so fresh and unique. Both the outdoor patio and indoAlright y'all. This was one of the best meals I've had in recent memory. The moment you step inside this place, you know you're in for something great. Every single thing we ordered was delicious. We went for happy hour and tried the dip trio (hummus/feta/eggplant) and each one was amazing. Believe Aba is one of the best dining experiences I had in Chicago. The food was delicious. I have a nut allergy, and the staff did a wonderful job making sure each dish we ordered was nut-free. Very communicative. Prompt service. Beautiful ambiance. I have nothing but high praise for this establishment.Overall, Aba delivers the perfect mix of ambiance, creative drinks, and flavorful Mediterranean-inspired dishes. A must-visit if you‚Äôre looking for a stylish spot with amazing energy, great service.

The cocktails are as beautiful as they are delicious vibrant, fresh, and garnished with thoughtful tLet‚Äôs start off with the good. The atmosphere is gorgeous. The city view was grand. The lighting and the foliage were beautiful. I‚Äôve traveled to Chicago a handful of times, and I‚Äôve enjoyed Aba in the past. Every time I visit I try to make an effort to come here and eat! name: Alinea
review:
Alinea was everything we‚Äôd hoped it would be, and so much more. Dramatic, unexpected, and fabulous from start to finish. I can‚Äôt remember every name (I left in awe and fullness), but the entire team from our evening in the gallery on Saturday, 10/4, was exceptional. My husband and I are lucky enough to have also been to the Inn at Little Washington and this was an entirely different experience. I booked seats in the Salon because the only seating for the Gallery (9pm) sold out instantly.This may be the most exciting meal I‚Äôve ever eaten. It‚Äôs a place where spoilers should not be shared so I‚Äôll withhold much of the experience, but Grant Achatz and his team delivers one of the most extraordinary dining experiences possibly anywhere on the planet. I was able to secure a seat at the GaWhat a unique experience. I went knowing almost nothing and I loved how I was constantly surprised by the creativity of the team in how they present the food, combine the flavors and and create a roller coaster experience.

I'm adding pictures to my review for myself, but I strongly recommend to avoAbsolutely phenomenal.
The entire staff was welcoming and fun. They all had a special flare that they added to each dish. Lots of surprises and whimsy!
Highly recommend. Well, worth the money.

It was a pleasure to have our table off the main I think they should bring new shoes in! Not sure what day they have the rope entrainment but that would be nice to see. The food was good and there is a lot to look at. The venue is huge. Service was good but a little on the slower side so if you need your check ask for it while they get you dessertAwesome place. So fun, colorful, and exciting coming here. Everything here is great, we got 2 different appetizers and 3 different entrees and there were 0 issues and everyone wants to come back! Our server was super helpful when we didn't know an ingredient. Would definitely recommend anyone to comWe visited after a LONG hiatus and finally had the whole family to share this place with. We saved for months to come here for our kiddo's fancy big girl birthday and she loved it. There happened to be Carnivale dancers every so often on the floor and it was incredible. The service was really bumpy.
location: 702 W Fulton St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA

name: The Whale
review:
Our experience at The Whale in Chicago was absolutely amazing! The lobster and waffles were seasoned to pure perfection! Every bite was full of flavor and cooked just right. The owner Justin went above and beyond to make sure our visit was nothing short of exceptional, and you can truly feel the carThis spot has a lively atmosphere with a menu that mixes comfort food and creative dishes. The portions are generous, and the flavors are on point whether you‚Äôre there for brunch, dinner, or just drinks. The cocktails are a highlight, and the staff keeps things friendly and relaxed. It‚Äôs a fun placeI recently had the chance to visit The Whale and finally see what it‚Äôs all about. For the longest time, I‚Äôd driven past but never had the opportunity to stop by‚ÄîI‚Äôm so glad I did this time!

We came for my cousin‚Äôs birthday brunch, and she had a fantastic time. My chicken sandwich was delicious, theDecided to dine in last minute for a party of 3 and a half (my infant). We ordered drinks first, which were part of happy hour (5-7pm). The cherry mule was my favorite, very refreshing and I also ordered the whale g & t that was more of a pine taste to it which I didn‚Äôt mind. For food, we ordered a I‚Äôm sold on this place based in aesthetics, but not all the dishes are meeting standards. We had reservations before hand. Parking can be a bit crazy. Loved the deviled eggs and Buffalos Cauliflower but the kale salad lacked some flavor. Cute spot for some bites and happy hour!
location: 2427 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA

name: Quartino Ristorante
review: It was my first time in Chicago and we came to this place after we had just drove out 10 hours, we came back on the last day of our trip because that first experience was so lovely. We came at a different time, and the service was absolutely stellar even in a packed restaurant. The wine selection isGreat high quality Italian that features small plates. Recommend the Kale Salad, Beet Salad or Assortment of Olives to start. For entrees recommend the Salmon or Beef Short Rib - was tender and flavorful. Truffle Risotto was amazing, Shrimp Risotto is good too. They have a solid Gluten Free menu.Great Italian restaurant serving up ‚Äútapas‚Äù like Italian dishes. The pasta is delicious, perfectly chewy in sauces that are not overpowering. Service is good even during very busy hours and this place seems to always be busy in the evenings regardless of the day of week. There is seating inside (botI recently visited this Italian spot and was pleasantly surprised by how warm and lively the evening turned out. The pasta dishes were well-balanced, with fresh flavors and good texture, though I wished for a little more seasoning in one of the sauces. The staff were friendly and efficient, explainiThis place is ALWAYS busy, a popular corner in River North. Good variety of Italian options, including fresh pasta, imported pasta, vegetable dishes, soups and salads. If you‚Äôre not sure what to get, ask for the half portions at half the menu price so you can get a sample of more dishes. I got the f
location: 626 N State St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA

name: The Wormhole Coffee
review:
The shop features a theme of maybe movies, games and local events. Not regular movies but mostly science fiction and interesting local tastes. I would assume boys would like this coffee.
The regular drop coffee tastes very good. Old style but rich. They don't have a wide selection for bakeries so ifIt‚Äôs been a decade since I last set foot in Chicago, and The Wormhole Coffee was a non-negotiable on my list of places to revisit. Stepping through the door felt like a trip back in time, and I mean that in the best way possible.
The 80s decor is as wonderfully quirky and over-the-top as I remember‚ÄîNice atmosphere. Cool niche posters and knickknacks! There aren‚Äôt a whole ton of spots to sit down, especially during busy hours and days. We came at 4pm on a Saturday and it was super busy. I can‚Äôt imagine what it‚Äôs like early on a weekday. Because of that, the service slowed down, but the staff weTasty and experimental coffee. Not too crowded on a Friday afternoon, moderately priced. My peanut butter/choc latte was deceThe socialist revolution starts here underneath the Back to the Future DoLorean.  Bike racks, throwback movie posters, Star Wars toys, young rebels.
location: 1462 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA

name: TARY
review:
Great food but very small portions. Amazing coffee and a beautiful space. They crank up the AC quite a lot so bring a sweater in the summer. We tried 5 different dishes and enjoyed all of them. Would recommend at least 2 dishes per person given the size.If you‚Äôre looking for a different kind of restaurant, especially if it‚Äôs for breakfast, then this is the place. I‚Äôve never tried Kazakh food before, and I was impressed. I loved the light, yet filling cottage cheese-like pancakes. The staff was very friendly and was great at making suggestions. The Great place in Chicago to try authentic Kazakh cuisine! This upscale coffee shop has great food options and unique drinks to try. The tary tea is super flavorful and with the added tary (millet), it gives a burnt, nutty flavor. I got the kuurdak in a bread bowl and it was amazing. Loved the fact tha‚ÄúBeyond our menu, we‚Äôve created an authentic experience where every detail reflects Kazakh heritage.‚Äù - Indeed they have. What a delightful place. Welcoming, unique, delicious.
My rice porridge was heavenly, the pastries yummy. Amazing coffee and on top of that super cute presentations.
Bravo Tary! I had a lovely visit at Tary Coffee House. The atmosphere was cozy and welcoming. The breakfast was just the right amount‚Äînot too heavy, just enough to satisfy me without feeling bloated. The food was fresh and tasty, pairing well with their excellent coffee.
location: 111 W Illinois St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA

name: Broadway Cafe
review: The nice girl working today was very kind and helpful.  What a nice place to be open so late until 3 am in downtown Chicago! Thank you bc I know it‚Äôs tiring to work so late. But it helps people who don‚Äôt have time or energy to cook or need something after hanging out late. They participate in deliveA cozy place next to Jimmy‚Äôs and the menu looks great. All day breakfast croissants, homemade sandwiches and all kinds of sweets. It was nice little find for us.I really enjoyed this coffee shop ‚Äî cozy atmosphere, delicious coffee, and a pleasant vibe. Special thanks to Jane for her excellent service! She was very attentive, friendly, and helped me choose the perfect drink. Definitely coming back!Chocolate cake was dry and very sweet. Didn‚Äôt feel worth the 6 dollar price tag :/Good products, confusing menu, in menu appear 5,25 = 16oz capuccino, but gave 12 oz capuccino, didnt understood why the difference between menu and what was served.
location: 22 E Adams St, Chicago, IL 60603, USA

name: Goddess and the Baker, 33 S Wabash-Millennium Park
review:
What a vibrant and thriving coffee shop!! I absolutely love how friendly all the staff is first of all. They warmly welcome you as you walk in and colors richly envelope the space to feel appreciated. They offer so many options for vegetarians! The coffee options are vast and I ended up getting 2 drThis place is super cute. The food is relishes and they have a lot to choose from. I DID NOT LIKE THEIR SEATING ARRANGEMENT: the metal chairs are very hard to seat on, the round tables are kinda small even for 2 people and when food comes, it occupies the entire table. We ordered the Ironman scramblThis place is ideally located for the intense foot traffic for practically all days when it is open.  The place was packed on this sunny Saturday as autumn descends on the month.  This is a well established institution city-wide with many locations as a baker and grocer.

I really enjoyed their ham I went here on a Thursday at 8:30 AM. The caf√© was very busy and they don‚Äôt have very good line management. People are always asking if you are in line to order or if you are waiting for your food. I think another issue is that the menu in the morning is way too broad and has too many menu items. MoGreat place for breakfast in the Downtown of Chicago. Just perfect if you have an early flight in and planning to explore the Art Institute of Chicago, which sits just a few blocks away. Have your breakfast here, then spend the rest of the day in the museum.

name: Prequel Cafe
review:
Cute modern space with great coffee, pastries, and breakfast/cafe fare. The walls are lined with fun art (available for sale).
What to get: cardamom brown sugar latte, honey cinnamon latte, avocado toast (with or without egg).
I like bold but smooth coffee and they have that. The avocado toast was wThe coffee here is rich and flavorful. Their latte is smooth and perfectly balanced. The sandwich is fresh and tasty too. Cozy place to relax and enjoy.Prequel Cafe in Chicago is a total gem! The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, with a retro vibe that's super charming. The staff is friendly and welcoming, making you feel right at home. Whether you're grabbing coffee to go or lingering over breakfast, Prequel Cafe is a top-notch spot. Highly recommeOrdered the Lavender Rose Matcha, and the breakfast sandwich without meat ‚Äî YUM! Best matcha latte I have had in a while.. Only con: they don‚Äôt take cash.I stopped here with my friends during our trip to Chicago, and it was amazing! The food was delicious. We got the bagel with cream cheese, the deluxe breakfast sandwich, a muffin, a cookie, and the turkey sandwich, and they were all delicious! The drinks were the perfect way to warm up on a rainy mo

name: Sawada Coffee
review:
Sawada Coffee lives up to the hype! The line was out the door when I arrived, but once inside, there was plenty of seating and the space is absolutely beautiful‚Äîgreat vibes all around.

I had a latte and it was incredible‚Äîthe espresso beans are truly next level. Smooth, bold, and perfectly balanced.I tried the military latte and it was a flavorful mix of matcha and espresso. The creamy touch of vanilla went really well with the earthy green tea. It was smooth and unique without being too strong. the space felt relaxed and had a cool vibe that made it easy to hang out. I will definitely return I loved my iced vanilla oatmilk latte! Coffee was delicious and service was great. Lots of seating and very unique atmosphere. The only thing is it smells really strong of meat due to it being connected to a restaurant. The smell was a bit rough for me but ended up not taking away from the great cofGreat coffee, great pastries. Loved their house mocha they do called the High Five Mocha, it is this gorgeous complex chocolate with fresh grated orange zest. Cool multi use space. Good vibes.Such an amazing vibe of a coffee shop. Drink divine. Atmosphere amazing. Food bomb. A deadly combination. 1st time visit and it was unforgettable. Such a chill vibe to grab a coffee and chill. Must visit 10/10
location: 112 N Green St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA

name: Hexe Coffee Co.
review:
My wife and I love this place. We walk over all the time.

Hexe has a great, big patio which is perfect for nice days. The coffee is always good, and they have a solid food selection too. It's cool that they also offer alcoholic drinks and have fun events like trivia.

Plus, they always have water bI‚Äôm used to cafes back from home in NYC, so I wanted to find a place in Chicago to chill while I was staying here‚ÄîHexe is exactly what I was looking for.

The dirty chai latte I got was great‚Äînot at all cloyingly sweet like some places do, just a great blend of bitter and spice with a hint of sweetnThis is way more than a coffee shop!! 1st the vibe is amazing, & staff is sweet, and on it. You can see them recognizing regulars (love that in a local place) & have a pastry (delicious). Bring your pup, their outdoor space is lovely & they have a cooler of water to self serve you pup. There is someThis coffee shop is a hidden gem for anyone seeking a spacious, comfortable setting to study or work. The drinks are pleasantly affordable, and the addition of cocktails is a fun bonus. Best of all, you‚Äôll never need to compete for outlets plug points line each wall, making it easy to keep your deviI really enjoyed coming here early in the morning, sipping a simple black coffee and sitting on their outdoor patio. Peaceful atmosphere, great coffee, and a perfect way to start the dayüíØüíØüíØ

name: Gold Coast Cafe
review:
Great space, family friendly and amazing choices of sweet treats, kunafa, chocolates and more. I loved the iced Dubai chocolate latte especially!
Update: the Dubai chocolate croissant is divine! Also their kunafa is world class.
Appreciate their partnership with Kareem‚Äôs Sweets to incorporate more mI saw all the hype on social media and had to come check it out for myself. Coming here today made my day, the Philly was phenomenal and the meat and spinach pies were to die for. The people here were so kind and told me all about the vision for the future, pop up events, and the new location comingWalked in right when they opened. I didn‚Äôt catch the guy behind the counters name but was so kind in offering me different coffee options and walked me through the menu. Their coffee is amazing.

Coffee was so good I didn‚Äôt even make it down the block before it was almost gone. Can‚Äôt wait to go backHonestly this coffee shop is average (for the vibes), I have no idea about the foods because I only ordered a cup of ice coffee (americano).
I gave 4-5 ‚≠êÔ∏è because of one thing, that's port charger everywhere. My phone battery is dying and I am a visitor, use uber, so my phone battery is most importaHere you can find the best sandwiches! Fresh, full of flavor and very tasty!
I highly recommend this place if you want something fast and delicious to go!
I had philly steak sandwiches and was fantastic!
The owner of this place Hani is very friendly and kind!
Definitely check out their food and medi

name: Cold Moon Cafe
review:
Disappointed in my experience here. The food tasted fine but not closely worth $30+ for 2 bagel sandwiches. They don't have their prices listed on the giant board behind the counter and now I see why. The service was also really slow. We waited about 20 minutes for them to be ready. It is a one persIt was fresh and clean. My cashier was pleasant and very helpful. I recommend,
If I could make a suggestion it would be nice to have a bell so the attendant will be alerted when someone is waiting to be served.The wait was ridiculous!! They had trouble understanding my simple order. Would not recommend. Spend your time somewhere else!! The croissant wait hard as hell!! 0/10!!!!!Everything was great ! The Tasha‚Äôs secret bagel sandwich is the best I have ever tasted in my life. The smoothies were amazing and the service was phenomenal! Thank you all for everything ! It made our vacation worth it.Only 1 table, but it takes forever to get your order. Only one person working to both get orders and prepare them and they weren't rushing...
20 minutes to get a simple tea... The bagel was decent, but definitely below expectations, especially considering the price and the "best steamed bagel" title

name: Sip of Hope Coffee
review:
Very solid place with great drinks,  great people,  and a worthwhile cause.

There's ample seating for working remotely or passing the time with a book. The shop also hosts & organizes community events.

As a community focused non profit, specializing in mental illnes, they're well worth your time tA coffee shop with an inspiring mission, great atmosphere, and delicious products. I will be back!

Most people here on a Monday during the day were focused on their work, it‚Äôs a quieter and more peaceful space. A ton of outlets, standing and sitting seating.

Kind staff that guided me to the best dThe best coffee shop in the world. My favorite. Not only are their coffee and treats delicious, but 100% of their proceeds go towards mental health. Not to mention they‚Äôre always so friendly and accommodating, and the artwork they have on the walls and in the bathrooms are so cool! Always a place woFriendly staff, atmosphere perfect chill vibes for a rainy day. Coffee was strong, holy, and so good!It woke me up instantly. I love that! Haha. It's rare for that to happen. If I lived closer, this would be my wakeup call for work daily. ‚òï #coffeelovers #rainydayvibes #perfecthideoutAmazing atmosphere and extremely helpful staff. All of the staff are mental health first aid trained. Buying from here is also a way to support a great organization in Chicago, Hope For The Day!

name: Three Dots and a Dash
review:
The cocktails are delicious (said the Tiki nerd) and the service is excellent.  Walked in on race day and was well communicated that we had an hour before a private party started.  As our time expired we were moved to an even cooler smaller room and had another round.  We could have stayed here all What a cute bar! Their drinks are very interesting-looking and well-priced for the wow factor they provide. Our table ordered 5 different cocktails and we did a tasting of all of them. One theme was that all the cocktails had the same major problem which was they were too sweet. They had notes of thThis is the OG of all Tiki Bar experiences complete with all the ambiance and a roped off VIP section to flex your style. I met a date at a standard table but still glad I made a reservation. Be prepared that they will keep you moving along after 2hrs in most cases. Lexy was awesome, great service & super friendly.
I would recommend making reservations if you‚Äôre coming during their peak hours as standing around the bar can be difficult to order.

name: Lazy Bird
review:
Very cool concept bar , downstairs within the Hoxton Hotel. Nice rotating special cocktail menu with very intricate cocktails !
Waitress was helpful in guiding me through their extensive menu of >50 cocktails (which can easily overwhelm any body).
Very limited bites (steak or fries) but the steak skAmazing rooftop bar close to Chicago downtown.  We tried many cocktails, were perfectly made. It is sometimes difficult to find place at poolside bar on weekendsVery cool speakeasy library you with beautiful decor. Drinks were recently made priced but shots are expensive! Bartenders were very good and made quality drinks I don‚Äôt recommend parties more than 6 because they let only two people in at a timeNice cocktail bar with an interesting menu, plenty of seating, and speakeasy vibes. Didn't adore the cocktail I received, but would try more options next time we're in Chicago.Excellent ambience, very moody. If you want it quiet and relaxing, choose a day where they have no special events or live music going on. They nailed the speakeasy feel. Drinks were spectacular, menu was unique and well executed. We ordered a Pornstar Martini, Mary Pickford Cocktail, and Flora Root
location: 200 N Green St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA

name: Long Room Chicago
review:
If you want to sit at a restored super cool old bar, this is it. Beautiful wood work, fun lighting in cased within the bar, and to pair with that is their wonderful bar staff.
Kind and welcoming, not to mention quite knowledgeable on spirits and craft cocktails. I'd for sure come back here again.

IHighlights: Uniquely shaped bar as the name suggests, attentive speedy and friendly bartenders, creative and tasty cocktails, fun pop up food offerings.

We specifically came because we wanted to support a friend‚Äôs pop-up. We ordered one of everything from Milo‚Äôs Market. It was delish!! Our fave wasChill cocktail bar üç∏ with lots of seating and a fun, lively atmosphere. It‚Äôs a bit loud but perfect for a night out! They have a solid cocktail selection, and there‚Äôs even a photo booth tucked in the back. Great for groups or casual hangouts.Stopped by around 3:10 PM on a Tuesday to grab food and a quick drink, but unfortunately the kitchen had just closed from 3-5 (or 6 PM). I was met by great service from Ollie, who recommended the drink Daquiri 4-Way which was SO delicious! The Parallelogram is a close second. The prices are amazing Really great drinks for a decent price. The service here is also amazing! I got the queenie (pictures) salt creation, and the parallelogram. All of the drinks were delicious. They have a fun photobooth in the back as well.
location: 1612 W Irving Park Rd Ste 1, Chicago, IL 60613, USA

name: Theory
review:
Probably the best sports bar I have ever been to! They are open and ready for any and all sports, including early F1 starts!

I had heard about an F1 bar in Chicago and as I was staying nearby I decided to check it out for qualifying. I ended up being the only one there for the start of it, and thatFirst time at Theory. Known for streaming sports and now gaining attention for Love Island USA watch parties. The place was packed for the finale, full of fans and energy. They are TVs everywhere so every seat is good. The small bites were good for a watch party vibe. Our server was doing her best dCan't say enough good things about Theory! Decided to come to this spot based on out of towner reviews with a group of 15 from San Diego to watch the Cubs home opener against the Padres. First off, the owner Joel is THE nicest guy and took care of us to make sure we had a great experience. The bar hTheory is a phenomenal bar. I work for a college and they helped me host an event for local alumni. Joel helped me coordinate for weeks, catering to my every need so I felt happy and confident for the day of the event. Then upon arriving, each member of the staff was so kind, helpful, and on their gGreat place to watch champions league games. We watched Arsenal Madrid. Service excellent, food ok I had a Mediterranean salad, and two Guinness pints. Great ambience and lots of TV screens
location: 9 W Hubbard St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA

name: The Green Door Tavern
review:
Had a drink. Awesome old school Speakeasy. The dark wood walls and decor look original. A lot of history here to admire while you sip your drink. Go past restrooms down stairs to Speakeasy The Drifter. Will need to get added to waiting list to get in.I‚Äôve been to Green Door Tavern before, but never had a bartender like autumn . I was in town again on a business trip and decided to stop by ‚Äî best decision I made all week. She completely changed the vibe. Fast with the pours, smooth with the banter, and just straight-up fun to be around.

She‚Äôs goCame here as part of the Barrel bus prohibition tour of Chicago. It completes the experience nicely. Love the fried Nutella sandy - I am too weak to resist üòÇ Service is great. They know what they are doing.Green Door is a great iconic Chicago tavern.  Food is hit or miss. For example, Scotch Eggs were great. Deviled Eggs weren't anything special. Grilled cheese was ok. Brisket on pretzel bun was incredible.Great bar that does the basics very well - good selection of beers and cocktails; music and TV sports on enough for you if you want and easy to ignore if you don‚Äôt, decent range of basic starters salads, sandwiches and burgers.

All this coupled with efficient and friendly service makes it easy to r

name: Cindy's Rooftop
review:
Delicious food and generous portions ‚Äî we tried the salmon, meat, and a roasted carrot starter, all outstanding. The atmosphere is great, and the rooftop view over Millennium Park is spectacular. You can grab a drink without a reservation, but I recommend booking ahead for the restaurant. DefinitelyWe went there on a Thursday with a reservation, they sat us down next to other people that were eating you‚Äôre literally shoulders to shoulders no type of privacy. Menu is pretty simple nothing crazy it is pricey but you pay for the location of the restaurant. We had a couple cocktails those were gooOur favorite thing was the garlic bread, best one we‚Äôve ever had! The scallops were good too. The tuna was different but good. My boyfriend also loved the oysters. Very nice view of ChicagoCindy‚Äôs Rooftop was one of the most memorable moments of our trip to Chicago. The view, stretching over Millennium Park and Lake Michigan, is absolutely magical‚Äîespecially at sunset, when the sky turns warm shades and the city lights start to sparkle. The atmosphere is refined yet welcoming, with frI recently had the opportunity to dine at Cindy's Top in downtown Chicago, and while the experience had its highlights, there were also several disappointments.

First and foremost, the views from the restaurant are absolutely stunning. You can't beat the beautiful skyline and the vibrant atmosphere
location: 12 S Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60603, USA

name: Matchbox Bar
review: Came here for a nightcap. Loved the vibe in there, everyone seemed to be ya ing a good time. They have a great variety of cocktails üçπ- we had their boulebardier and I personally wanted something that was not sweet and asked for a Tequila Martini üç∏ and it did not disappoint. I asked for ‚ÄúLa Gritona‚Äù Visiting town for a wedding and was looking for good cocktails, found this bar on Google Maps and it did NOT disappoint! I really liked the lowkey vibe and eclectic music selection. I ordered a pisco sour, then another pisco sour because it was so tasty! And very reasonably priced. The staff is realSuper cool place with great cocktails. Get a gimlet with a powder sugar rum, delicious üòã the place stands true to its name, not much bigger than a matchbox.Stumbled upon The Matchbox the other night, and man, this place is tiny but oozing with that classic Chicago charm. It's like squeezing into a CTA train during rush hour, but way more fun. The bartender, Zack, whipped up a killer margarita for around $12‚Äîtotally worth it. The vibe's cozy, making it If you love dogs go to this bar! I had just lost mine so Nadia put me on the corner next to a bowl of treats... Couldn't have been thirty seconds later three pomeranians are sitting at the door. That continued thru out the night.  Needless to say I didn't leave, and my soul was restored that night.
location: 770 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60642, USA

review: Arrived at the restaurant and the host just directed me straight to the bar top due to just being one person which I assumed everything else was reserved. The bartenders are very knowledgeable and friendly. The drinks were very good. I ordered the cucumber gin and tonic which was really good. I alsoI didn't have any food. The drinks were a hit!! Thanks to bartender Ruben!!! He was very comical and attentive to our needs. I came here for an event r&b event. They didn't disappoint.  Please come check out Roof on the Wit!!!This is a cool rooftop bar with a lively party vibe in the heart of Chicago. The drinks are excellent, and the service is outstanding. The bartenders and servers are super friendly. The music is loud and energizing, so if you're looking to stay hyped, this is the place to be. In addition to the mainCame here to enjoy an after work happy hour and loved it! We were a pretty big group but we were able to be seated fairly easily which is much appreciated.  The drinks were really great! Had a wide variety and you‚Äôll instantly earn cool points for having a Penicillin on the menu. Service was good tAbsolutely loved our evening at theWit Rooftop Bar! The food was delicious ‚Äì the Thai chicken pizza, in particular, was a standout and full of bold, unforgettable flavor. The cocktails were top-notch, expertly mixed and beautifully presented. The ambiance was vibrant yet relaxing, with a perfect mix

name: Gus' Sip & Dip
review:
Landed in Chicago last night and came to Gus Sip & Dip bc of a recommendation of a friend- this place delivered beyond my expectations. $12 for ea perfectly curated & beautiful cocktail- fries are so good you can't believe they're just handcut fries, Wagyu Sandwich & the cheeseDog!

Service was top Well done Lettuce!! Gus‚Äô Sip & Dip is Chicago‚Äôs new gem. The atmosphere is incredible and the food, the food is even better.

Continuing a tradition borrowed from McSorley‚Äôs in NYC, you get a choice of light or dark beer, for which you receive 2 beer mugs per order.

We ordered the French Wagyu Dip The Breakfast Martini was hands down my favorite, tasty and the little toast on top was a nice touch. The gin gimlet was light and refreshing, and the espresso martini was smooth and not too sweet, perfect pick-me-up. We also had the warm olives with parm, which made for a great snack, and the friesThis place is the best new addition in river north! $12 well crafted cocktails $6 happy cocktails.my favorite is the clover club! We loved the black truffle grilled cheese sandwich with tomato bisque soup and we absolutely loved the roasted chicken dip sandwich. The Cesar salad was a little bit saltThe atmosphere is unique and the food was great! You know it‚Äôs good when it‚Äôs packed with a line to get in at 5:00 in a weeknight! We got in line at 5:00 on a Thursday and were seated around 5:15 and then cashed out by 6:00, so service is quick. We had the burger and chili cheese dog and loved them

name: The Meadowlark
review: After entering the unassuming side door to Meadowlark we were greeted by a very friendly hostess. We were actually there to buy a gift card but decided to stay and check it out. The waiting area is separated from the main room and is quite small. We waited about 30 minutes to be seated. We loved theMeadowlark Bar is such a creative and memorable spot in Chicago! The drink menu is wild‚Äîin the best way. Each page is themed around school life, and the cocktail ingredients play right into that concept. Super unique and well thought out. I tried some bar bites too, and they were just as inventive‚ÄîeBeautiful place to experiment with drinks at. Chrissy (The Bartender) was extremely friendly. There needs to be a more clear understanding with reservations. I was told when it is a party of 2, reservations were not taken and that it was first come first serve. However 2 specific locations in the baMe and my hubby's all time favorite bar in Chicago! Every time we're in the city, we always stop by Meadowlark. We've had the privilege of trying three of their menus since their opening in 2023. They change up their menu every 8-12 months so you are getting a different set of curated craft cocktailI can see why Meadowlark made it to the top 50 bars in North America. Not sure if the theme continually changes bc the menu I had was different from the one on their website, but when I went recently it was space-themed. The cocktails were creative and spirit-forward. I liked Earth, which tasted ear

name: Bottega Louie
review:
Went for Sunday brunch and had a delicious meal. We ordered matcha latte, green juice, Belgian waffles, a√ßa√≠ bowl, farmers market breakfast, salmon & bagel, and beignets. All were delicious. We also got several macarons, a baguette and pretzel from the bakery. Delicious! I would recommend. Large ligWe stopped at Bottega Louie, just a short 4-minute drive from the Crypto.com Arena, and had a really enjoyable meal.

I ordered the Chicken Parmesan, which came with a breaded chicken breast topped with their house-made marinara, Grana Padano, mozzarella, fresh basil, Espelette pepper, and a drizzleThe bite-sized macarons were displayed by color, making me want to try every flavor. I ordered chocolate, strawberry, pistachio, and vanilla, and I loved how the flavors were rich yet clean. The raspberry cream doughnut was also delicious; it wasn't too sweet, and the cream filling was perfectly balThe restaurant is combine with bakery. The service was good. They came to check from time to time.

They served bread before foods. And I‚Äôd ordered gnocchi and it was delicious!

Only pity that the restaurant has strong echo noisy environment. Everything became loud.I haven‚Äôt had a bad experience yet. And I can‚Äôt say the food isn‚Äôt delicious. It‚Äôs actually quite solid. It‚Äôs not the best food I ever had but it‚Äôs also very consistent and the portions are fair. You‚Äôre coming here for the atmosphere. Big, bright, loud, chic and the options are plenty. I usually alw

name: Holbox
review:
Came here with a friend for lunch on Friday and this place totally deserves its Michelin star. We got there about 15 minutes before opening, so parking was easy and we were part of the first group in line.

Holbox serves Yucat√°n-style seafood tacos, and every single one we tried was incredible. We oI had huge expectation for Michelle 1 star. Long story short, it is not worth to wait 1 hour to get the food. I might try again if no line.
The octopus was good but not exceptional, the sauce was not aligned with octopus and not tasty.
The Aguachille was too sour and couldn't enjoy it well. Octopus Amazing very high quality seafood taco options at an affordable price. The Baja fish tacos were so crispy and so tasty, my wife loved it, we had to order a second round! The Baja shrimp tacos were also great and a good size compared to any shrimp tacos I ever had. The octopus tacos were cooked just Phenomenal food! Exceptional, creative, and incredibly delicious. I was first skeptical due to the long wait outside, but when you get in and are seated, the food order and delivery is fairly quick. Prices are absolutely reasonable for the quality. The lemonade was delicious. Definitely worth visitiSeeing as this was my first time dining here - I grabbed a little bit of everything. Here is my review by item:

Halibut tostada - 10/10 - Spectacular, by far the best halibut ceviche I have had to date. The fish is premium quality and melt-in your mouth and the exact right amount of citrus to spice

name: Girl & the Goat Los Angeles
review:
Might be a 20/10 now. Had maybe my best meal ever before and was scared I may be let down this time and can say without any hesitation I was not at all and loved every bit of it once again! Definitely my favorite restaurant ever! Group of 4 of us went and ordered the naan, kimchi sourdough, spicy haWe had such a great dining experience. The ambience was nice, the service was great and the food delicious! There was not one dish that we didn‚Äôt enjoy. We started off with grilled oysters and kimchi bread as appetizers but they went over a complementary naan for the long wait. All three were soooo Came here early with a reservation and our party of three was immediately seated. name: Redbird
review:
Great vibe, nice hospitality, can‚Äôt beat the setting. The food was good but not out-of-this-world good. Our favorite part was actually the free bread to start the meal. We weren‚Äôt told what it was but it was stuffed with a light cheese? and it was amazing. The crudo was fine but nothing unique. The As we acclimate to being parents and finding places that we can pop in and still have a good time with our baby, Redbird raised the bar.

We were able to walk in firstly get to order from the happy hour menu which does come with the requirement of being seated inside in their lounge area but it in iThe atmosphere is chill but distinctly upscale.  The inside seating has a fancy lounge vibe to it. We sat outside with the open air ceiling and it was very pleasant. The menu was not overwhelming but still had some nice options. The food was delicious. The drinks were on point. Great spot for a niceWe came here on the day the LA protests were happening. So things would have been quieter i am sure.

I highly recommend the prawns which were full of flavor. The snap peas were so refreshing and delightful.

I really liked the Cavatelli because it wasn't too heavy. The pork chop was prepared very wBeautiful restaurant, with pretty bathrooms.
Food quality is superb. Had the sea bass, smoked tofu and fig appetizer & mochi nut dessert.

Cocktails are very unique with fruity wine mix and carbonation.
Love the ‚Äúoutdoor‚Äù seating.

name: Maccheroni Republic
review:
I didn‚Äôt want to be generic and order what everybody else did. However, I did. Hahaha. I ordered Bianchi and Neri, and it was delicious! No wonder it is a popular dish. Pasta is cooked just right. Not too thin or thick. Sauce is creamy. Delicious. I added cheese on top, but I probably didn‚Äôt need itI thoroughly enjoyed my lunch at the Maccheroni Republic.  I appreciate all of the trees and greenery within the concrete jungle of downtown LA.
I ate the delicious salmon spaghetti with lemon and capers.  The service was quick and I witnessed many tasty dishes being served to tables of locals and tPastas on point! No reservations unfortunately so recommend going on an ‚Äúoff time‚Äù such as a weekday evening. We went on a Monday and didn‚Äôt have to wait. They have wines and cocktails available but you can bring your own wine for a $30 corkage fee. The pastas are the highlight here so definitely reI picked this restaurant for our group before the Pink Marrini concert tonight. Didn't know them before hands, just googled and couldn't wait to experience...

Cocktails: very creative with different mixes and very good. We had Passione and Watermelon Ciao. Very refreshing for a warm summer night.

It‚Äôs rare to find a restaurant where the food, service, and atmosphere are all equally on point. Stepping into this oasis downtown feels like walking into a trattoria in Italy ‚Äî such a treat. We‚Äôll definitely be back the next time we‚Äôre in LA.

name: Manuela
review:
Loved this restaurant including the vibe. Impressed with the albacore spread served with a bold rice cracker that was so large , you broke off a piece at a time and spread the delicious tuna. I would watch out for those delicious, buttery, flakey, rich, heavenly, satisfying house made biscuits with the side of honey butter!Manuela is a gem of restaurants. The atmosphere is like a peaceful garden, inviting you to sit & enjoy. The service was top notch, everyone made us feel welcome. All the food recommendations were perfect. name: Fleur Caf√©
review:
Best chilaquiles I‚Äôve had in a long while! The space is clean, pretty, spacious. Service is excellent, super friendly and quick. The hot chocolate was delicious. I also tried their banana bread, it was moist and tasty! It‚Äôs a hidden gem!What a little gem of a cafe. Only a 5 min stroll from the JW Marriott and perfect for a great meal any time of the day especially when they offer all day breakfast. They have a good menu which is also great value for money. They also pack your optional side servings for take away which is perfect whThe food was all nice and consistent. Only thing I didn‚Äôt like was the halloumi. Would come again and recommend coming here if you want solid food. The eggs were actually really nice too and I loved how you could get a side of roasted potatoes or veggies, which to me is really appreciated üòä

Also thThe food here was immaculate. She had the omelette and loved it, and I had the chicken kebab with pita. We split the chocolate banana pancakes. All of it was incredible. Even the kebab! Service was friendly and quick, and the view was nice outside. Park in the lot across the street, not behind the bDelicious for a small mom and pop place. Fresh ingredients, tasty food, good prices.  Will definitely come back.

name: Jurassic Magic
review: Cute little cafe, wanted to try it because I' currently on a mission to try all these new matcha latte/newly opened Korean/Asian styled cafes. Smelled amazing outside of it all the way to the back of the very long line. Very popular place but the line moves moderately fast. You really feel the care in the design and vibe of the space. The service is friendly, and the coffee is delicious. I just wish they offered more vegan options for baked goods to enjoy with the drinks. Still, a magical little place I‚Äôll hMy neighborhood coffee shop (by LA standards: I drive 10 minutes) and the nicest bar team I‚Äôve encountered. name: Alchemist Coffee Project
review:
I love this coffee shop! The coffee is excellent ‚Äî this was my second visit, and it was just as good as the first. If you ever find yourself in Welshell, definitely stop by this place. Highly recommend their coffee!Was staying in the area for a couple of days and we were able to walk to this cute little shop. Fun decorations inside very like steampunk in a way but for coffee.

Service was goods

My friends enjoy their coffees, so I‚Äôm not sure what they were drinking, I think they got the same the next day .

TIntended to pay a visit to their West Adams location, but apparently the listing was kinda misleading as it's not open yet. Having 2 existing locations in Ktown, the one at Pearl apartment was just awesome and I couldn't agree more when plenty other reviews called it as productive space. Yeah, just I discovered this caf√© by chance while walking around Los Angeles. The service is quick and very friendly. I spent some time there with my wife, she had an almond milk cappuccino, and I had an iced hibiscus tea.Been here twice so far and both times have been great.

The available syrups are not house-made, so I skipped on getting vanilla latte (my go-to drink) and got the Spanish coffee, which was great. Their Matcha latte was pretty solid too.

Btw, I loved their Basque cheesecake. It was delicious.

name: De La Tierra Caf√©
review:
you guysssss. this place is FIRE. workers are so sweet! the food is AMAZING. the vibes are incredibly cute. i‚Äôm so glad my gf and i stopped by on our way out of la. we had the avo toast, the house sandwich (made veggie friendly) and a pumpkin horchata latte. coming back for SURE. THANK U GUYSIf you're in the vicinity or staying at the Hollywood Hotel, visit this venue for for hot or cold lattes and teas. Coffee is a special bean from Mexico and each is made with care and ‚ù§Ô∏è from the owner. Maria is upbeat, efficient, courteous and cares about the customer.  Don't leave without somethingThis coffee shop was near our hotel so we stop there for breakfast, and it is a decision I do not regret at all !!!
The food was excellent. I took a breakfast sandwich.
The coffee is to die for !!!
And the atmosphere the cherry on top of the cakeThis Latina woman‚Äìowned coffee shop is such a hidden gem. From the outside it might look a little rough, but step inside and you‚Äôll be greeted with the warmest service and the most delicious food. I had the best breakfast sandwich I‚Äôve had in a long time, and the mazap√°n latte was out of this world.A very cute small coffee place. We were coming down from a hike and needed some coffee. We saw this and stopped by. I also got a breakfast bagel really good. Will come back to try more coffee drinks for sure.
location: 1144 N Vermont Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90029, USA

name: Yeems Coffee
review: the coffee at yeems is always a hit‚Äî super strong, high quality flavor with minimal wait time and fuss. their set up is extremely direct and no nonsense. very limited seating inside and parking can be fairly difficult in the tiny lot they‚Äôre in but the coffee and matcha are completely worth it. i reLovedddd the drinks here, I got the passion fruit drink they had and even though I‚Äôm not a huge fan of passion fruit it was delicious!!! I also tried a friends strawberry matcha and it was also great! The service was very fast and the girl that took our order was so nice!You smell Delicious coffee from the parking lot. Vienna latte is amazing. Holidays hours posted. Among all great cafes, I keep coming back here before I leave LA. Both hot and ice coffee are good.This shop has limited parking, and it charges a fee, so you need to find a spot on the street, which can be difficult to find. The coffee is good. I tried their Top 1 coffee, which is a bit pricey, but the taste is still very good. Highly recommended.Delicious lattes and fast and friendly service. Definitely would come back and recommend. Their buttercream latte was sweet, but not annoyingly so. The perfect balance of sweet, creamy, but the coffee still shone through.
location: 3033 W 6th St #107, Los Angeles, CA 90020, USA

name: Cafe Dulce (Little Tokyo)
review:
Cafe Dulce offers variety of tasty pastries, donuts and coffee. I tried hot Americano and the Tiramisu cake. It's a great pairing. My daughter loves the blueberry matcha latte. We will go back there again tomorrow.Nice caf√© in Little Tokyo with a great selection of drinks, sandwiches, salads, and sweet treats. Perfect for a casual stop any time before the kitchen closes at 6 PM.

Drinks from $4.00 to $7.25
They offer coffee (drip, espresso-based, cold brew, Vietnamese), matcha options (classic, blueberry, unsI enjoy drinking at Cafe Dulce. I usually get the Apple Spiced Latte and my Mom gets the Rose Tea Latte which is really good!! I enjoy the Foam of the Latte. Last Saturday I tried the Blueberry Matcha Latte and it is really good!! The Service was Good when I was going to get the Matcha Latte but theCame by for the Silent Hill event, and despite the line being long, the staff was efficient and got through all of us in record time. The special event rose latte and strawberry pastry were tasty! Excited to come back and try their regular menu next time.I & my wife very enjoyed going to this cafe in the morning, because is the morning is not that crowded, and can slowly enjoy breakfast sandwich & morning coffee at this cafe, the coffee is good, but the most delicious is the breakfast sandwich, the sauce on the sandwich is perfect not too rich and c

name: Dalian's Caf√©
review:
This coffee shop in downtown is a total gem! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, with plenty of cozy seating. The coffee is hands-down some of the best I‚Äôve had ‚Äî rich, smooth, and clearly made with care. Their pastries and small bites are fresh and delicious, perfect for pairing with your drink.

This caf√© is a hidden gem! I have drove by many times but today is the first time I stop in and I wish I did sooner. The cafe is very welcoming and the owner was incredibly friendly. The pastry I had was absolutely delicious, fresh and full of flavor.  The coffee was amazing. The service was excelleThe coffee is top notch.
Elegant serving.
The guys shift is much better than the girls one - after being help by the yesterday I fell in love with the place.  It my first time were today, u would be so sure.
The croissant was okI ordered a hot chocolate and a turkey sandwich. Both were so delicious ü•∫üíûüíìüíñ yesterday was my first time here, as my friend invited me; he said he comes here daily and loves it. The staff were amazingly kind. The ambiance.. it‚Äôs just so charming. There is seating inside and outside. I will return, aSpending my breakfast time during my business trip in LA in this cafe was a great choice. I like the pain au chocolate (I think the menu is chocolate croissant), croissant with turkey's meat, and kouign-aman. For beverages, I personally like matcha and vanilla latte. location: 530 S Grand Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90071, USA

name: Cafe Calle
review: I love to support local coffee shops and was so excited to find Cafe Calle! Street parking was pretty easy and I stopped in for a latte. It was lovely inside with lots of different seating options for work or chill. I ordered a hot oatmilk latte and the barista made a cold one, but very quickly replOrdered a iced Spanish latte with oat milk (half sweet) I always do half sweet when trying a new spot I don‚Äôt like my coffees too sweet and it came out really good. The ham and cheese croissant was amazing too. No complaints.Very cosy outdoor, bench and umbrella. Quick stop over to cool down  a bit. Of course, mostly for take away because very limited seatings. The drink is marvelous!Great vanilla latte! Roasted to perfection & a perfect ratio of milk and syrup combination, what a great little hidden community gem! Was passing through the area on the way to work & was hesitant to stop here due to not being familiar with it but it's high ratings review nudged me in the direction I tried the iced matcha latte, and it was incredible. Also tried the coffee cake it was nostalgic. The brownie is moist and delicious. We're definitely going to be a regular here now.
location: 3310 S Central Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90011, USA

name: Library Bar
review:
I love a bar with a concept and was obsessed over the library theme. Though not exactly hidden, the walls of books and intimate, cozy seating felt akin to a speakeasy. The contrast of the classic study aesthetic against the neon, almost cyberpunk-esque bar was surprisingly harmonious. Best of all, oNgl those fries changed my life lol. Super good bar food! Love this place. The atmosphere is great, there's really nice clean bathrooms, drinks are great, and the bartenders were so friendly. Music choices were superb, and not too loud. Small and cozy, so probably better for small groups or individuI‚Äôve driven past Library Bar for years and always told myself I‚Äôd stop in there finally made it last night, and I‚Äôm glad I did. The drink menu is creative and fun, with cocktails named after books (with clever twists on the titles), which really adds to the charm.

The atmosphere is relaxed but stylI just went for happy hour.  Had the fish sandwich, which surprised me how good it was. Very limited food menu but atmosphere and drinks were great. Don't know why I never had been to this place before. Kind of have to looking for it to find from the street.Cool moment and feel in the place. I am a bit of a drink snob so I was a tad let down with some things but I stress that's just me. No reflection on overall time at this place.
location: 630 W 6th St suite 116 a, Los Angeles, CA 90017, USA

name: Perch
review: Perch in Downtown Los Angeles is one of those rare places that makes the city itself feel cinematic. Perched high above Pershing Square, it offers a panoramic view that stretches from the shimmering skyline to the Hollywood Hills. It‚Äôs no wonder that this French-inspired rooftop restaurant draws botIt has a rooftop and a great environment. You need to go to the 13th floor first and then transfer to the 15th floor. It offers dining options and also has an outdoor area. The 16th floor is the rooftop, where the night view is fantastic. The food taste is just so-so, but the environment adds a lot We valet parked right in front and it cost $15. We went up two different elevators and came out into an old antique room..the decor was from the early 1900s and wonderful. Paintings of naked ladies over the bar..cool chandeliers and lights and event he floor was really old patterns and the dining arThe food was amazing! The view was spectacular! I came here for the happy hour menu and everything we ordered was delicious. They also have a rooftop lounge for you to enjoy a drink and chit chat with a friend. I'd definitely recommend this place!This place was delicious! We got the steak frite, Chilean sea bass, the pesto gnocchi, and the provence plate . For dessert: almond cake, chocolate pot de cr√®me and mango sorbet. All of them were very good!! For the Vegans: the Provence plate is vegan fyiüòâ. The atmosphere was very nice as well. Over
location: 448 S Hill St, Los Angeles, CA 90013, USA

name: Frolic Room
review:
Went here on a Saturday morning. Late morning and fortunate to find parking in front of the bar. Please wasn't busy.

No frills about the esthetics of the bar. The sign is classic Hollywood, but very small inside. Beer selection wasn't great, so you may want to stick to cocktails.

Overall, don't exCool little bar, not a lot of room, but I think this is the type of spot you pop in on the way some where else so not a lounge type of bar. We met up with friends here before a concert and its was nice. Bar tenders were very attentive and made sure we were taken care of while we were there. I ordereWelcoming, No Frills bar! While walking down Hollywood Blvd, I stopped to look in and this Friendly bouncer (pictured) said, "go on in and check it out," glad we did. Fun people, neat lights on the ceiling that I now know have been featured in movies. If you want a good, inexpensive adult beverage aA must-do experience when you are in Hollywood. It‚Äôs iconic. Always crowded before a show at the Pantages so getting a seat can be a challenge. We managed to snag a table after a few minutes and the staff quickly removed the prior customers glasses and cleaned the table, which was appreciated. name: Death & Co Los Angeles
review:
One of the best bars in America. Slotting us in on a Friday early shift, the bars atmosphere is intimate, high end and accessible. Friendly staff walk more nervous customers through the phenomenally balanced menu in a way that helps without them feeling patronised. More experienced drinkers will finDeath & Co LA is hands down one of my favorite bars in the city. The cocktails are always creative, balanced, and beautifully presented, the mixologists here really know how to combine flavors you won‚Äôt find elsewhere. On this visit I tried the Kissaten Caf√©, Hail to the Thief, Sun Dream, Morning DoThis chic, dimly lit bar gives speakeasy vibes with a lengthy cocktail menu and amazing food. The lamb burger is the best I have ever had. Raven and Mike always provide fantastic service and drink recommendations. Reservations are strongly recommended.This was one of the best experiences from start to finish and had everything you can think of in a bar. First off, I was running late and they messaged me and changed my reservation to accommodate me. The drinks and food? SPECTACULAR! Over 24 drinks to choose from and to celebrate my birthday, the TDeath and Co. LA is THE date night location!

Partner and I celebrated our 7 year anniversary there recently and not only was the ambiance amazing but the food and drinks were up to par.

We started our night with an order of the Esquite and let me tell you..this is a great take on a childhood cultu

name: Everson Royce Bar
review:
Came here for a quick drink and got the Pineapple Daiquiri. Really enjoyed this rendition on the Daiquiri as it added a sweet acidity without being too much. We came here early in the day so not busy at all but would have loved to stay a bit longer. Nice bar on the inside and a patio on the back.Great patio for big groups. You don‚Äôt have to worry about splitting the bill! Every one can get their own tabs. The waiter/serving staff are always on the move making sure everyone is satisfied with their order or if they‚Äôre ready to order more. Great in the summer time. Great happy hour specialsI went to this spot last night on a whim and was pleasantly surprised.
The host, bartender and staff on the floor were kind and quick to assist. Blake was exceptional making suggestions on the menu and getting our food out quickly.
I really enjoyed that you could customize your espresso martini.the burger and fries were fine but was a decent deal for the happy hour. the chipotle dip the fries came with was really good. also got the soundcloud celebrity happy hour drink and that was good.Found this bar after trying to go to other spots in DTLA. I‚Äôm glad the other places didn‚Äôt work out because everything was great here. Drinks were amazing, the food was really good with multiple options for different diets. The ambiance was chill but lively. There‚Äôs also a large patio area that is p

name: Broken Shaker at Freehand Los Angeles
review:
Made a reservation here to have a nice rooftop terrasse view of LA. Nice view, cool that can you can access the pool. However, drinks were overpriced but bland. Also I was not pleased and uncomfortable to see the way we were charged- a credit card being "held" by the waitress before ordering the driHad a cocktail on the patio on a warm day. Good quality and fairly priced - the patio get you away from the ‚Äòstreet below.‚Äô Very nice pool as wellWe wanted to eat at a place with a view of the city that had a laid-back, relaxed atmosphere. We sat at the bar since it was just thntwo of us. The bar tender was attentive and helpful. We ordered the curry shrimp skewers, the fish tacos, the chicken sandwich, and some fried plantains. Overall, theROOFTOP WITH KILLER VIEW!!

Food - 4
Service - 4
Ambiance - 5
Price-quality-ratio - 4.5

If you‚Äôre looking for a rooftop bar with a killer view of downtown LA, Broken Shaker is the spot. The vibe here is laid-back yet stylish, with colorful decor, twinkling lights, and a pool that adds to the atmospGreat rooftop pool with bar and dining area. The drinks are great.

name: Seven Grand
review:
I've never seen a place like this in the US. They have so many different types of whisky including Scotch and Japanes (like Hakushu 18 years). Eden also recommended great Rye and Scotch whiskies that I liked so much! Thanks Eden!Checked this place out after hearing some great things. Popped in shortly after opening and had Javier at the bar. Dude is super chill and very knowledgeable, talking me through different bourbons and teaching me about what I'd probably enjoy the most since im not super knowledgeable on whiskeys andI visited this place with my friends, where we enjoyed drinks, played pool, and listened to live music. The worst part is the waiting time; we have to wait 15 to 20 minutes each time we want to order drinks.I have loved coming here throughout the years on special occasions to drink with friends. It's a very chill spot with an old time vibe (built in the early 1900s) and has a good atmosphere. Seating is very limited, mainly has a bar area, 2 pool tables and a few booths off to the side (if you're luckyExcellent spot & great drink selection.  The Bartenders are great, the crowd is great & feels more casual to business casual.

Great cigar smoking area with seating on the side patio.  Also a great place to play pool.  The drinks at happy hour are pretty good and it‚Äôs a solid chill place to enjoy a

review:
Treehouse has overtaken the club scene here in LA. Don't take the negative reviews serious. There is a reason why this place gets packed every weekend! The vibes are good, the dress code is enforced. name: The Escondite
review:
Awesome Chicago style & themed bar, killer ambience inside, outdoor section and extra picnic benches out front to chill with crew. Live bands & music, Malort shots, antler chandeliers, Old Style, and all!
Dog friendly too but bring earmuffs for them, it might get loud.
Don't pass it up, drop in for Great time here. Meticulously decorated, has a saloon/tavern vibe that I was looking for in LA. It seems like they have free live music all the time, which is fantastic. It is adjacent to skid row so be smart about how you're traveling to and from. There is no clear signage - look for the opening inGroovy alternative + underground music including live bands on weekends. Cool dark atmosphere inside with lots of red lighting + crazy animal trophy heads on walls, sort of a weird David Lynch hunting vibe that's hip right now. Bar looks very legit old school fancy wood from old times. There's a nicI ventured to this bar one Saturday night, drawn by the live streaming of the LA Derby Dolls bout, despite having no prior knowledge of its existence. Nestled away from the bustling nightspots of Little Tokyo and the Arts District, this establishment provides a unique, secluded atmosphere. What setsSuper hidden place. It's pretty empty so if you don't like crowds it's actually really nice. I was surprised to see there's a bar that has Malort, so that was a cute little memory of Chicago. The staff is friendly and they had live music when I was there
location: 410 Boyd St, Los Angeles, CA 90013, USA

name: Tiki-Ti
review:
Classic tiki bar with a great selection of delicious drinks and a unique atmosphere. The bartenders are generous with their pours, everything has a little extra rum. Service is excellent, but the location itself is very small so expect to wait 30 minutes to an hour to get inside.First time here, and we absolutely loved it. It was definitely worth waiting in line for, and this comes from someone who avoids lines like the plague! The atmosphere was super fun and the drinks are fantastic. They were definitely not watered down, so very reasonably priced. We're definitely lookiThis is the second oldest tiki bar in Los Angeles. It‚Äôs tiny place that‚Äôs covered floor to ceiling with amazing tiki decor. Great drinks! I had the Ray‚Äôs Mistake and the Oooga Booga. Get there early unless you want to wait in line.No food. Bar only. Extremely limited seating so come early. Parking is a nightmare. Street only from what I could tell. Lucky you don't have to pay meters if you have a handicap placard in California.

Amazing cocktails. This place is an institution. Order the Ooga Booga or the Toro. Decent selectioAn iconic must-visit tiki bar. Definitely get in line around opening because it‚Äôs a bit small, but everyone inside is absolutely joyful! Great drinks and an adorable spot.
location: 4427 Sunset Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90027, USA

name: Crazy About You
review:
We had a fantastic dining experience at Crazy About You! The atmosphere was warm and welcoming, and the food was absolutely delicious;  every dish was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented.
A special shoutout to our waitress, LAURA, who went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we nThis terrace is a hidden gem! With breathtaking views of the city bay skyline, it‚Äôs the perfect spot to unwind. The ambiance is cozy and inviting, making it ideal for family gatherings. The service is exceptional, with friendly staff that make you feel right at home.

Overall, the combination of greI loved the cocktails here!üçπand my favorite dish was the baby back ribs.  The place feels tight when it starts to get busy, but has great service. If I come back I‚Äôll probably do it for dinner, I think the view and atmosphere are better at night.During a quick stop in Miami, after a LONG day of flying, my husband and I stopped here for a quick dinner. The ambiance was chill, sophisticated and warm. The service was top-notch and the food & drinks were excellent! It was our first visit but definitely NOT our last!!!this place was pretty dang solid! the decor for both inside and outside was very cool, loved the atmosphere. the outside has a direct view of the water and was nicely shaded at night. for our appetizers, i got the asian spring rolls and my boyfriend got some type of cheese dip and both were very goo

name: Naked Farmer
review:
I had such a great experience at Naked Farmer!  Picked up some takeout for my husband and me; and server Rebeca was incredibly friendly and helpful, she explained the menu and even offered me a free small sample to help me decide. Her kindness and attentiveness made the whole experience so easy and Very tasty salad in a quick serve counter based restaurant. The staff was friendly, and the food all seemed to be of good quality. The only reason it wasn‚Äôt 5 stars is due to the cost and limited indoor seating. Over $20 for a chicken salad is a bit steep. As long as you don‚Äôt mind the prices, you wI had such a great experience at Naked Farmer thanks to Lore and Lenia! They were both so helpful and kind while assisting me with my takeout order. They made sure everything was packed perfectly and even double-checked that I had everything I needed. Their positive attitude and excellent customer sThe food here is immensely fresh, good portions, and most importantly delicious! Tiago was so kind and patient to us with our questions as it was our first time here. We will be coming back! It‚Äôs a nice hidden gemIf you‚Äôre looking for a quick post workout meal that‚Äôs health, has protein, AND doesn‚Äôt give you a food coma, this is it. If that‚Äôs not enough, the team is always so welcoming‚Ä¶.name dropping in 3, 2, 1 Lenia, Georgina, Mirna, and Karim. Tell them Stan recommended you üòâ they‚Äôll hook you up hahahah

name: Rusty Pelican Miami
review:
Not our first time at this long-standing waterfront restaurant on the Rickenbacker Causeway, but it was definitely one of the most memorable! The stunning views of the Miami skyline made the perfect backdrop for our anniversary celebration, and what truly made the night special was the outstanding sWe chose The Rusty Pelican for a special dinner after getting engaged, mainly for the stunning views of the Miami skyline ‚Äî and it did not disappoint! The atmosphere was perfect, and the food was incredible. We had the surf and turf with the tomahawk steak, lobster, and shrimp mashed potatoes, all fMy sister, a local, said the Rusty Pelican is one of the best restaurants in Miami and she was not lying. The location is amazing! It's right on the water with beautiful views of the city. We went for their Sunset hour/happy hour and it did not disappoint. The food was so flavorful and delicious andWe celebrated my best friend‚Äôs birthday at Rusty Pelican and couldn‚Äôt be happier with the entire experience. From the moment we arrived, the service was outstanding ‚Äî warm, attentive, and on point all night.

If you‚Äôre into cocktails with show-stopping presentation, you must try the Tiffany‚Äôs. WhileFood and drinks were delicious, the place was clean, aesthetically pleasing. Our waiter Matias was amazing, made us feel welcomed and comfortable. Pricing was decent considering the quality and quantity of food üî•  Highly recommend this place!

name: Komodo Miami
review:
Chose this place to dine for our 8th anniversary together. Duck was fantastic, the skirt steak was good. The Brussels sprouts were so on point! We also had the blue fin tuna sushi. Perfecto!!!! Our server Justin made us feel like we were the only ones in the restaurant! A great ambiance, grown and sKomodo Miami absolutely killed it this year with their Miami Spice offerings. My friends and I got to experience a variety of their small dishes, each delicious in their own way. The drinks were refreshing and perfectly balanced. Beautiful ambiance with good music in the background. The service was WOW is the best way to describe our (my GF and I) experience at Komodo Miami on 8/31/2025. Our first interaction was with a bartender named Jennifer. She poured great cocktails, and was friendly, welcoming, and gave some great recommendations! Over the top service!!! Thank you Jennifer!!!

name: MILA
review:
I planned a quick 3 night getaway in Miami for my husbands birthday weekend celebration, and Mila was one of three restaurants we visited during our stay. Out of the three, Mila was my favorite!

I made a reservation several days prior, and  when we arrived, we were seated promptly. It was completelMila exceeded all of our expectations! The food was absolutely outstanding, everything tasted incredibly fresh and flavorful. We tried the tiraditos, the wagyu steak, and sushi, and each dish was prepared to perfection. The quality and presentation were truly top-notch.

What made the evening even mI came to Mila for the first time with my best friend and had an amazing dining experience. The vibe is very elegant but relaxed and I loved the aesthetic. Even sitting near the kitchen was a good experience. Mario and Melvin made sure we were comfortable and had the best time. I‚Äôd love to come backWe chose Mila for our anniversary and loved everything from food to service. We tried caviar potato millefuelle, gyoza, spicy hamachi and spicy tuna. Everything was amazing, especially the sushi!! Highly recommend. Our server Andy was the sweetest, great with suggestions and offered us champaign andWe're in Miami for our honeymoon & our friend said we had to come here and we're so happy we did! The restaurant is beautiful, the atmosphere is great, and the food is absolutely insane. The flavors of everything we tried were unreal. name: Fiore Caffe Miami
review:
My husband and I visited Fiore Caf√©; a humble, small scale caf√®, last week while we were in town. From beginning to end, we were greeted with smiles and treated favorably.

Our waitress was very polite, and checked in on us quite frequently. Our order arrived swiftly, fresh and hot. Our waitress conThe food was absolutely amazing! We got the strawberry cheesecake pancakes (not on the menu but just ask!), the fried chicken sandwich, the french toast, and the steak eggs. Mafe was our server, a sweetheart! The area is so cute, and there‚Äôs a little parking garage right next to it, and parking is vI stopped by Fiore Caffe Miami for brunch and really liked the cozy, cheerful vibe. The avocado toast and pistachio pancakes were delicious and fresh, though the sweet dishes were a bit too sugary for my taste. The place has a nice open layout with a chill, welcoming atmosphere that makes it easy toFiore had great food, service and vibes! Our server Cristina took great care of us and was very sweet and attentive. The food was soo good and the cocktails were original and savory. I got the crispy chicken tacos and my partner the chicken waffles and they were both delicious. Would definitely comeTraveled for a weekend trip to Miami with a friend and stopped in for brunch on a Sunday morning.  Staff super friendly, service great.  Tiramisu french toast was amazing!  Applewood bacon also incredible.  Coffee surved with warmed froth for a gourmet touch.  Parking ticket for the garage next door

name: Magdalena Coffee & Houseplants
review:
I absolutely loved Magdalena! They offer a great selection of coffee (including pour over). I chose the iced V60 option and it was so aromatic and enjoyable. The place has a great eccentric playlist in the background. Easy to have a light conversation and still enjoy the groovy music. Staff is frienüòãüòãüòãüòãüòã
I've been a loyal fan of Magdalene Coffee in Wynwood since they opened, and it's consistently one of my favorite spots! Their coffee is always fantastic, brewed to perfection every time. You absolutely have to try their Danish pastries‚Äîthey're incredibly delicious and taste so fresh. It's the Magdalena welcomed me with a perfect parking spot right in front and with friendly faces taking my order! I loved the vibe of the shop, the light that comes through and all the plants. Such a great atmosphere to work and eat. I had a vanilla latte which I enjoyed so much! Will be coming back to try I don‚Äôt really know how living in this neighborhood for almost 3 years and been a coffee snob I didn‚Äôt find Magdalena Coffee earlier.

I‚Äôm happy I made it here. I love the ambiance, decoration, all the natural light they have and more importantly the quality of the coffee. Their coffee is just how IOne of my favorite spots for matcha! The lavender matcha is excellent. Their coffee is just as good. There is a selection of pastries that I highly recommend. Also, a small selection of plants and merchandise. There is some street parking and a small lot at the end of the block on a side street.

review: I have to say, from the moment you walk in, you feel welcomed. I loved the vibe and the atmosphere it has. The crew is very friendly and the food is amazing. Get yourself a Cappuccino and add a little bit of splendar! You will thank me later.Food is amazing. Depending on the time you go and your group there will be a wait time. But it is definitely worth it. The portions are big. I wasn‚Äôt able to finish my food and took it to go. Everything is so good even the drinks. If it‚Äôs coffee or mimosas it‚Äôs made to perfection. Not only that but Ran up on this place by accident, we were trying to visit Miami Slice, saw the long line and decided to investigate and what we found was some of the best food service and atmosphere you can find in Miami. (Angel the host was on the job, thanks for looking out for me and my lady) he got us in as sooJuan was absolutely incredible! From the moment we sat down, he greeted us with the warmest smile and made us feel right at home. His attention to detail, patience, and genuine kindness made the whole dining experience unforgettable. name: Vanilla
review:
If you're looking for a cozy spot in downtown Miami that feels like a little slice of heaven, Vanilla Cafe is it! From the moment we walked in, we were charmed by the super cute, warm ambiance -- it's the perfect blend of modern and inviting.

The staff truly made the experience unforgettable. Anna I tried several desserts and they were great. Shakshuka (pictured) is very far from the original recipe and this dish should have a different name so as not to mislead. Will come back only for desserts. Meringue pistachio raspberry is my favorite today.We had such a lovely experience at Cafe Vanilla! The coffee was rich and flavorful, made just right. We also tried the Kyiv cake and the Ferrero cake - both were absolutely delicious.
The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, making it a perfect spot to relax and enjoy a treat. Highly recommend this cafThis place was such an unexpected find but so delicious! The vibes are super chill and welcoming and the staff is, too! The brownie and vanilla croissant were amazing and well priced, too! We will definitely be returning!The syrnyky are simply amazing ‚Äî both the classic and the vanilla ones! The borscht is top-notch too. The service feels just like back in Ukraine: everything was served quickly, the staff was polite and welcoming. It‚Äôs a real pleasure to visit and support a Ukrainian place like this. üá∫üá¶
location: 117 SE 2nd Ave, Miami, FL 33131, USA

name: {petite} maman
review:
The sandwich I ordered was delicious and I am definitely coming back to try the beautiful pastries I saw in the counter.
The staff was very nice, only gave it 4 stars since this isn‚Äôt a sit down kind of place. You have to order at the counter and wait kinda deal no big problem.
The area is beautifulAlthough I‚Äôm still quite new to Maman, I‚Äôve already tried four different items from the menu, and each one has been absolutely delicious. I‚Äôve even discovered a few new ingredients through their creative dishes, which has made the experience even more enjoyable. On top of the amazing food, the staffQuaint little spot. Went early so was able to get in and out.
All of the pastries were excellent. Small location*Service was so friendly and helpful. Our drinks (coconut water Matcha & vanilla matcha latte) were refreshing and so tasty. The goat cheese berry scone and avocado toast was fire! 10/10 all around. Will be back again and again!Very good quality drinks, and everyone is so nice! I definitely would recommend. Super cute and trendy inside also!!

name: Rosa Sky
review:

Definitely a great spot for a fun night oMyself and my partner are on holiday from the UK and personally had a great experience here. We paid a ‚Ç¨50 deposit which was expected and we went during happy hour so a lot of drinks and bites were only ‚Ç¨10, so we got a lot for our money. Our server Lacey was really attentive and friendly too! The bI had an amazing experience with the cocktails here! The drink was not only beautifully presented but also perfectly balanced in flavor ‚Äì refreshing, smooth, and crafted with real attention to detail. A true masterpiece in a glass.

Special thanks to Ramon, the cocktail master, who went above and beLove Rosa Sky for their awesome happy hour, spectacular views and great selection of drinks ! Came here on a date and reserved a table for happy hour, great deal on the drinks and bites !!! Highly recommend reserving a table. Views are amazing and this is one of the best rooftops in Miami !!!
