name: Lola bar
review: If you ever find yourself at Lola Bar, do yourself a favor and ask for Natalia ‚Äî she‚Äôs the kind of waitress that takes your dining experience from good to unforgettable. From the moment I sat down, Natalia‚Äôs attention to detail and warm, professional attitude stood out. She made sure I never needed Amazing service and good. Drinks were strong in the best way and flavorful. Melissa was great and had such great customer service. Definitely will be back!Amazing spot in Miami! The cocktails are creative, refreshing, and so much fun, and the vibe is always lively with great music. The staff is super friendly and the food hits the spot for a fun family afternoon. Perfect place to enjoy drinks with friends ‚Äî highly recommend!Lola Bar in Miami has a great vibe and stylish atmosphere. The drinks are strong, creative, and well-crafted, definitely a highlight. The only downside is that the music can get really loud, making it tough to have a conversation at times. Still, it‚Äôs a fun spot to unwind, meet people, and enjoy theMaria Camila was friendly and a great waitress. We had a  great time here. Will be back to enjoy an amazing experience.  Its a great latin vibe.
location: 401 Biscayne Blvd S118, Miami, FL 33132, USA

name: Blackbird Ordinary
review: Sean at Black Bird Ordinary is truly one of a kind! He‚Äôs not just a bartender‚Äîhe‚Äôs a mixologist with his own signature style. From his incredible spicy mix to creative, perfectly balanced drinks, every sip was a hit. The vibe he created with great music, friendly conversation, and an all-around welcGreat place to go dancing! The bars are well kept, and there is a good variety. Even though they were packed, it was quick and easy to get a drink, as the bartenders were very efficient. The music was great, and I love that there are different styles in the 2 rooms.Best bar/club in Brickell , been coming religiously for a while now. The scene is amazing,it  has two sections , in the front its like a night bar where the Bartender are amazing, my boy Tony knows exactly what I like to order and bring it up before me even saying Anything. And the back is more of aLADIES NIGHT TERRIBLE!!! 10/14/25- I endured RACISM with one of the bouncers. I‚Äôve got my phone stolen and wallet before!!! its broke dudes waiting to catch you lacking. This been my SPOT since 2021! As a local guide go somewhere else where all ladies are valued,less watered down drinks, and where mThis bar/lounge is a "hole in the wall". I had a good time. The atmosphere is too dark though. The 4 stars is for the fact they charge a service charge along with the price of the drinks. The bar tinder was actually pretty nice, though.
location: 729 SW 1st Ave, Miami, FL 33130, USA

name: Tipsy Flamingo Cocktail Bar
review: Love the decorations and the overall atmosphere of the place. Bartenders are quick to get you drinks and the sound is super punchy, with some nice fat bass. It's not a super spacious place, which I think adds to its charm. Usually on week days you find people coming from work for happy hours, includJosh was really imperative in helping us with our happy hour options! He was super sweet and extremely friendly in helping & just talking to us while it was a random Tuesday night. He also made it very obvious that he wanted to take the time to make our drinks super tasty & garnishing them beautifulThis hidden gem in Miami is the perfect blend of trendy and cozy. My group stumbled in here on a weekday and it ended up being the best night ever! From the neon signs that provided the perfect backdrop for photos, to the bubbles they showered us with randomly throughout the night‚Äîit was a dreamy amThis place is such a vibe, we came from another bar that was crazy crowded where we couldn‚Äôt even enjoy ourselves and this place was a great switch up. Great people, atmosphere, music, and drinks. It was decorated for Halloween which was cute and the dj was on pointüëåüèºWill go back every time I'm in Miami. Amazing cocktails. Amazing service. They pay attention to details in the cocktails.  Great atmosphere.  Don't be weary of the dark tinted windows out front. Go in and have a drink you wont regret it.
location: 40 NE 1st Ave #101, Miami, FL 33132, USA

name: Mama Tried
review: YALL. WHAT?! The new Mama Tried menu is ABSOLUTELY PHENOMENAL. The drinks are up to their original standard, but they're modern and absolutely delicious. I would absolutely recommend checking out the new menu, hang out for the vibes & and definitely get a cocktail from Dominique! She's an amazing baLove the vibes in here and djs! I stumbled upon this after a concert and it was a fun time. I came here on a solo trip and their espresso martini frozen drink was delicious. I only had 1 drink but their drink list looked delicious and fun! They have 1 pool table as well.Had Happy our drinks. Major vibes, music was lively and bartender was fine fine‚Ä¶. The drinks did the what it had to do (IYKYK).My go-to spot in Miami!! This is THE SPOT for pre/post AND game. Every time I come here I have a good time with friends, the DJs are always on point and Matt is the absolute best!!! This has become my non-negotiable for a night out in Miami and I will keep coming back like I have been. Definitely a Fun spot to relax and party after a day of traveling. Was right by the hotel and easy to walk to.

name: Over Under
review: The food is very promising. The burger is decent and good fries. It‚Äôs sloppy and messy, dripping wet sauce, but tastes good. The crab hush puppies - ate they supposed to be that dense instead of gooey?  Atmosphere is lively and soon filled up after 5pm, but the music that night (heavy mental) was noWe went on happy hour and ordered two Paloma‚Äôs. They were frozen and incredible with a generous amount of tequila. Then for the appetizers we ordered the loaded fries with pulled pork and it was really really good. As for the spicy chicken sandwich it was alright. It wasn‚Äôt spicy at all and didn‚Äôt hThis place is really cool. I‚Äôm local and just stumbled across it looking for a place open late for dinner. Their kitchen is open until midnight. The food is surprisingly good and fresh. Everything seems homemade and they have some of the best French fries I‚Äôve ever had. I got the veggie burger with So my wife and I were looking for a place that had vegetarian food late night (12am) and food a spot called over under.. at that point it had club music, but we sat outside and got a vegetarian burger and truffle fries, with a Caesar salad. name: Lost Boy Dry Goods
review: Nice fixture and neighborhood bar downtown that has survived all the building and street closures. Happy to see vegetarian and vegan options which were also very tasty. Nice selection of cocktails and place to hang out with colleagues and or friends. Cool atmosphere and dog friendly!!If you‚Äôre looking for the best pizza of your life, Losy Boy is the place to go. From the very first bite, you can taste the quality ingredients and the passion they put into every pizza. The pepperoni pizza is simply outstanding‚Äîa perfect balance of crispy crust, perfectly melted cheese, and pepperoClosest thing to a dive bar I could find in downtown Miami as an out-of-towner. Some of the best bathroom graffiti I have observed in my extensive bar-going experience. Bartenders were attentive and friendly. Drinks were strong enough and reasonably priced, for Miami standards. A little unnecessarilLost Boy Dry Goods is a cozy, dimly lit pub in Downtown Miami with a laid-back, inviting atmosphere. I had a hot dog and pretzel, both of which were delicious. The beer selection is top-notch, and the music sets a great vibe. With no table service, you order at the bar, which keeps things casual andIn port for the day, working on a cruise ship, and needed to find a place to have some food and drinks with a proper American feel (and find a place that was open at 1pm on a Monday). name: Caroline
review:

My food came out fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. The staff were so friendly and made tTerrific experience! We were in town for a music festival (!) and found this spot. Food and service were both excellent. The coffee and Green Goddess salad to start set the tone, then the green chile enchiladas (me) and sweet corn cake Benedict (her) were flavorful, fresh and most enjoyable.

ShoutoWow! That pretty much sums up my experience at Caroline. Wonderful food and top notch service from waiter, Aaron despite the lunch time rush. It was pretty loud during this time and but you can still talk. If you come at this time, the outdoor seating (weather permitting) might be best for an easierI'm struggling to understand the glowing reviews and high star rating for this place. We arrived for our 8:45 PM reservation at 8:30 PM. The host, with a terrible attitude, directed us to wait 15 minutes upstairs for a table that was already ready. When we returned at 8:45 PM, he ignored us until anSituated just blocks from the State Capitol of Texas, Caroline is nestled in the corner of the street. name: Corner Restaurant
review:
I had such an amazing experience while catching a late night bite. I came back to the restaurant 3 times before I left Austin. The vibe, energy and customer service was great. Everyone was down to earth, personable and welcoming. Kudos to all the staff throughout my stay.
‚Ä¢Carmine
‚Ä¢Kelsey
‚Ä¢Gary
‚Ä¢BraCame here on a whim after looking for restaurants in the area with good reviews. Service was excellent & what stood out the most.

Tried the brunch burger & wife had the burrito. Good portions & left feeling satiated. Food was yummy & got the job done.

A little on the pricier side for what it was, Great location and venue overall, service was unbelievably slow saw a few groups sit and leave during our brunch, luckily we were in no way in a rush but it was still frustratingly slow. Food was amazing, shrimp and grits are a must, breakfast burger was awesome as well. $70+tip for 2 person brunch Our waiter Adam was absolutely the best and so were the bartenders! However the kitchen staff needs a little work. For dinner, I ordered I ceaser salad and the wagu burger medium with no special sauce. The ceaser was to die for. My burger on the other hand came out well done with the SAUCE! Our waitFor a casual business event, Corner Restaurant is ideal. Its convenient location attached to the Marriott, diverse indoor and outdoor seating options - each with a unique vibe and quality food and service make it a standout choice. The staff are are friendly, too.
location: 110 E 2nd St, Austin, TX 78701, USA

name: Sour Duck Market
review:
Went during a happy hour, ordered a double with queso, a lemonade, a dreamscicle and a non-happy hour pretzel. I was happy with the food and ordered everything on my phone, which felt really convenient - but when I checked my credit card the next day, I noticed the amount the business was charging mPatio happy hour is the place to be. A large set of picnic tables with lots of seating and a great happy hour menu! The smash burgers were delicious and the drinks refreshing. The fries and squash didn‚Äôt hit the mark.

Officially updating my review - been back at least 5x since my original review. WI really wanted to like this place, their baked goods look stunning and the vibes are great. I went for brunch to scope it out for a date and ordered 3 dishes and a coffee to give it a fair chance. Again, everything came out looking spectacular. But to me, it didn't taste like much. Everything was bCrispy edged thin double smash cheese burger was pretty good. Drinks were also good. Service at the table from the QR code so easy to order and all very informal.Love the outdoor area, great places for family and kids.
Happy hour is fantastic price for an amazing burger, drinks and pastries.
Definitely recommend the cayenne coffee drink. The fries are phenomenal with housemade ketchup better then any ive ever had.
location: 1814 E Martin Luther King Jr Blvd, Austin, TX 78702, USA

name: Corinne Austin
review:
Ellie provided us with a great friendly  service. Make us feel welcome. She assist me with my gluten free diet and help us with our options to enjoy our dinner experience. The food is amazing and tasty, we had avocado hummus, fish tacos replacing tprtilla with lettuce a. Wagyu burger with fresh frieLet me just say if you want the best server there, ask for Ellie! Hands down awesome service. Food was great and loved the espresso martinis. Thx Ellie for going above and beyond to make our experience in Austin great! Sincerely‚Ä¶the Florida girls Corinne has been a great place to stop for brunch on our visit for ACL. Our server, Ellie, created a lovely experience through her sweet, helpful, bubbly personality, making sure to answer any questions about the menu and even giving us local tips to make our travel experience better over all! 10/10My family and I visited Austin from Newfoundland last month, and Corinne was a highlight of our stay at the Downtown Marriott. Ellie served us twice while we were there and she was wonderful. She listened carefully to our families allergies and made sure our food was safe. Her suggestions from the mFabulous meal from apps to dessert.   Kudos to our server Skylar who not only provide top notch service but gave us a list of recommendations for the city!

So may things on the menu sounded great.  We started with the crab croquettes which perfect.

For the mains, Diver Scallops and the wild Mushro

name: Acre 41
review:
Our first visit to Austin for a comedy show Saturday night. Acre 41 was a few minutes away from our hotel. It was amazing! Our server Ram, was great! The atmosphere was intimate with low lighting. The food was wonderful. We shared the wagyu meatballs which were flavorful and went well on the bread wExcellent food and service! Ram, our waiter was very friendly and helped us order the best meal to celebrate my sweethearts 60th birthday! We will be back and not just for a special occasion.I‚Äôve been to many fine restaurants but this one was the absolute best! My wife and I enjoyed a lovely dinner and fortunate the have the most amazing waitress, Hannah. Atmosphere was spectacular and dripping with elegance and sophistication. Food was amazing and I could only handle one drink from theI visited Acre 41 for brunch and was immediately impressed by the ambience, absolutely beautiful. The d√©cor and overall vibe of the restaurant were top-tier and made for a great first impression.

For my meal, I ordered the Wagyu flat iron and eggs which came with potatoes. I requested my steak wellExceptional service from start to finish. Ram was highly professional, attentive, and went above and beyond by providing excellent recommendations. He anticipated our needs before we even had to ask, which made the entire dining experience seamless and enjoyable. The food was absolutely delicious, a

name: Geraldine's
review:
Very unique food but it was amazing! Forgot to take a photo of the steak, halibut and lamb because we ate it so fast! It was amazing. The staff were so friendly and attentive.Sure! Here‚Äôs a polished and natural rephrasing of your review:

‚∏ª

I‚Äôll definitely be back. The food was delicious‚Äîespecially the omelette, which was outstanding. The potatoes were tasty, the sausage fresh, and the eggs cooked perfectly. The biscuits were a bit dry, but that didn‚Äôt take away from thWow. As a chef myself, I think what chef Andrew Amador and the team at Geraldine's really have something special here. The live music, the addictive craft cocktails, the flawless composed dishes leaving the kitchen had my girl and I thoroughly impressed, and our pallets pleased. Thank you TY for youWent for the jazz brunch, the musicians were great and the ambiance was top too. It wasn't too loud and we were able to carry conversation without having to shout or worry about loud tables.

The downside was definitely the eggs benedict. It was a tad overpriced, undercooked, and surprisingly, had tVictoria provided the best service, and the musicians were wonderful.

My eggs bene at jazzy brunch was MUCH better then the other recent review so my be hit or miss. Delicious in every way.

name: Zanzibar
review: Such a great spot! The open-air vibe with all the greenery is beautiful, and the seating is really comfy. We loved the tropical cocktails. The poke bowls were fresh, flavorful, and the portions were just right. Shoutout to our server Dee‚Ä¶ she was so sweet and made the whole experience even better. DZanibar Is a 10/10 experience. They have the ambiance that you for looking for intimacy or with a group. The aesthetic set up is very pleasing to the eye. They are located at the perfect spot downtown as you can see the lady bird lake and also see the busy skyline of Downtown Austin. The servers werThis is a five star restaurant but keep in mind, This is not five star as in fine dining nor as in a hearty meal. This is more like small meals that you share with your friends over drinks. It‚Äôs definitely a night time before the club vibe, but I would not recommend this if you want a solid dinner oThe food and drinks are fresh, tasty, and surprisingly reasonably priced. The music and scenery set the right atmosphere.  The crew is fun with the tropical outfits, and especially Christopher W. providing delightful and fast service at the bar and bringing it poolside for fun in the sun!Absolutely loved the vibe of this place! Drinks and ambience was outstanding. And the view! üòç my only feedback is I wish they had more food options in the menu. Other than that 5/5
location: 304 E Cesar Chavez St, Austin, TX 78701, USA

name: Aba Austin
review:
Aba had been on our list of restaurants we wanted to visit and were finally able to get in this time around. The wait was worth it. The food is amazing!!

Great choice of cocktails and I'm pretty sure we ordered one of everything on the menu. The haloumi and fish were favorites from the main menu anWe had an amazing experience at Aba! From the moment we walked in, everything exceeded our expectations. The atmosphere was beautiful, relaxing, and full of great energy.

Our server Aiden truly made the evening special ‚Äî attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu. He went above and beyonI had such a wonderful dining experience at Aba Restaurant in Austin! Everything from the service to the food was excellent. Noel was my server and was so friendly, attentive, and incredibly knowledgeable about the menu‚Äîshe made the experience even better.

I ordered the short rib hummus, fried potaThis was my first time at Aba, and we came in with high expectations since we love Mediterranean food. I‚Äôve had the chance to try several Mediterranean restaurants in Austin, and honestly, the one that stands out the most for me is The Peacock.

At Aba, the only dish I truly enjoyed was the crispy sTrifecta of greatness!
Wonderfully executed, fast, accurate process even though the waiter knew this was our first time. He calmly listened to every question and answered in detail following up with great insight on what we had ordered.
Super cool experience! We WILL be back! New bestie!

name: Ember Kitchen
review:
Every single dish here was unique in its own way and had very sophisticated flavor profiles that fancy food tends to bring. This was one of the priciest restaurants I‚Äôve visited, and I wasn‚Äôt disappointed.

I ordered a Pisco Spritz as my drink to start, which wasn‚Äôt too sweet and had the right amounWent here for Sunday brunch with two friends, loved it! The vibe was super chill, perfect for a date or a small group. We got the Caviar Bites (on tortilla) and Burrata Bread to start, both delicious. For mains, we had the Steak & Eggs (that hot sauce was so good), Chorizo Hash, and Josper Chicken SWent here for dinner today, everything from start to finish was spectacular. Had the pleasure of being served by Claire and Colin, both of them were fantastic. The food was so delicious, I already have my next meal here picked out. Highly recommend the filet (either the full portion or the small bitI‚Äôm in between 3 and 4 stars. The atmosphere was super cute and appeared inviting. We had a 5pm reservation made for 4 people. It was 3 adults, a toddler and a baby who would spend the meal in her car seat or on a lap. We were immediately met with ‚Äúoh your reservation said 4 not 6, this might be a pWe went to Ember for my birthday and then our anniversary dinner. Both experiences were 10/10. The service is always amazing and they went above and beyond to treat us for the occasion. I love the drinks and the attention to detail for each ingredient. Although pricey, the food is worth the $$

name: Hestia
review:
The food was fantastic, especially the small bites! A touch too salty for my liking, but overall very flavorful. The restaurant is not big, so it‚Äôs best to book a reservation in advance. They even prepared a handwritten card signed by all the staff for my husband‚Äôs birthday, which was such a thoughtThis place is amazing! The blending of smoke and fire is evident, thriving in their menu. Not overdone, subtly mixed in the right proportion to create unique and amazing flavors throughout the dining experience.  The wait staff are well trained, working behind the scenes of diners as a well oiled maWe celebrated our anniversary with friends last night and had an amazing time. Our service was phenomenal and we appreciated the little touches to make our night extra special. I will dream about the charred corn and the halibut for the rest of my life! Everything was great but these 2 were the absoThe chefs tasting menu is phenomenal. This was our 3rd time visiting a Michelin star restaurant and is now our new favorite. Service was just as good as the food. The pace of each dish was perfect as well.Puts the fine in fine dining! Everything about this place was 10/10. The food was immaculate and service even better. It was fine dining without it feeling stuck up which is one of my favorite things. You can have conversations with the wait staff and service and still felt elevated.

Do the Tasting

name: Terrible Love
review: Terrible Love is fabulous and serves a lovely, smooth, delicious cappuccino! The housemade grapefruit brown sugar syrup is delightful and perfectly pairs with the espresso. I love citrus, and grapefruit elevates the cappuccino above the typical orange flavoring. Amazing! The cute green mug they servI would definitely recommend the cold brew with grapefruit syrup, it‚Äôs so tasty and refreshing, also very unique to this place. Their matcha and banana drink is also pretty good!! The banana in no way overpowers the matcha instead both flavors meld pretty nicely. Also their breakfast tacos are delicI‚Äôve been coming to Terrible Love consistently for almost a year now, and I can confidently say it‚Äôs the best coffee in Austin. Brian, Dema, Grace, and Mia always deliver top-tier customer service, which is the cherry on top of their already incredible coffee. You won‚Äôt regret spending your time or I was just saying how it‚Äôs been a long time since I‚Äôve had a coffee that impressed me. I wish I lived closer to this place‚Äî truly a hidden gem! The place is so cute and love the branding for pictures- but most of all, our drinks were so, so good!! Grapefruit brown sugar latte & terrible latte ‚Äî mostWhen I envision an adorable, hole in the wall, coffee shop ‚Äì this is it. The service is wonderful. The coffee is delicious. And I couldn‚Äôt think of a better spot for coffee, especially in the cute Hyde Park neighborhood. I‚Äôve been coming here for many years, from the time they were in a small traile

name: Flora Coffee & Culture
review: Popped in here on a whim and were pleasantly surprised! The cafe is tucked inside a yoga studio with a few cozy spots to sit and enjoy the calm lobby. We were happy to see that non-dairy milk was not an up charge and the syrups were homemade. We both had delicious lattes that were temped perfectly aThey share their space and identity with a yoga studio, and that‚Äôs important to know upfront. It‚Äôs not just two businesses coexisting - they‚Äôre part of the same operation, and some of the reviews you‚Äôll find reflect the yoga experience. This can be confusing for anyone expecting a dedicated caf√© expGreat coffee shop. One of my absolute favorites. It‚Äôs not a big space, but there‚Äôs sufficient seating. It is beautifully decorated. It‚Äôs a good spot to do some work, read, or socialize with a small group. The coffee itself is great. Overall, one of the very best coffee shops around.I love Flora! Such a great neighborhood coffee shop! Their coffee is amazing and you can taste that their beans are roasted to perfection. The baristas are always so welcoming and good at remembering who you are.I had to check out Flora coffee due to the incredible reviews. This place seems like it‚Äôs the front to a yoga studio. It‚Äôs in a strip mall, but it‚Äôs cute and serves basic coffees and drinks, although no pastries or other breakfast items. The store is nice and clean and has a cute layout even with a

name: Magnolia Cafe
review:
Magnolia Cafe ‚Äì A Perfect Austin Kickoff Spot!

We started our day at Magnolia Cafe, and it was the perfect move. The landscape hash was hearty and delicious ‚Äî definitely a meal that keeps you fueled for a day of exploring. We split a pitcher of mimosas, which set a great tone, and the atmosphere waI've been having the occasional dinner here since the mid-90s, more frequently in the beginning but less so in the last few years as I don't find myself around south Congress very often anymore. Last Sunday, we decided to swing by, in part for old time's sake, and I'm glad we did. Magnolia Cafe is sI have to admit, Magnolia Cafe has been in my list of places to try but somehow it never happened. Today, because we're in the neighborhood, so we decided to visit one located in the South Congress Ave. After putting the name down to get a table (a straight forward process that just need to scan a bThis place is seriously super cute! Service was amazing and the food was delicious. While you wait you can purchase a beverage out back, and we only waited about 15 min. Seating consists of indoor and outdoor. Parking lot can be busy, but there is a side lot and parking in the back. Def worth the waThis was our second visit, although this time on Saturday around noon it was kind of disappointing. Both host staff was not friendly or welcoming, just matter of fact.-no smiles! Our server was very friendly but very distracted  and not very attentive to us. We had to wave her down a couple of times
location: 1920 S Congress Ave, Austin, TX 78704, USA

name: Desnudo Coffee: East Austin
review:
We stopped by Desnudo Coffee during our weekend trip to Austin and ended up coming back three mornings in a row‚Äîit was that good. It‚Äôs a small coffee truck inside the Webberville food truck park, which also has great breakfast spots like Veracruz Tacos and a kolache truck right next door. Super convGreat coffee with a smooth and balanced flavor. Tried the tira-miso and white vanilla miso with orange blossom - they both were really good. The environment/vibe is very energetic and lively. The staff were super friendly and the service was also great. A bit on the pricier side though.Desnudo Coffee in East Austin is an absolute gem and totally worth the hype. I tried the Matcha Uji and the Brown Sugar Miso Latte, and they are some of the best drinks I have ever had. The flavors are smooth, rich, and perfectly balanced.

If you visit on a weekend, expect long lines between 8:30 aI‚Äôve been on the hunt for the best coffee in Austin and, wow! Totally found it. The flavor is good and it‚Äôs consistent throughout. You know it‚Äôs good when there is a line at 2pm for 15 minutes to get coffee! The barista was super chill and they really have a great atmosphere as well. Tiki huts and LWhat a great find and awesome environment. Coffee and matcha were excellent. When we first arrived it seemed the line might be too long, but don‚Äôt worry because the wait is not long at all.
It was pretty cool they would come and give sample to everyone waiting in line, and they have multiple people

name: Prana Caf√©
review:
Rating: 4.3/5 [take out]

Such a cute spot to hang out! They were literally playing a guided meditation while we sat outside sipping our drinks--super peaceful vibes. They have an extensive menu, including daily specials, spring/summer protein smoothies, their regular smoothie offerings, and a hot tNew favorite brunch spot! The cacao smoothie and pranacavo toast were absolutely delicious. Amazing service too!
Such a vibey, peaceful outdoor patio.
I will definitely be back!I‚Äôm not one to write reviews because I work in service industry but wow this place is not friendly at all. I was standing at the window while both the girls inside were just looking at me and finally came to open the window. She was super unpleasant seemed like I was bothering her? If I ever treatedBeing all the way from New Zealand it‚Äôs always amazing seeing people still working even on Christmas, the staff were very humble, happy to see you and the place has a very relaxing vibe. The smoothie presentation was immaculate, very tasty, filling and vibrant. Best smoothie I‚Äôve had in a long long Beautiful space with incredible smoothies and top notch service. I stopped by to kill some time before my flight and wish I could spend hours here! Great work spot too and chill music.
location: 1623 E 7th St, Austin, TX 78702, USA

name: Haraz Coffee House
review:
Visited Haraz in Austin and really enjoyed the experience. I tried their tea, coffee, and a sweet, and everything was excellent. The tea stood out the most ‚Äì so flavorful and refreshing.

The place itself has a beautiful vibe with amazing music and ambiance, and even their cutlery is aesthetic and wI got the rose milk cake and the iced mufawar, and it is absolutely delicious. It is a little pricey $7.50, but it is worth it! The other drink is the matcha with mango which my friend got, and was also very good. ‚ô•Ô∏èüáæüá™‚òïÔ∏èI ordered the cheese cake and the chai. They both had such a rich flavor and very distinct, homey tastes. I also really enjoyed the atmosphere, it felt a very personal and comfortable. Everyone was very welcoming and loving. 10/10 place, I really want to go back to try everything else on the menu!Been here a couple times. Love the service and the drinks, specially that mango matcha! Shout out to Keyly! Always nice and greets you with a smile!I‚Äôve got say, great tasting coffee and great tasting pastries. The environment was nice and enjoyed people watching from the bar type seats.

name: Mozart's Coffee Roasters
review:
Good place to visit with your loved ones like family wife friends and all. They have the best coffees and desserts. I love strawberry cheesecake and chocolate frappe. evening sunset timing is the best time to visit as they have outdoor seating.This is my favorite outdoorsy coffee place in Austin ‚Äî and hands down my favorite waterfront coffee spot. The lake views are stunning, especially at sunset, and the outdoor seating makes it perfect for relaxing and a must go if you‚Äôre visiting the city.

This place is an Austin classic for a reason.The coffee and desserts here are absolutely amazing! Every sip and bite is perfection. The ambiance by the lake is superb ‚Äî relaxing, scenic, and the perfect place to unwind day or night. Whether you‚Äôre catching up with friends or just enjoying a peaceful moment by the water, Mozart‚Äôs never disappoiGreat place, gets busy quick

Mozart‚Äôs Coffee Roasters is a true Austin gem, offering a perfect blend of scenic views, great coffee, and cozy vibes. Nestled on the shores of Lake Austin, this spot provides a peaceful escape from the city, with a spacious lakeside deck that‚Äôs ideal for studying, catcMozart‚Äôs is a beautiful space by Lake Colorado. More than a coffee shop, it felt like a cozy hangout by the water (saw many small groups of students chilling and working there). name: Better Half Coffee & Cocktails
review:
Better Half has been on our radar for a long time now, so we popped in for a late weekday breakfast.

The property is really nice with a number of inside seating spots as well as plenty of outside seating under some lovely, old oak trees.

We ordered the Breakfast Sandwich (with sausage), the Fried I‚Äôve visited this restaurant three times, and it‚Äôs consistently solid. My recent Saturday brunch really stood out. The food is flavorful and well-executed, with a thoughtful concept that shines through in the menu. The space is clean, modern, and stylish, creating a welcoming vibe. My only gripe is Truly one of the most mediocre places I‚Äôve been to that is trying to be trendy. The breakfast sandwich was so underwhelming for the price. No seasoning, no salsa, no sauce. Just a bunch of fried elements without seasoning. It was very one note and nothing to it. Difficult to eat.
Coffee was okay, muGreat Vibe and Good Food, Definitely Worth a Visit

This is my third time coming to Better Half, and once again, it didn‚Äôt disappoint. I ordered the half Chop Chop salad, the single chicken bacon burger, and a veggie burger.

It‚Äôs hard not to like this place. The amount of property they have means yWe loved this place so much on our trip to Austin that we went a few times during the week. We didn‚Äôt have too long of a wait each time but we were there during off season and not peak hours. There‚Äôs plenty of outdoor seating which was so nice on a warm day. name: Neighbor Coffee & Friends - Burnet
review:
Got the iced bourbon caramel latte (one of their specialty drinks) and it's delicious. Caramel with a savory finish, but not too strong to where it overpowers the espresso flavor. They also do punch cards!I came because of the great reviews and ordered an iced latte and sausage biscuit, which I've been getting at a lot of places lately.

The latte tasted like coffee-flavored milk, and the sausage biscuit was stale and dry, like it had been reheated and sitting around for a day or two.

The cashier waFood truck very conveniently located on the way to work. The espresso handshake is phenomenal. They also have some small bites (loaf, biscuit, sausage biscuit). Great service!Rating: 4.6/5

We were in the area, ordering lunch from one of the other food trucks, when we stumbled upon this coffee truck. The bourbon caramel latte caught our eye, so we decided to give it a try. It looked like there was only one person working and taking orders, so you might have to wait a bitDivine every time! Love this spot! They cater to every palette - from lightly sweet lattes to decadent shaken espressos. Great service and a stellar vibe!

name: Edge Rooftop
review:
Located in the JW Marriott on the 5th floor around the corner from the pool.  Their hours are 6-12am everyday.   Hours may change when weather begins to cool down.  On Sunday they have Sunday scary night where they have a selection of martinis for $10.00.  I tried the Red Lotus for the first time, wWe loved the vibe up there! It‚Äôs beautiful. There‚Äôs a great view of the Capitol building. We were there for a conference, and the Edge was a nice place to sit and talk afterward.

The food portions are huge and tasty.

Our server was incredible! She took great care of our group of six.We had an amazing day in our cabana celebrating our friends bachelorette weekend!  Colin was an amazing server and made the day so much fun.  He was super attentive and personable. Enjoyed the comfort of the cabana and would definitely recommend!Great view! Great place for few drinks at the end of a long day. Live music was perfect. Drinks recommended by Jae did not disappoint. Jae was very friendly!!! I‚Äôd def recommend the Edge Rooftop and we are def coming back.This is such a amazing rooftop bar, Colin recommended me the soco marg and guess what? Was the best margarita that I ever tried, I like to put sugar on it and was just delicious same as the nachos. We had a such a good night for my best friend birthday, thank you so much Colin for the good attitude
location: 110 E 2nd St, Austin, TX 78701, USA

name: The Dead Rabbit, Austin
review:
The food was tasty and unique. It‚Äôs a very large area and they played a lot of Irish music, which was nice. The place atmosphere, wise-Just seems very conflicted about what they want. It‚Äôs Irish, but also very tropical. There is sawdust on the floor, which is very unique to the culture. However, youHidden gem!!!
Scotch eggs is deliciously crunchy with perfect soft yolk. The deviled eggs is out of this world. The sliders hit the spot. I had Irish espresso martini. That was so smooth and delicious. I had a great service. Fast! The atmosphere is sexy & stylish... Great spot. Check it out!Loved The Dead Rabbit. I brought some foreign guests and wanted them to experience 6th Street, and I thought this place was the best decision.

The food was amazing. The fish and chips were amazing, and my lamb chops were the best. The mint sauce was so delicious.

My friends ordered the mussels andA nice restaurant famous for its amazing Irish cocktails, good food, vibe and ambience. The staff is friendly and took care of us.
The service is quick and you get everything as how you ordered. They don‚Äôt mess up even if the place is packed.
We ordered different cocktails, chicken pot pie, chips anWe came here on a friday night, the atmosphere and service was perfect. Coming to food, chilli shrimp campis was really good. The remaining food was pretty average. Coming to the good part, the drinks were really good. Mainly the presentation of the drinks were awesome, all my friends loved those cu

name: The Roosevelt Room
review:
Upscale cocktails with a cool ambiance!

If you like mixed drinks this is the place to go.   They have a great mix of traditional cocktails and their own creations.

It‚Äôs also very educational as the drinks are arranged by era from prohibition to today and ranked by boozy-ness!

Lawerence was very fRating: 4/5 [dine in]

We were excited to try The Roosevelt Room since they've won so many awards, but honestly, it fell short of our expectations. The place is dimly lit and gives off Prohibition-era vibes, but makes it hard to see -- especially if you're trying to take photos or videos without usiAfter being out shopping on a very hot day, we walked past this place and decided to call in for a refreshing drink. It is a very cool bar with a very large selection of cocktails, all of which are responsibly priced for Austin. Our bartender Tom√†s made the visit definitely worth it. He is very knowWent for drinks and enjoyed our time. Expansive menu but the server was really helpful. So many great cocktails. Loved the chalkboard above the bar details time periods and drinks!A top-tier cocktail experience! The Roosevelt Room offers a classy yet comfortable atmosphere with expertly crafted drinks.

üç∏ One of the best espresso martinis in town!
üç¥ Great happy hour snacks‚ÄîI haven‚Äôt made it for dinner yet, but I definitely will.

The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. A mus

name: Midnight Cowboy
review:
Midnight Cowboy is such a unique and unforgettable experience! The atmosphere is one-of-a-kind‚Äîintimate, cool, and perfect for anyone looking to enjoy a night of truly great cocktails. The drinks here are not just tasty but carefully crafted, with so much attention to detail. You can immediately telAmazing drinks menu, each and every cocktail is beautifully crafted. The menu is fun too and takes you through a journey. They change their menu periodically. It‚Äôs a speakeasy and not easy to find. Also, I recommend reservations in advance as this place is quite small and is famous and full. Had a gMidnight Cowboy is everything I imagined it would be and more! A speakeasy always adds to the fun of a night out and this is one of the coolest I‚Äôve been to.

When you make a reservation (this is a must) you‚Äôre given a name to select on the callbox. Buzz the name and the host will let you in.

I wasVery laid back environment with fun drink menu. The speakeasy vibe add to the mysterious atmosphere of the summer menu, inspired by the toro cards.Love the intimate setting. There are only 8 tables. Technically, it's reservation-only, but walk-in might be accommodated near their opening time at 5 pm. Their cocktail menu is interesting, a 6-chapter story on cowboys vs. aliens (Texas with a quirky twist!): Highballs, Stirred and Down, Mahattanas
location: 313 E 6th St, Austin, TX 78701, USA

name: Speakeasy
review:
No food here, so grab a bite before visiting. The ambience was great and the drinks were decent. The old fashioned was heavy on the syrup, but after adding a double shot it evened out. Espresso martini was just what the doctor ordered. Live music seemed like it would be good, but we had to leave befThis place was very fun and of course it helped a lot that I was with a fantastic group of people. The food was very good as were the drinks. I enjoyed the atmosphere and the ability to actually talk a lot with my friends. We had a great timeNot what I thought of when I saw speakeasy. I was expecting a trapdoor or something of the sort but it was just old school decorations. And lots of stairs. There's one side that goes all the way up to the third floor but then you have to go all the way down to switch more stairs to go up to the secoGreat place for live music. We had a work function here and it was a blast. We had bowling, pool, shuffleboard and ping pong, along with 2 stages of music. Plenty of bars and servers to handle the crowd.

Will definitely be back when in the area again.Great place for live music. The upstairs roof top patio is off the hook. There's usually a Dj and full bar. Smoking area.

The dance floor is awesome for live music. Two bars on the second floor. There is not much seating area unless you pay for it, but you get full service from a full bar and food

name: Azul Rooftop
review:
Great place to hangout for drinks. This is our go to spot when guests visit from out of town. No need to stay at the hotel for access. I do recommend to book a table at least a week ahead. They also have a pool.Beautiful rooftop experience, especially as night fell. It was more of a small plate experience,  set in outdoor lounge furniture - comfy but not supportive of you have a bad back.  We stared oft with a cheese and corn based dip- esquites- with highly seasoned corn chips.  It might have been the higHostess was super sweet! The view was nice but that‚Äôs about all that‚Äôs good about this place.

The server was not friendly at all and the drinks were not good.Anthony and Sabrina made sure I was taken care of from the moment I walked onto the rooftop! They were incredibly accommodating and quick with providing the food and drinks that I ordered. They also are super sweet individuals who made me feel like I‚Äôm hanging out with old friends. Shoutout to theseThe rooftop pool was nice for the occasion - it was our friend‚Äôs birthday and we rented a cabana. The staff was friendly (Sabrina was wonderful), the drinks were good, and the food was fine. Definitely on the pricey side but for a special occasion with friends, it was enjoyable.

name: Whisler‚Äôs
review:
Rating: 4.4/5 [dine in]

Our friends wouldn't stop talking about Whisler's $0.75 martini summer special on Wednesdays from 4-7 PM, so we finally made time to check it out. We got there around 5:30 PM and luckily didn't have to wait in line to get in. They handed us two white drink tickets for the maWonderful character and authentic decor. Walls are covered in signatures, drawings, etc! They even have sharpies available if you want to sign. We sat outside and had seating right away on a Sunday afternoon. Lots of fans and misters available outside. Drinks were wonderful. Wide variety of options This place is where the hype outweighs the flavor. Big, crowded, and trying way too hard‚Äîeach $25 cocktail was a messy mix of ingredients that tasted more like a bad smoothie than a drink. Bill was $100 for four drinks and left unimpressed. Cool vibe, but pure hipster tax.Super fun and eclectic bar with indoor and outdoor seating. Craft cocktails and very nice staff. They‚Äôll also make you anything based on your flavor profiles too. We loved the cocktail happy hour menu and candlelit ambiance inside.I was walking past when I found this cute little place. Needless to say I was not disappointed! The mezcal bar upstairs has almost an ‚Äúillegal speakeasy‚Äù vibe to it just adding to the already amazing selection and service. Ideal date spot and some beautiful vibes and ambiance. Andy in the mezcal bar
location: 1816 E 6th St, Austin, TX 78702, USA

name: Mean Eyed Cat
review:
My absolute number one favorite bar in Austin and probably all Texas!  Great atmosphere and super nice and fun staff!  Always a fantastic time when you come here.  Walls are so interesting with old Johnny Cash posters and art, stickers and stuff to talk about.  Great merch too, get a hat or shirt!Atmosphere is always awesome, def one of not number one fav bar in Austin, huge patio, huge! And always chill even when busy. Gabriel was great, made the weird drink request i asked for and chatted for a moment as i came in after work alone, cool to small talk with someone while unwinding, better thThis place is so cool! I'm a huge Johnny Cash fan so it was awesome to see all the Cash memorabilia.  Shelby is such a great bartender, she went out of her way to chat with my husband and I, and tell us about the history of the bar.  I will definitely make another visit on my next visit to Austin!Shelby was great. I came into the bar and she tried to sell me a timeshare in south Austin, but it was a great deal. After a couple a beers, I caved but it was overall a pretty decent deal. She waived her commission. 10/10 would recommend.This. Place. Is. Amazing.
The staff was so so nice. Decor in here is so cool. It‚Äôs mostly Johnny Cash but everything about it is great. If I lived in Austin I would frequent this place all the time. The outside seating is just as great. If you are in the area visit this bar!
location: 1621 W 5th St, Austin, TX 78703, USA

name: Nickel City
review:
Is this the best bar in Austin? It‚Äôs in the running!

This is not your hipster bar‚Ä¶this is a true Texas dive bar.

They have a great bourbon selection at fair prices.

Bartenders are top notch! The food is delicious! Better not touch my tots!Cannot visit Austin without going to Nickel city! The food is delicious,  not the cocktails are even better!!! I always get the pink drink and tater tots!! Their bourbon selection is impressive!Atmosphere was divey but still welcoming. Joey was awesome, super attentive and personable. I will come back just for him ü´∂üèºWe went here for national hot dog day! Had some great dogs, exactly what you want when you want the classic! Nice frosty beer too! Pet friendly as well!Used to love this bar. Used to be the dive bar with great mixed drinks. Things are not going great.

Went in on Labor Day for drinks, food, and to pick up a t shirt as a gift. It was moderately busy. They're not serving cocktails because they're too busy and they took at least as long to explain tha
location: 1133 E 11th St, Austin, TX 78702, USA

name: Six Seven Restaurant

Gorgeous views, great food with generous portions, and surprisingly reasonable prices for the location. It‚Äôs classy but not too formal _ perfect for hanging out with friends, taking photos, and enjoying the vibe. Our server, Justin was friendly, attentive, and made thDelicious meal- but make reservation. We were waiting for our room to be ready and enjoyed a meal - there were no tables available and only smaller bar tables to eat our meals- it was so busy. Definitely reservations. We stayed after our cruise.
The hotel also has a small cafe. But the food was deliBeautiful view, day or night. Absolute wonderful service~
The bread, the salad, the clam chowder, and the firecracker shrimp were all very good. Can't wait to go back and try more items on their menu next time I'm in Seattle.

name: The Pink Door
review:
TLDR; go for the dessert, drinks and appetizers (in that order)

We came in for a late lunch on a weekday and were very surprised to see how busy they were.

Food: between the two of us, we ordered 2 appetizers (mushroom crostini, arancini), 2 mains (eggplant penne, spaghetti and meatballs), a drinkThe meal was a delightful experience from start to finish. The seafood was incredibly fresh, with clams and mussels cooked perfectly in a rich, buttery broth that carried just the right touch of herbs. The crisp bread added a wonderful contrast, soaking up all the flavors. The salad was refreshing, If you‚Äôve never been, find a way to make a reservation! You arrive at an unassuming ‚Äúpink door‚Äù in an alleyway, and it opens up to a beautiful sprawling restaurant with packed tables. The place is bustling with live music, views of the bay, rustic Italian food, and apparently, at times, cabaret and Placed a reservation via OpenTable (highly recommend). Those without a reservation were told it was a 1 hour 45 minute wait. Server was nice. Live music in the front area as you walked in. It was nice and warm inside. Got the bolognese, lasagna and apple pie. Very good!What a fabulous find! Started with a bottle of Planeta Rose ($53) accompanied by the freshest Bruschetta ($22)! The tomatoes on this appetizer were so red and ripe and BIG! Small Caesar ($15) was enough for 2 people. Lasagne ($27) was heavy with plenty of garlic and herbs paired with 3 meatballs ($2

name: Canlis
review:
Canlis is an absolutely beautiful restaurant for a special occasion with your partner or family and a beautiful view of the city! The service is good and everything you would expect in a fine dining experience. The food is also quite good!

I left off a couple of stars only for a few reasons:
- the We had an incredible evening here. The service is top notch. Our waiter, Mack, knew everything about every item on the menu, and described them perfectly. We never felt rushed, even though we asked a lot of questions. The support staff was very stealthy at times, when I would realize I had new silveIt was ok. Wouldn‚Äôt come back for an $800 meal. It was our 8 year wedding anniversary and it was swept under the rug, no one really cared. Dont expect anything for your anniversary. The couple next to us got a free bottle of champagne though for the ladies birthday. For anniversary really they don‚Äôttldr; uninspired tasting menu, disinterested vibe from staff

I've been coming to canlis for the last 15 years, I usually try to visit at least once a year or catch any new updates, such as a new chef. I was interested to try the updated menu.

Overall, the visit was average and each visit has noticOne of the Finest Dining Experiences ever. From the beginning, the valets, to the friendly hostesses, to the server to the management was absolutely impeccable. The food was not only incredibly tasty, but presentation was beautiful. The service really stood out. Overall, a top notch dining experienc
location: 2576 Aurora Ave N, Seattle, WA 98109, USA

name: Alder & Ash
review:
Sat at the bar, nice place. Convenient for a quick but yummy meal.

The Adler and Ash burger was tasty. I wouldn‚Äôt say it‚Äôs special but decent. No blue cheese stuffed olive for my dirty martini but the server made up for it by being so attentive.
Happy Hour was pretty good. $10 menu list was pleasanFood exceeded our expectations!  Great portion and good value. The restaurant is part of the Sheraton hotel, so it‚Äôs a bit difficult to find.  The address will take you to the back of the hotel where you‚Äôll be greeted with a sign telling you to go to the front of the hotel.  Not ideal and a bit wastJoyce was amazing!!!!  We are from Canada and first time in Seattle and at this restaurant. Service is top notch , breakfast had the best Ava ado toast I‚Äôve ever had and the decor was sensational!!!  Highly recommend.  Jim & Michelle ‚ù§Ô∏èGreat burger and sampler platter. Everything here looks amazing! Just was craving a good burger tonight. Drinks are well thought out and made well. Would highly suggest this place if your tired of restaurants missing the mark.This is a really beautiful lounge, the furniture is so plush and comfy. Came for HH before an event at the Paramount.  Food options were really good. Hh drinks were tasty also. Servers were very attentive. We would definitely come back here again.
location: 629 Pike St, Seattle, WA 98101, USA

name: Lola
review:
Amazing. Amazing. Amazing. My friends and I were speechless‚Äîliterally silent‚Äîbecause we were too busy savoring every single bite. Each dish was a perfect balance of flavors, and our amazing server made the experience even better. She suggested we go family-style so we could try everything, and it waWe went for breakfast on Sunday morning and it was packed, so we had to wait about 20 minutes. The good thing is they have a lounge where you can comfortably wait. For this reason, I think it‚Äôs definitely a good idea to make a reservation.

The staff was super kind and attentive ‚Äî they brought us waWe came in at late lunch time (dinner menu), the manti is amazing, it‚Äôs inspired from the Turkish Manti and is very flavourful, the lamb is tender and moist.
The chicken kebabs are succulent and arrive at the table with a sizzle, we ordered some pita to pair the kebab with.

It‚Äôs a great place to peVibe check: perfect. Visitor or local this location is central to so much. I stayed at The Hotel √Ñndra next door and this combo made my trip so easy. Breakfast is great. The bar is a super place to chill meet locals or people traveling through. Great service and food. name: Shaker + Spear
review:
We came here last night (Tuesday) before an event in the building next door, and the place was absolutely packed. Still, the atmosphere, the food, and especially the service were just outstanding.

Our server, Hector, deserves special recognition. Despite the full house, he took amazing care of us ‚ÄîFood was fantastic especially the duck and the roasted potatoes. The duck was cooked perfectly and the roasted potatoes were extremely crispy and flavorful in a large shareable portion. Cocktails were also great. Open kitchen style so you are watching as they‚Äôre making the food! Great service and amWe came here for a team dinner and enjoyed ourselves. The food was very very good and the service was decent. However the service was rather slow. It took us well over an hour to get our food, but when it was served it was delicious! I would recommend but go early and order quickly then sit back andWe ordered the fish, duck and mushrooms.
Fish was amazing. Duck was still good and tender but the mushrooms were covered in salt and fried so much you could not taste the mashroom flavor. Do not recomend this one. Also the tables were so close to each other if was awkward to talk because you could hThis is my 4th time here, they just rotated their menu. All the food we had was delicious. I especially loved the mussels! I normally don‚Äôt eat mussels but their mussels are fresh and flavorful. Our group had people that are vegan, gluten free, and dairy free, they were able to accommodate all of us

name: Elliott's Oyster House
review:
My wife and I walked in for dinner and the restaurant was clean and on the water and looked very nice inside with the wood and oyster selection. We told them we are visiting Seattle for our 15 year wedding anniversary. When we arrived to our table they had an anniversary card for us. Our server EdieI don‚Äôt usually eat oysters, but this place completely changed my mind. The oysters are a must-try‚Äîsweet, fresh, and full of flavor. The restaurant is set right on the harbor, so you get a perfect waterfront view while dining. The vibe is casual yet classy, making it comfortable but still special.

This was my second visit to Elliott‚Äôs, located right on Pier 56 along the Seattle waterfront. As expected, the place was packed, but we lucked out and snagged three seats at the oyster bar for our party of three.

Service started a little slow since David, the oyster chef, let us know we couldn‚Äôt orAmazing food, don't let the 20% service charge fool you, it goes to the company and the server gets a 12% commission on orders. The 20% service charge is to cover additional labor costs for employees, insurance for them, etc etc. Its not because "They want everything handed to them". They are doing Fast, fresh, and ferry-friendly.
My wife and I were craving oysters but had a ferry to catch in about 40 minutes. The team at Elliott‚Äôs sat us at the oyster bar right away, got our half-dozen oysters out fast, and let us settle the bill early so we could head out as soon as we finished. Super fresh,

name: The 5 Point Cafe
review: Tried this place for the first time back in 2019 when I first visited Seattle. Tried it again this past weekend and it was just as good as I remembered it. The service was great and we got seated immediately. The food was very good. It is a little pricey but still so good. Highly recommend it!We ate breakfast here twice during our extended weekend (why are there so few breakfast spots in Seattle!) and absolutely loved it. Food was great with huge portions (we never came close to finishing). The chorizo is amazing, great taste and not greasy. The French toast my daughter had was so good. The food at The 5 Point Caf√© was incredible‚Äîeverything we tried was packed with flavor, and the portions were perfect. The staff were quick, friendly, and really on top of things even when it was busy. I was only in Seattle for three nights and ended up eating dinner here twice, which says a lot. review:

I grew up on 13 Coins, always loved dining at the old Seattle locatioExcellent show.. service and food. Stayed at the connected Embassy (best room I've seen in awhile) grateful 13 Coins was right here. Had two amazing meals. Watching them cook in front of you is an experience. Breakfast all day... but I would say I was full on regret mode when I saw their chicken fetWe ate here before going to the Mariners game on Wednesday September 10th.  It was really good. Fantastic burgers.  Great service.

name: The Crab Pot Seattle
review:
Visited family in Seattle on a Sunday and this place was the only one that was left open in tourist area until 9 PM.

It did not disappoint in having really good seafood. The portions were generous, and the staff is really nice. My dad is handicapped and they made sure to get us a good table for himWe had high hopes for The Crab Pot and spent around $200 for our visit. The service was truly excellent. Warm, attentive, and welcoming from start to finish. Unfortunately, the food didn‚Äôt quite live up to the experience. Everything looked great, but the flavor was surprisingly mild, like they forgoThe Crab Pot is a seafood restaurant with a few locations in the US known for its large selection and group meals where they dump the food on the table. This location is on the pier in Seattle inside the big building under the Ferris wheel. Parking around here is awful, so be ready to either pay a tThe food here was very fresh and of good quality, and the beer was absolutely amazing‚ÄîI still find myself craving it as I write this review. As for the seafood, the Dungeness crab was delicious, but the snow crab was too salty and the shrimp felt under-seasoned. The portion of potatoes was overwhelmWe came for dinner the night before our cruise. What better way than to start with some seafood.
We got the sourdough bread and the clam chowder soup to start. The soup was delicious. My wife got the shrimp sliders and I got the fried platter. Both were tasty and would get again.

name: Piedmont Caf√©
review:
Very pleasantly surprised with this place. The  building and decor were on point. Perfect play to get some work done, people watch, or chat with a friend. The food and coffee were outstanding. I had an almond croissant wheel and it was absolutely perfect. The texture was crunch, crispy, flanky, and My favorite caf√© in Seattle. Everything feels perfectly cozy and relaxed. The matcha latte with oat milk was creamy and filling, and the chocolate croissant was also nice. As you can see in the picture, the atmosphere is calm and warm. The Wi-Fi can be a bit unstable and there‚Äôs a time limit for havDuring a visit to see our son we walked around looking for a good coffee spot and we wandered upon Piedmont Caf√©. What an adorable, quaint, beautiful caf√© very laid-back easy-going there was a gentleman and a young lady behind the counter. Very helpful with decision-making. Very simple yet very wondWarm and cozy place to catch up with friends or even enjoy yourself!

Amaziiing Dirty Chai Latte! I ordered the 16oz size and it was a giant cup! Looks small in the photo though.

Intense chai flavours even in big size! You can size taste the notes from star anise, cinnamon, and other spices, with aBeautiful! So divine. Sweet little spot in First Hill. The decor, and in a beautiful setting. Don't miss this gem! Ambiance 10/10, coffee 7/10.

name: Storyville Coffee Pike Place
review: You wouldn‚Äôt think to wander all the way up to the top floor of the Corner Market Building in Pike Place, but that‚Äôs where Storyville is hiding. My cousin, who‚Äôs a pilot, insisted we check it out, and right away I was drawn to the vibrant wall of wooden pallets that gives the space so much characterHonestly, I didn't find the coffee to be amazing at all, even after I picked up a deal on some of their beans to drink at home. I went here specifically because the vibe looked cozy and warm, and that's exactly what I got. Is it worth a visit? Sure, but I‚Äôve had better coffee. Their cinnamon roll waLoved the vibe here! The delicious coffee and all of the perks involved far outweigh the costs! As soon as you walk in you can feel the quiet, pleasant, casual, and cool atmosphere that you want at a coffee house. It really contrasts with the hustle and bustle of Pike Place. The staff was one of theWe visited Storyville Coffee at Pike Place based on reviews, and it definitely lived up to the hype. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, with a warm, modern vibe that made it a perfect spot to relax. The vanilla latte was rich and smooth and the cinnamon roll was delish! The service was friendly aAbsolutely loved this cute little coffee shop. I‚Äôm a sucker for house made syrups which is exactly what they offered. I ordered a hot vanilla latte which was divine. name: Day Made Kaffe Bar
review:
I‚Äôm so glad I found this cafe! I was looking for a place near my husband‚Äôs office and this one caught my eye, so I decided to stop by. It turned out to be such a nice spot. They did such a great job with the interior, and the atmosphere was great too. I‚Äôd love to come back again!‚ò∫Ô∏èüíöüíôThis is my favorite cafe. Don‚Äôt come for a quick cup though, instead be ready to take time to enjoy it.This review was about sustainability!

I was so happy to see your intention and attention when it comes to reusable ware for your customer customers.

From the real mugs, to the glass plates, to the metal silverware, to the refillable cups at the water station‚Ä¶beautiful :)

By 2050, there will be moOne of the best pour overs I‚Äôve had in my life! They know what they are doing! Espresso based drinks are spot on too!Lovely place to get coffee and affagato! One of the best affagots in Seattle. Great espresso flavor from the syrup and dust. Beautiful restaurant with decent amount of seating. They also sell coffee beans here too. I highly recommend and would come back!

name: Bacco Cafe
review:
Went with high expectations but left somewhat disappointed. The Dungeness crab omelette had a noticeably strong fishy smell, though the flavor itself was pleasant. Overall, the food tended to be on the saltier side, and the coffee was underwhelming.

One thing to note ‚Äî there‚Äôs an extra tax for usinAs a huge lover of brunch, I can say that Bacco completely satisfied my cravings! Let's start with the juices: the Verona and Modena were so fresh and sweet they set a new standard for me. We ordered the Salmon Benedict and the Salmon Omelette to share, and they were both fantastic. The Belgian waffSo impressed by this place! Was staying at a hotel nearby and was sat outside right away. The strawberry orange mimosa was delicious. The highlight meal was the French toast which absolutely blew my mind. My partner also liked the crab sandwich!Cute place. We went here for breakfast and they seated us very quickly. There‚Äôs more seating outside behind the restaurant and it‚Äôs such a nice area. Food was solid and wait staff was fine.This place doesn‚Äôt accept online reservations, and has a line system in front of the restaurant. We went on Sunday at 11 am and were seated instantly. The place is big and takes up almost the entire block on one side so it‚Äôs spacious.

name: Ghost Alley Espresso
review:
if you're a fan of delicious & strong coffee, you have to check this place out.. their cold brew fuels mee...definitely my go to spot when I'm out and about in downtown üôåüèº

the baristas are chill, and if you avoid peak tourist hours you'll wait no longer than a couple minutes for your coffee.

if yoI went here to get my latte fix. It took a while for me to find it. When I got there, there were only 5 people in front of me. So I got my latte and I was quite disappointed. There was no coffee taste. I expected more from this edgy caf√©. The price was also quite steep, $7.17 (incl. tax) for a tasteMy group had various lattes. All were amazing. It is a fun atmosphere. I have had coffee many places in Pikes Place. Ghost Alley does not disappoint. Put it on your to do list.Feeling pretty neutral towards the coffee. Ordered an ice latte. Hope that the coffee can be more full bodied and aromatic. Taste wise, can be stronger.Such a cool vibe! Friendly staff and strong coffee drinks. The mystery mocha was so fun! Strongly recommend Pike‚Äôs Place Market goers stop here for coffee üòç

name: CU URBAN MARKET & CAFE
review:
What a fantastic spot for coffee. Unpretentious, yet high quality. The apple turnovers were terrific, the lattes were incredible! I only wish I found it earlier than the last day of my visit home to Seattle. Deft will visit next time I‚Äôm back in town!Had it one day, came back the next.

Best coffee we had in Seattle from 2 Aussies who love their coffee.

Great price point, friendly service and smooth and strong coffee that‚Äôs well balanced.

Love your work!This a chilled cafe. The price is very affordable and the coffee is excellent we actually visited here almost every day when we are in the town.I had their peanut butter flavor cream coffee and it tastes great. A good mix of creamy and not too much peanut butter. Overall atmosphere was calm and food selections were varied. A bit pricey but still a good amount of selections.Went on two separate occasions. Last week I tried their strawberry real fruit smoothie which was not overly sweet and just right. Texture was good.

name: Victrola Coffee Roasters
review: Needed some good quality coffee in the morning.While on vacation. Thankfully, this place is located inside of the hotel. We was staying at and it did not disappoint. We are visiting in the fall time.So of course, I had to try some of their seasonal drinks, and they were splendid. For anyone in the aThey serve some of the best coffee in Seattle, along with a great selection of snacks and sandwiches. The cookies are freshly baked and delicious. The staff is friendly and welcoming. Seating is limited, especially during the busy morning hours, so plan accordingly.Victrola Coffee Roasters on Pine Street is a true Seattle gem! The coffee is exceptional‚Äîrich, flavorful, and expertly crafted every time. Their selection of pastries and treats pairs perfectly with any drink. The caf√© is spotless and well-maintained, making it a comfortable place to relax or catch The coffee was fantastic! Lots of syrup options, but only vanilla sugar free. Salted caramel hit the spot. Close to Pike Place. It was on the way to there from Westlake rail stop.So this spot consistently showed up in various blogs and I expected it to rock my world. Unfortunately it did not live up to anything I read or saw. It's ok. But in a world where there are so many options in this town, still not sure why people keep bringing it up as one of the best.

name: URL Coffee
review: I visited a few months ago and the space is beautifully decorated and my latte was quite good. The only downside was the seating arrangement. There's one long communal table and a few small seats, so it can be tough to find a spot to enjoy the lovely atmosphere.Matcha latte was very smooth and visually appealing. Drink was out quickly but was warm not hot unfortunately. Scone was good. Has a nice seating area but felt like wifi was slow  for working. Great hangout though.I really liked the place and staff was also very nice and attentive. Drink Walk to Work for very delicious! Their toasts were overly sweet even the ones that were savory options.Nice cute clean place to sit down and have a light meal and coffee. I felt the cortado was excellent‚Ä¶ I also order the crepe cheese pancake‚Ä¶ this can be made better if they made home made jam. If it is home made jam then it tasted like it was from the jar that was overly sweeten and it did not have I don‚Äôt really have anything bad to say, but it‚Äôs not astounding. I heard rave reviews about URL and it was fine. Iced latte wasn‚Äôt anything special and a bit too milky for my taste. Didn‚Äôt try the food so I don‚Äôt know about that! Cashier was really nice, the interior is pretty big but it has very l

name: Moore Coffee Shop
review:
Very cute coffee shop. They serve unique and fun drinks. Lots of options if you don‚Äôt want coffee. I loved the taro latte. They also have a great horchata coffee. The food also, is good. Waffles with guava were tasty. I will definitely come here again. Maybe on a weekday though. The weekend was packthis was our first stop after arriving in seattle for the first time! so cute and everything is pink in here. the boyfriend enjoyed a drip coffee and i got a horchata latte! we also got a cheese danish and it was so delicious. i love the cozy and intimate vibes!! would recommendA cute cafe with excellent non-coffee options! The ambiance is cozy and inviting, and the beverage presentation is absolutely stunning. The highlight for me was the Besame Mucho (definitely ask for your preferred sweetness level). Tres leches matcha is also a tasty beverage and comes with strawberriThis is a Latina-owned business, which is absolutely awesome and definitely worth championing.

I ordered the Caf√© Madrid and loved it. Made with sweetened condensed milk, it is creamy, rich, and on the sweeter side but not overpoweringly sweet. Just the perfect balance of bold espresso and smooth sAdorable latte art and delicious mocha! Visited Moore Coffee in Seattle and got a mocha latte with the cutest bear face on top. Rich, smooth, and perfectly balanced. The caf√© is small but cozy, with a warm vibe.

name: Drip Drip coffeehouse
review:
We really enjoyed Drip Drip! Their coffees were flavorful and not too sweet. The interior vibe was colorful and eye catching‚Ä¶but maybe a little too cluttered? The staff were friendly and helpful as it was our first time there. A very delightful surprise was their homemade rice crispy treats! They haSuper cute coffee shop!
Fun decor on every wall with a quiet but jazzy soundtrack. Big bright Windows lighten the space.
The stools of the bar are super comfy!

We got an egg creme brulee coffee and a matcha pandan coffee.

I loved that they offered such unique coffees with such a clear and easy to This is such a fun spot to check out! Love that they have the flight option so you can try a little of everything.

Of the flights we tried, I love the egg brulee foam & taro/ube foam the most, it has the right flavor and compliments the matcha drink. Roasted sesame foam was good too but I feel likeHoly crap everything is amazing! I got a bao bun and a matcha flight and everything was so epically flavored and balanced. Nothing was too sweet and the bun was moist and flavorful (mushroom cashew mmmmm). The buns were gluten free too so my friend was able to indulge in one for herself! The matcha Beautiful bright space with plenty of seating serving up Vietnamese coffees and treats. Only complaint is the smallest coffee is a 16oz, when they should offer a 12. Great new neighborhood spot!

name: The Hideout
review:
Great drinks and atmosphere; the drinks are very expensive, but they are tasty and boozy. There were only two bartenders working and it was a Friday night so we often had to wait 5-10 minutes to be able to order a drink. Artwork was cool, vibes were immaculate üëå there is no food on the menu but a coMy favorite neighborhood bar. a HUGE fan of low light, chandeliers and candles and the art covering the walls. Almost every cocktail I‚Äôve had has been delightful and decently priced, can have about two rounds without feeling the sting of the bill.

Staff is super chill. Only complaint I have is whilWe had a great experience here in First Hill. This spot has a cool vibe with a creative cocktail list, a fabulous bartender (Fiona), and Seattle worthy music playing. There is also a collection of beautiful art on both walls.Visited in Aug 2023

A really great ‚Äòhidden‚Äô bar as the name suggests. My friends and I ended up visiting the place twice during our short stay in Seattle. Really loved the cocktails. My favourite cocktail was the ‚ÄúSeats Way Back‚Äù drink. Service was good.

The interior artwork on the walls is so gooWe went on a Monday night so it was pretty dead. Super cool art on the wall. 2 drinks was 50 bucks with tip so be prepared for that.  But great service, great character and good drinks. Forsure would go back
location: 1005 Boren Ave, Seattle, WA 98104, USA

name: Some Random Bar
review:
This bar became my go-to spot during my time in Seattle. The food was tasty, the drinks were spot on, and the staff were super friendly. My stay was short, but somehow I ended up here almost every day. Next time I‚Äôm back in Seattle, this will be one of the first places I visit again. Big thanks to eThey have 4 TVs and play NFL although the TV size is probably on 55‚Äù for 3 and smaller for the fourth. Just opens late.
The drink menu is great and the food is delicious and not just run of the mill bar food.
The clientele is not young and more laid back atmosphere and not loud.
Music is played so nWas staying in Seattle at VRBO for a couple days before getting on a cruise for Alaska. We were looking for a place for drinks within walking distance of the condo and stumbled on Some Random Bar. We liked the drink options on the menu so gave it a shot. We absolutely loved it, drinks were awesomeOverall had a good time here. I ordered the Italian style burger, and after a 6 day backpacking trip, it was delicious! As were the fries and beer.A fun spot for pre-gaming before a show. Their food menu appears to rotate seasonally, with some house favorite cocktails staying through the year.
Happy hour is a good deal, one of the surprisingly dangerous drinks that is a go to is their house margarita mixed with pina colada and toasted coconut.

name: Jupiter Bar
review:
I came to Jupiter to try the pizza at Good Shape, which is served inside the bar. As soon as I walked in, I was greeted by chill staff members. I ordered a pie and grabbed some drinks while we waited. The beer selection was nice, and the cocktails had some solid mixology behind them. The pizza was rI came here mostly to hangout. Turned out to be a pretty sick dive bar. Lots of arcade games options out here. Definitely played lots of games. You can exchange dollar bills for quarter coins and play arcade games. Pretty cool spot to hangout during late evenings. The cocktail options are limited buReally great bar that embodies the Belltown nightlife. You can hit the arcade in the back or fill up on some Good Shape Pizza in the front. The bartender was knowledgeable and friendly. This bar has great energy and I absolutely reccomend this one.Great customer service!
I had a billing issue during my visit to Jupiter Bar ‚Äî I was accidentally charged more than I ordered. But when I reached out, the staff handled it quickly and professionally, and they refunded the money without any hassle.

Mistakes can happen anywhere, but how a business reLove this place! Always great service. Never no attitude or the feeling like you‚Äôre unwelcome. Decent priced drinks.about $8-$10per drink & frozen margaritas!-$10üëåüèº Food is a little over prices but convenient if you‚Äôre hungry. Booths by the bar have domino sets. back room is an arcade filled with ne
location: 2126 2nd Ave Suite A, Seattle, WA 98121, USA

name: Radiator Whiskey
review:
Run, don't walk, to your experience at radiator Whiskey.  What a treat, this was an excellent evening.   As an out of towner, I will be back here on my next trip to Seattle.  The staff was extremely welcoming and friendly.  The cocktails were all delicious, and would order any of them again.

The piIt's a pretty cool place located on the second floor in the Pike Street marketplace. They have a great selection of rare bourbons and some tasty snacks.  We had the baked fontana and some tots loaded with a fried egg, gravy, and pulled pork. The snack was nice and hearty. We also had their smoked olWhiskey Sour with Maker‚Äôs blend was incredible..Bartenders are all so sweet!!
We work in food industry and they gave us industry discount as well..ü´∂üíïüòòü•∞üòçüíûWe also got Mushrooms as our appetizer, Beef Short ribs as our main course, and lastly to pair with the crazy deep fried Bread pudding which is outWe ordered the 1/2 pig head a week in advance. 7 of us at the table, 6 from Hawaii, that poor pig did have a chance. Deep fried ears, lots of meat and the nephew ate the eye ball for a free shot of whiskey. We drank and had a great time. We will be back.Radiator Whiskey: A Seattle Gem Worth the Splurge

Radiator Whiskey in Seattle truly delivers an experience that makes it a must-visit, despite the inevitable Pike Place Market-adjacent pricing. From the moment you step inside, the incredible atmosphere transports you. Hats off to the designers ‚Äì th
