name: Mini Bar Seattle
review:
All the delicious things I love eating at Mini Bar. From the Thai wrap larb to the Soul Street food fries, to the bulgogi to the fabulous cocktails adorned with beautiful glittery orchids. This place is my go to for Korean fusion Street food. The heart and love put into every dish is a delight to myThe Mini Bar is my favorite place in Seattle.

Jane and Jesse and incredible. Thry treat us like family and always make us feel at home.  They even make a special dish for our dogs when we vist.  The environment is calm and not too loud. Food is is out of this world, easily ny favorite in all of SeaThis is a hidden gem! I randomly walked in and after I watched Jane work in the kitchen I was extremely disappointed that I had already eaten. The food looked and smelled phenomenal. I had envy for sure watching others enjoy their food. Jane was so nice and welcoming. I had a great time chatting witLocated across from Fremont brewery, Mini Bar is a great easily accessible restaurant. Came here for a double date on a Wednesday evening. My group planned to order a few appetizers on the share section of the menu but ended up ordering and sharing more plates half way into the evening because the fSo many good things to say‚Ä¶.!! Came in with friends for an early dinner and was immediately seated by super friendly server. They recommended some of their most popular dishes to try and we were not dissapointed! Everything was so flavorful, super well presented and tasted incredible! Drinks/cocktai

name: Diller Room
review: One of the most impressive bourbon selections that I have seen with my own eyes.  The Captains List will take you on a journey.  The old fashioned list built with their barrel picks and the list of house cocktails are also extensive.  Enjoying your drink in the historic setting adds to the experiencI believe Corey served us (so sorry if i got the name wrong). He was so attentive and welcoming to customers coming through the door. As someone involved in the service industry for years it was very impressive, as was the quality of our cocktails. Fantastic, friendly service in a great atmosphere. Dillards is a great bar. It‚Äôs cozy and private. My husband and I came for a few drinks and we had the pleasure of having Corey be our bartender. He made all the drinks with care. They all came out so tasty. Definitely a place to visit!Absolutely. The best cocktail I have ever had. Christian and Cory were rock stars. Never even heard of a black Manhattan. My go to drink these days. They are a wealth of knowledge. Really enjoyed my time at The Diller Room. Rob the owner spent a lot of time explaining to me what is a black manhattanBest bar in Seattle. A wall of wonderful liquors to tempt your tongue.  Bar staff is knowledgeable and amazing! Find Christian and you won't be disappointed with his suggestion and personality. Prepare to be very happy!
location: 1224 1st Ave, Seattle, WA 98101, USA

name: Black Cat Bar
review:
This is a really fun dive bar, but I was only there to order food and found out the kitchen doesn‚Äôt open until 3 PM. I will definitely be back. The layout reminds me of Brutal Poodle in Denver, but this place is more punk than metal and more cat than dog. Plus they‚Äôve got pinball!5 stars for this dive bar, nice and spacious - order at the bar. Our drinks were STRONG, kicked off our evening! We also really loved the hand cut fries, we couldn‚Äôt decide on 1 so we tried all 3 - so delicious! Thanks for having us!I'm not sure how to review this situation.

The bar table service was perfect- attentive, prompt, cordial.

BUT, the food service, which happens at a different counter, was kinda sorta fulla mediocre.

On a Thursday night, at 10 pm, not crowded, I ordered & paid for a $14.50 Veggie hot dog (yup).

AThis place is great. I wish I had a place like this near my home in Illinois, because I would be there everyday.

On our trip to Seattle we stumbled upon this gem and found the whole vibe - for us, at least - to be comfortable and welcoming, with great music and attentive staff. Maybe not for everyoReally cool place to hang with my boyfriend while we visit the city. Played some good music and had really friendly service!

We ordered the Putin and my only critique was that the gravy was too watery. The fries themselves were tasty though!
location: 2132 1st Ave, Seattle, WA 98121, USA

name: Bad Bishop
review:
I absolutely love this place. If you're in Seattle and you visit the pioneer square neighborhood, definitely put this one on your to-do list. The cocktails are fantastic, I had a great old fashioned! The food is tasty. (Try the Burger with fries and tell me that they don't give you a bit of nostalgiGreat smash burgers and cocktails. I liked the atmosphere, it felt laid back and not as pretentious as other places Pioneer Square but definitely not a dive bar either.What a delightful gem in Pioneer Square! Love the vibe of how they really incorporated the historic building. Drinks were phenomenal and the fries with my burger (which was also delicious!) are worth coming back alone. Great place, can‚Äôt wait to return!Be cautious of the overly positive reviews‚Äîmany of them seem disingenuous or misleading.

I decided to visit this establishment based on the positive reviews I saw online, but unfortunately, my experience was very disappointing.  The atmosphere was unpleasant ‚Äî the space was poorly maintained, and tThis place is quaint and feels like you are in Seattle back in the 90‚Äôs. Sweet old vibes. Had the warm Cesar salad and it was a little off, the chicken was sorta not right. Also had the wings which were outstanding. Really different with great flavors. The hero here was the drinks. Oh my, some of th
location: 704 1st Ave, Seattle, WA 98104, USA

name: Inside Passage
review: This place is fantastic! Great craft cocktails in gorgeous glasses and tasty small plates. I also have to give a huge shout out to our server, who kept an eye on me and my friend, erring on the side of caution when she wasn't sure if another friend of ours was actually a friend, or just kind of a crWe had a wonderful time here! The atmosphere was fantastic and really well done. The drinks were really fun, unique, delicious, and on theme. They were a little expensive, but that's to be expected. Our server was really kind and helpful.Pirates of the Caribbean meets 20,000 leagues under the sea one of the most incredible bars that I have been to in a very long time. Great customer service and incredible presentation. I would highly recommend it. We will definitely be back.We had a fantastic time at this Tiki-style spot in Seattle! The atmosphere was vibrant and fun, and our waiter, Alex, truly made the experience memorable. He was attentive, friendly, and offered excellent recommendations that really enhanced our visit. From start to finish, everything was smooth andTL;DR It‚Äôs a cool spot, lively servers but your drinks will be on average $25 each (including well/non specialty drinks), in a large/decorative vessel about 2-4 sips and a pound of ice. Like while you‚Äôre taking the first few sips, your straw will make sounds because you‚Äôre already hitting air. We sp
location: 1108 Pike St, Seattle, WA 98101, USA

name: The Lookout
review:
Went here specifically to review the place. Showed up in time for sunset and sat on the patio. The view is breathtaking and the outdoor vibe is cool, laid back and friendly.
The service was kind but infrequent. The crinkle cut fries were actually really good!Nice vibes, good service, and a decent selection. Cool spot for views if the weather is right and there's a seat outside.Love the firepit on the back patio. My  dog and I enjoyed the view. The cocktails were great! The bartender makes a really tasty cosmo. He used Contreau liquour for the orange flavor in the drink and it tasted outstanding. (Most bars use Triple Sec liquour for the orange flavor in a cosmo.)  The NY Lovely beer selection and great patio. Individual washrooms available üëçMe and 4 other buddies of mine came in for their bottomless mimosa special last week for a good time to enjoy the nice day. We were nice and respectful to our servers. The first server, Dan, had a great attitude. He switched servers to, Lulu, who had an attitude every time we would ask her to refill
location: 757 Bellevue Ave E, Seattle, WA 98102, USA

name: Buttermilk & Bourbon
review:
What a fun brunch spot! We have been to Boston several times, but never had the chance to eat here. Glad we did! The atmosphere is like no other. We were seated in the back room, blue light so it made for interesting photos. The service was phenomenal! Loved our server, she was so fun and friendly aPart of my friend group headed back before the rest of us, so we decided to stop in somewhere for dinner before we caught the train back. All of us were very glad we found the Buttermilk & Bourbon: a New Orleans style restaurant in Boston?? Yes, please.

Even though it was packed, we managed to get Decent southern comfort food. I liked the fried chicken waffle place for brunch. The beignets are amazing, flaky. The atmosphere wasn't great though. The service was also slow, it seems like they were understaffed. We waited for a long time to get out check (after asking for it for 3 times).One of very few restaurants where the ambience, service, and food are all top tier and incredible. We tried the BBQ shrimp, Mac n cheese, chicken sliders, and whipped ricotta. I truly have no other words than‚Ä¶wow. This place is a must must must for anyone looking for southern comfort food to heal thHaving been to this place a few times over the years, it has somehow gotten even better.
Their renowned biscuits are soft, sweet, buttery all on their own but when paired with either the smoked cinnamon butter to up the sweetness or the pimento cheese to provide more savoriness you cannot go wrong!
location: 160 Commonwealth Ave, Boston, MA 02116, USA

name: The Salty Pig
review:
During our time in Boston, we visited this place twice, and both times were fantastic. The Italian food is authentic and unforgettable.
On our first visit for dinner, it was a bit tricky to find a table, they had space but only offered seats at the bar, which isn‚Äôt ideal if you‚Äôre not into drinks.
OHad dinner here with my wife and we ordered the Chicken Piccata and a Margherita-style pizza. The Chicken Piccata was the highlight of the meal ‚Äî the portion was generous, the chicken breast was tender and well-cooked, and the lemon-butter sauce with capers gave it a bright, tangy flavor that pairedI am Thrilled to find this Hidden Oasis of incredible food service & ambiance! The freshest Foods, Charcuterie boards Pizza and incredible staff , I had the absolute pleasure of being waited on at the bar by Cam the bartender & just a short time after was visited by the Manager Jill to see if everytTasty pizza, and friendly staff/atmosphere. We ordered 3 meals for 5 people. We ordered the Polpette Sandwich (meatball), Salsiccia Pizza and the Bianco all very tasteful. Our favorite was the Bianco pizza!This resaurant is by the Copley pla e mall. Really nice vibe inside. Staff was super friendly. Love that they come with the bottle of wine and then serve you onbthe spot. Applaud themnfor that. Rhe meatballs with taiasted bread is a great app. But the Margherita & Bianco pizza were amazing. name: MIDA
review:
Cozy and nice place for a dinner. Happy atmosphere, minimalistic design and furniture setting. Delicious food. The roasted chicken smelled heavenly. Don‚Äôt know what spice or oil it was infused with, but I was impressed. Eggplant parmigiana was very delicately cooked to perfection.Great menu, everything you want out of a higher scale Italian place. Arancini had great balance in terms of richness and acid from the tomato sauce. Tomato sauce really stuck out in the short rib lasagna as well, portion well worth the price, great flavor. Gnocchi was unbelievably soft, definitely sI had a great meal here! The food is well-seasoned and cooked well. Definitely one of the better pasta restaurants I've been to. I'd come back!

Delicious, would get again
- The mushroom pappardelle was excellent! The mushrooms were tender and delightfully savory, and the noodles were perfectly al dMIDA is a standout Italian restaurant conveniently located near Boston Symphony Hall, making it a perfect pre-concert dining destination. My dinner began with the arancini, fried to a golden, delicate crisp and topped with creamy fontina cheese. The rice inside was hot, moist, and flavorful, creatinWe had an incredible experience here! We tried the mushroom frittata, the crispy French toast, and the crispy potato bowl ‚Äî and every single dish was delicious. The French toast was unlike any I‚Äôve ever had ‚Äî super crispy and easily the best I‚Äôve tasted. The frittata was flavorful with perfectly coo
location: 782 Tremont St, Boston, MA 02118, USA

name: Estella Restaurant
review:
Estella was a fantastic place for dinner in downtown Boston. We didn‚Äôt have a reservation but were welcomed regardless and were able to be seated immediately. The service from Rim was impeccable. She honestly made our night. She was so sweet and accommodating. One of the best servers I‚Äôve had- and aWhere can I begin on talking about a place like this. With it being located in Boston‚Äôs Downtown Crossing the Estella Interior has a nice nighttime vibe to it. On to the food and drink I had, I first ordered the Strawberry Spritz which has an amazing sugary rush towards it‚Äôs taste. For my entr√©e I hI recently had my birthday dinner here with friends and the food is pretty good. Service is alright. Atmosphere is nice.

It took some time to order food after receiving our drinks. Half of the table received food while others had to wait some time. And we had to ask someone else to bring over utEnjoyable dinner experience!
We just arrived to Boston and walk into Estella without a reservation. The hostess was so sweet and was able to accomodate us! While taking us to our table, she described her favorite food.  We did took her advices and‚Ä¶glad we did. We ordered the candie brussel sprouts‚Ä¶oVisiting Boston on a Monday, we stopped in here. The ambiance is nice and dark. Our server was nice. The food came out quick. We tried the Rasta pasta with chicken which was great. The taste had a nice balance of spices. The burger was okay. The clam chowder needed a little something more.
location: 49 Temple Pl, Boston, MA 02111, USA

name: 1928 Beacon Hill
review:
The food was absolutelyyyy amazing. The filet mignon with scallops was a must!
I really enjoyed my meal. However, I do think the service could have been better. It wasn‚Äôt bad but it wasn‚Äôt great either.
4.5 out of 5! Which is still great!Started our dinner off with some drinks, our server Mike (who was amazing!!) recommended the Beatnik which I absolutely loved. I would come back for just that drink. I had the lobster gnocchi which was a great portion size and was pretty yum ! Overall had a great time, just didn‚Äôt love how close togI LOVED this place! The service here is fantastic, the food is delicious and the ambiance is beautiful. Our waitress was great. Also, Shout out to the lovely hostess who used her phone's flashlight as I was taking a photo with my boyfriend, she's awesome!The food is pretty average. In vibes are pretty cool. Unfortunately we did not have the best experience they sat us for party of 10 for a table that wood be a tight squeeze for 8. Our waiter did not seem overly interested in waiting so that was kinda odd. I‚Äôm sure we just went on an off nightPretty, pretty, pretty good!

We went to 1928 Beacon Hill to celebrate my husband‚Äôs birthday and had a great experience. The food is delicious and worth every penny. I recommend making a reservation if you‚Äôre more than three people. Everything is made from scratch, so you need to order appetizers an

name: Grana at The Langham, Boston
review:
Grana is one of the most beautiful restaurants I've had the pleasure to dine in. From it's high ceilings, chandeliers and artwork on the wall it just screams opulence. This is the on-site restaurant at the Langham Boston for breakfast, brunch and lunch. The service was excellent from the hostess, waGrana is a western restaurant located in the heart of Boston‚Äôs financial district. While it is convenient to get to for anyone (as there are multiple modes of public transport that can get you there), since it is located in The Langham hotel, it is particularly convenient for hotel guests. When you Wow, wow, wow!
We were in town visiting family and came in for Brunch at Grana. Our group of 4 decided to order several different dishes so we could all share, and I‚Äôm so glad we did! From the Lemon cello French toast and Scottish eggs (with a delicious Dijon sauce and pickled mushrooms), to their uWe ate breakfast here morning of our stay. Although all were delicious we definitely recommend the savory selections over the sweet. The coffee is fantastic!Love the vibe and decor. We were seated before the entire party arrived which was great and not expected during brunch time on a Saturday. Our server was very patient and came back several times to check on us.

name: Mooo.... Beacon Hill
review:
I had an excellent  meal at Moo....Beacon Hill with my friends.  The service from the each and everyone of the staff's was amazing, they really  out did themselves and showed care for everyone of the customers. The food was truly amazing I enjoyed  the tuna tartare, and the Prime NY sirloin the mostexcellent food, excellent wait staff and chefs.
my partner and i arrived a bit early but were able to sit at the bar for about 20 minutes and the bartender was wonderful, explained a little of the menu to us with some recommendations and answered some questions. the drinks were all amazing.
the foodWhat an unexpected and wonderful dinner! We hadn‚Äôt planned on eating at Mooo but ended up at the bar, and it was such a great choice. Everything we ordered was excellent, the steak was perfectly cooked and just melted in the mouth, the carpaccio was full of flavor, and even the carrots were a standoThe service was outstanding. Our server was friendly, attentive, and made sure we had everything we needed throughout our meal. I ordered the rustic corned beef hash, and it was easily one of the best I‚Äôve ever had. My husband enjoyed his omelette and was equally impressed. I mentioned in our reservWe visited Mooo‚Ä¶. in Beacon Hill for a birthday lunch and overall had a good experience, especially thanks to the excellent customer service and beautiful ambiance. name: Boston Sail Loft
review:
When we arrived we were told it was 1.5 hr wait, but about 20 minutes later we got a table at the bar. The bartender was friendly and helpful with the menu, we ordered the fish and chips  to share and two cups of the clam chowder. The fish was very tender and the chips (fries) were high quality. TheI was on a trip to Boston and really wanted a lobster roll. Myself and my friend ordered the hot lobster roll and it was so delicious. It came with fries, coleslaw, & extra butter on the side. It was so good that we visited 2 days in a row while on our trip. It is worth the wait.

The Boston creme pWe flew in from Florida and North Carolina for a cruise on Sat. We wanted a day to play and tonight was a mini reunion and birthday dinner. It was excellent!! We agreed to an outdoor table for immediate service otherwise it would have been 45 mins for an inside table. (On a Thur night around 5:30p) My sister and I wanted the view of the harbor with our food and stumbled upon this gem. Made reservations at the front and only needed to wait 20 minutes. Server was so kind and efficient, really appreciate her recommendation of the seafood pasta which my sister absolutely loved.

Lobster was great,I recently took a friend visiting from out of town to this spot to try the famous New England lobster roll, and we were both impressed! Having tasted lobster rolls at several places before, I can confidently say this restaurant serves one of the best. We went for dinner on a weekday, so it was pleas

name: Yvonne's
review:
Great atmosphere perfect for a romantic date and the tapas style menu also makes it a great location for social gatherings. Service was incredible. Our server was able to answer our questions on the menu and also provided the best wine recommendations.

With two of us we found that a snack, a socialIt‚Äôs such a hidden gem in the downtown area of Boston! Vibe ‚úÖ Food ‚úÖ Price & portion ‚úÖ! And as I walked in this restaurant, it felt like I‚Äôm walking into an unknown territory! Classic speakeasy! The special architectural design with chic, classic, modern, and warm look entertained by Latin House musTLDR: Much better as a pre or post-dinner drinks place. Don't get food here.

Ambience: Gorgeous space, dark and intimate. Perfect for date nights. It is located in kind of a sketchy alleyway. We had no issue, but a brisk, purposeful speed walk is recommended to get to the restaurant.

Food: DisappoStopped by with the wife for a drink per a recommendation from our hotel lobby. This place did not disappoint. The bar staff was absolutely amazing and really went out of their way to take care of us. After finding out it was for an anniversary they had some food sent out for us to try. The drinks w10/10 Really amazing food, amazing service and great atmosphere. We arrived for 5pm and were seated straight away. Our server Espeana was straight over and we were made to feel so welcomed instantly. It‚Äôs small plates and we had 4 between 2 of us. We had the Seared Hallumi Cheese, Lazy Lobster dumpl

name: Saltie Girl
review: Saltie Girl completely lived up to the hype. The lobster roll was buttery and perfectly balanced; One of the best I‚Äôve ever had. The oysters were incredibly fresh and paired with great sauces. The atmosphere is lively but intimate, making it a perfect spot for seafood lovers. Service was attentive, Saltie girl was packed when we went, but we had a reservation so we didn‚Äôt have to wait. We were seated inside‚Äîpatio seating didn‚Äôt seem to be available for reservations. The atmosphere was lively, though a little too crowded to have an easy conversation. The food, however, was really good and beautExcellent staff, great menu with seafood focus with classics and specials, lovely ambience. We went to dinner both times but would recommend making a reservation unless you have a small party of 2 and you might be lucky with bar seating. I think their drink menu is simple and delicious. Would recommThe fried lobster & waffles and oyster was perfect and the lobster roll was great but a little smaller compared to other restaurants. But the service was terrible. We were mostly ignored, all the tables around us that arrived after us got their food and finished it even before we got ours. We asked This place was bomb! We ordered one clam chowder for two people, lobster roll with caviar and tuna with pistachio. The clam chowder was sooo good but the lobster is by far the best one I have tried we got it hot, the bread was crunchy but soft and moist. Really pricy meal but good for special occasi

name: Phin Coffee House
review:
Came here on a thursday afternoon and this place was popping! May(mae?) helped us out and was so so sweet! I got the coconut latte which is a delicious coconut milk coffee blended and the veggie sandwich. my partner got the boston cream latte which was pretty light and amazing as well. She also got This is an nice coffee shop located a short walk away from South Station. They offer a wide variety of specialty coffees and matcha options. We stopped by and tried the Boston Creme Latte which caught our eye on the menu. It had a unique taste; quite sweet but not overwhelmingly so. It just seemed tThe iced latte was quite bitter to my taste. The interior was nice, the staff were good. I recommend looking elsewhere to get your coffee but if no other options are around, this one is viable - iced latte became better as the ice meltedThe staff is friendly and takes our order efficiently. The latte with almond milk tastes good, the coffee tastes is not entirely covered by the almond flavor.

The seating area is small but there are plenty seats at the area, maybe grab one coffee and find a place to enjoy the city.The coffee with coconut was really special. Must try on your list! The snack was also tasty! Hopefully I could have next visit and try other food.

name: Madhouse Cafe
review:
Very cool spot! Drip coffee was smooth, but with a heavy caffeine kick. I tried the Tahini latte, unique and delicious. You can walk through the shop and check out bikes and the shop cat. Worth the special trip when coming through Boston, I‚Äôd be here all the time if I lived here. Don‚Äôt go in a hurryI came to this cafe with my sister, we got lemon pound cake, ice chai latte and hot latte. The drinks and food was great, great customer service and the cafe is quite enough to talk with friend or just do your work. I love cute interior design. Definitely would be coming back, next time I am in the Great coffee. Their specialty tahini latte isn't overly sweet, which I appreciated.

Unique shop with character. Highly recommend for coffee or bike lovers.

There is a high top table, bar seating, 4-5 small tables, and more patio tables outside. Good spot to get some work done, read or chat!I'm in the minority here where I had a bad experience.  Let's start with the good.   We came in here and the caf√© looked awesome... you can get coffee AND watch people fix cool bikes and cars.

The earl grey latte caught my eye so that's what I ordered, large, I didn't say iced because I wanted hot Great code with a strong body, well balanced. In one week I went like 5 times and brought my friends to get a taste of local coffee shop. Barista was patience and customer friendly.
location: 24 Blue Hill Ave, Boston, MA 02119, USA

name: Sip of Joy Caf√© & Bakery
review:
I love going to this cafe, whether it‚Äôs to grab a quick coffee or sit in the window seats and work for a few hours. It is very calm and welcoming - a great quiet place to focus. Their coffee is amazing and they offer Turkish coffee as well as other creative drinks. I also like their food options likService are nice but I can‚Äôt believe after they warm it the food is still cold ‚Ä¶ what? :( The food quality is good tho. The latte is too much milk and taste like water but the black coffee definitely is good tho. Kinda sad :(. Turkish coffee is good but not great.If you're in Boston's South End and looking for a cozy spot that blends Turkish and American flavors, Sip of Joy Caf√© & Bakery is a must-visit. Located at 661 Tremont Street, this family-run caf√©, opened in July 2023 by owners Matt and Burju Sari, offers a warm and inviting atmosphere. ‚Äã

One of theA cozy corner of simple Turkish delights in South End.

While there are many Turkish bakery and coffee shops in Boston, South End and South Boston doesn‚Äôt have a lot of options. Sip of Joy filled this niche and brought a much-needed splash of Turkish goods to the neighborhood.

On my recent visit arVery lovely folks who work here and nice space, but if you‚Äôre a coffee snob who came for the high ratings just be a bit careful what you order.

The flat white here is a latte and the beans are not good. I think this is somewhere to go more for Turkish coffee or American-style syruped coffee. And (p

name: Cafe Bonjour
review: The line outside the door tells you just how good the food is!  However, to accommodate the eager patrons adorining the waiting list, seating is literally anywhere they could make it‚Ä¶bathroom hallway, seating on ‚Äòthe line‚Äô as the food is being prepared.  It‚Äôs very cramped!  But the staff is friendlyThis cafe lives up to its name.  Cafe Bonjour is so warm and welcoming.  There was a long wait but it was so worth it.  I love that everyone here has a sense of urgency.  From the host to the servers to the kitchen, the service was expeditious not to mention super friendly.  The restaurant is in a sReally enjoyed brunch here! We had the bagel with potatoes and eggs Benedict - everything was delicious and perfectly cooked. The service was quick and attentive, and the atmosphere was very nice. A good place to start the day!We waited 40 minutes for nothing. The only good thing about this restaurant was de updated bathroom, it is nice and was clean. I thought I would eat a delicious croissant but it was greasy and mushy. I didn‚Äôt eat anything that I enjoyed, even their cappuccino was not good. I have been in great breakWe went here for a quick brunch which was very easy to get a table. We sat up in the front, which is the most glamorous thing to look out, but the weather was nice. It‚Äôs right next to the orange wine so that can get pretty busy. The food came out really fast, probably about 10 minutes after we order
location: 55 Temple Pl, Boston, MA 02111, USA

name: Gracenote Coffee Boston
review:
Spent hours trying to figure out the best coffee spots to try while on my trip to Boston. This place came up a lot so I decided to give it a try.
I have to say it definitely does the job of waking you up. I was just kind of bummed out at the choices of coffee. As someone who likes trying seasonal / Definitely one of the top coffee brands in Boston. They‚Äôre doing really well, but if I could ask for more, I feel their espresso bean selection is a bit limited given their reputation. I hope they expand their medium-roast espresso options in the future. That said, aside from the beans, their presenThere is an art to espresso, coffee roasting‚Ä¶ if you feel that way, go to Gracenote. They take it serious but are in no way pretentious. You could get an hour long explanation on roasting and the process of making a good espresso, or have a beer and talk about the Red Sox with the baristas. The cappThis a cozy and friendly vibe in this coffee place! It‚Äôs warm, inviting, and full of character. Honestly, this might be the best coffee I‚Äôve had in the United States so far. Everyone should try a cup here at least once ‚Äî highly recommended!hands down the tastiest coffee i‚Äôve had in boston. i got a takeout latte with a simple syrup, it was rich & creamy - in love with the microfoam. i enjoy smaller portions of coffee, so the cup size & price were reasonable & perfect! will be returning soon :)

name: Greystone Cafe, Bakery, and Provisions
review:
Beautiful place with a cozy atmosphere! Their pour-over coffee is excellent and really stands out. The sandwiches are fresh and delicious, and the staff is friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend for both coffee lovers and anyone looking for a nice spot to relaxVery delicious almond croissant, super generous and decadent.

Greystone is a very popular small neighbourhood bakery near Boston Library. Had to queue for about 10mins on a Sunday morning before getting my almond croissant.

It‚Äôs on the bigger side for sure. Inside is a delicious almond paste filliPretty good coffee spot! Enjoyed their homemade vanilla flavor in the iced coffee, but the coffee was fine, nothing spectacular. The mixed berry scone was an amazing flavor, a little over baked so very hard outside but truly still a great treat. Will definitely come back for more baked goods!Super busy on a Sunday morning in March, the vibes were great for chatting with a friend. I also saw some folks having business conversations. It‚Äôs not a big place so limited seating and one big table to stand at and talk. Love the no laptops policy for most of the cafe. The cappuccino was not bad aI stopped by this cafe while exploring new spots in the city (though I don‚Äôt live here). It‚Äôs a cute place, though on the smaller side with limited seating. There‚Äôs outdoor seating as well, but it‚Äôs definitely more enjoyable when the weather is warmer. The staff were friendly, and I didn‚Äôt have to w
location: 123 Appleton St, Boston, MA 02116, USA

name: Heidi‚Äôs House of Coffee
review:
I LOVE Heidi, her coffee, her pastries, her sweet disposition,  everything about her business! We go to BWM regularly for my son's care and she is our port in the storm. This is the one spot where the coffee tastes like home, and the service feels like your own kitchen table. So grateful to her! ThaI LOVE Heidi and I LOVE her coffee! The various flavored iced coffees are amazing. I love being surprised by what she has brewed today! Heidi is so kind, friendly, and welcoming. Taking a walk to get a coffee at Heidi‚Äôs is the best part of my work day and it is SO much better than Dunks or StarbucksI recently got a iced dirty chai and regular iced chai and they were soooooo good. I also met Heidi and she was soo sweet! Definitely recommend!Heidi is honestly my favorite barista! She is always so sweet and welcoming. Getting coffee here is the highlight of my dayüòä I look forward to seeing her friendly smile and what variety of iced coffee flavors she is offering that day. She is just a joy and if she is not there, oh it is definitely feHeidi's House of Coffee has quickly become my go-to destination for its outstanding coffee and delicious pastries.
The lattes here are exceptional ‚Äì with a large variety of specialty flavors.  I especially like Heidi's nutella lattes.
location: 350 Longwood Ave, Boston, MA 02215, USA

name: Central Perk Coffee Co
review:
We stopped by Central Perk Coffee Co. in Boston and enjoyed a relaxing break. The coffee was solid and the cake was delicious. A perfect combo.

The service was friendly and professional, and we didn‚Äôt have to wait too long (around 15 minutes on a busy afternoon).

We lucked out with a seat on the tFound this cute cafe while roaming the Boston streets. It's a must visit for FRIENDS fans.
The ambience is so great with lots of references to the show.
Our barista was amazing (unfortunately I didn't get her name!) and took the time to talk to us about the season specials.
The coffees tasted great Had a great time here with the moist maker, I mean the sandwich btw. Now the atmosphere was very chill. You can relax for hours. It‚Äôs cool to see friends references everywhere from the WiFi password to the menus. It‚Äôs fun if you‚Äôre a fan. Worth a visitFrom the barista to the random lady, all were very welcoming. From food suggestions and recommendations to random acts of kindness like wanting to take our picture for us. From the Janice coffee, Joey sandwiches and Gunther specials it was all hands-down a friendly environment Thank you so much and I‚Äôm  from New York and we make it a priority to stop at Central Perk every time we are in/near Boston! The coffee is top notch, the service incredible and the atmosphere magnetic! There are so many different coffee options it‚Äôs hard to choose in a good way! My friend and I are both coffee lovers and

name: Koko Coffee
review:

My friends and I ordered some sandwiches, pastries and beverages.

We all loved the almond croissant! My iced tea was super refreshing for a hot summer day!I actually had an interesting time while I was waiting for another event to start. I ordered a drip coffee ‚òï, which someone else grabbed, a chocolate croissant ü•ê and I tried a French Madeleine, which had a lemon üçã flavor. My coffee was quickly remade. Everything tasted good üëç and there was a lot of Pretty good coffee and treats, but not anything that special.

The latte flavors were hit or miss, but the coffee and espresso are good quality! I like their roasting flavors like the blonde batter, but others you can barely taste.

The croissants are pretty nice, especially the pistachio one which Food and drink are good, but not very special. Good location for a quick meal if you are around and don‚Äôt want to wait for too long. I would give 120/100 only because the matcha latte is not sweet. Finally a normal drink without sugar.

name: Trident Booksellers & Cafe
review:
New favorite place in the city for breakfast!!! Reasonably priced food that‚Äôs yummy - love! Location on Newbury Street - love! Fun, quirky bookstore to roam through after - love! Seriously, so much to love about this place!!!

I‚Äôve been here twice now, and the service has always been amazing!!! So fCafe in the book shop, fantastic atmosphere!
There are seats indoor, outdoor, and upstairs.
I love books so it's such a great place to relax, enjoy delicious food and drinks and being surrounded by book!
Easy to order with QR code and food delivery to the table. There was a couple items didn't show We had a late breakfast there on Saturday morning. The place was not over crowded but there was a lot of people between who was attending the food and who was looking for the right book to buy.
The saff was welcome and helpful.
The food is fresh made so expect to wait a little bit for your food to bStopped here on a whim and I gotta say. This place is super chill and charming. Tons of books , blind boxes, totebags, and other gifts. And on top of that you can get breakfast /coffee/drinks??? This place is amazing. I had the study special while trying to escape the rain and has such a nice experiThis bookstore has everything! A great vast selection of categorised books, and an overflowing gift shop section with so many cute nick nicks to gift and take back: hats, cards, games, candles, gag gifts etc. you name it they have it. They also have a cute cafe with both indoor and outdoor seating (
location: 338 Newbury St, Boston, MA 02115, USA

name: The Tam
review:
Awesome experience here, just enough chill and spunk to fully appreciate the experience. The bartenders were AWESOME and had some good banter with them. Would come back again 100% if I lived in Boston!What a great dive bar. Awesome vibe and welcoming atmosphere. Can be a regular here for sure!  They don‚Äôt have a kitchen but you‚Äôre welcome to bring your own food in, do Uber Eats or grab a slice of NY pizza next door.Very tasty draft beer, I love the whirlpool hazy pale ale, excellent! Relaxing time .The drinks flow as cheap as they can,
The charm‚Äôs in the grit, not the glam.
Though the restroom‚Äôs a fright,
You‚Äôll remember the night‚Äî
For there‚Äôs nowhere quite like The Tam.What a great local bar with lots of locals hanging out!  Our bartender was great! We were looking for a nice low key bar to just hang out in for a while and this was the place!
location: 222 Tremont St, Boston, MA 02116, USA

name: Extra Dirty Cocktail Club
review: We attended an event that was designed around cocktails paired with food, and it turned out to be a wonderful experience. The cocktails were truly exceptional‚Äîbeautifully crafted, balanced in flavor, and presented with creativity. Each one felt unique, and you could tell a lot of thought went into tThis was a really good experience! You got four courses of cocktails paired with four courses of food. They're cocktail menu varies by the season. Currently it is their fall menu and the drinks are fall themed with spice, pumpkin, star anise, and new takes on old classics. A great experience and I lI took my 24 year old son who is a bartender for his birthday along with his girlfriend and my other son. What a wonderful experience from the speakeasy atmosphere, to the music vibe to the beautifully crafted cocktails and light fare. It was more than expected. The staff was wonderful, warm and graThe place is quaint. Nice music üé∂ you can have a conversation. If you like to drink this is a great deal. 4 cocktails of your choosing. They are all very thought out. Very balanced. The food is well planned but the limited kitchen space hurts the execution. From Texas I can say that the ribs were flThis was one of the best experiences you can have in Boston. It is a well tailored drink menu that changes every month with food to accompany it. The staff takes you along this journey.

name: The Stratus - Rooftop Bar Boston
review:
Worth it for the views!
Cocktails are little on the sweeter side.
First-come first-serve seating.
Recommend visiting during the sunset ü´°We had an exceptional experience. The bar is sophisticated and employs real mixologists and skilled professionals. This is all to say before mentioning the views. I am surprised to see reviews that say this place isn't amazing, it's a must go when traveling in Boston in my opinionUnbeatable view and so cosy and Christmasy for a mulled wine üéÑ would love to see a few more vegan snacksCasy was unbelievable; the hospitality and service here are unreal. What an experience. I have been waiting quite sometime for this spot to open. A must for anyone visiting or even if you are from the Boston area!!! The cocktail selection is one of the best in Boston!!!!!!!! Get here!The bar was great, I hope there will be more non-alcoholic options too. Otherwise the atmosphere and whole experience was amazing. Thank you

name: Moon Bar
review:
Absolutely loved this place. Delicious Caribbean-inspired food that didn't hold back on spice or flavor. Simply superb cocktails made by professionals and outstanding service. It's a classy spot for adults to mingle and could totally see a great date night here.I loved the decor of this place! The wallpaper is amazing and it‚Äôs a nice, open, eclectic space! Their menu is pretty unique and has an island vibe. The Golden Colada was delicious and the Jamaican Beef Patty was a great snack (very spicy!) service was great, not sure it‚Äôs a spot I‚Äôd hit up for dinnEveryone was so nice and accommodating. The drinks and food were exquisite and vibrant. Best Jamaican Patty I‚Äôve ever had. I‚Äôd go over and over just for that.We didn‚Äôt have any food but we tried some cocktails and they were well crafted. The space itself is gorgeous (photos attached).

There appears to be an inherent relaxation vibe in this joint. They want you to settle with your group when you get in, take your time with your drinks, and the service stSpicy drinks. Spicy food. Cute menu font. Low-key tropical vibes. Lots of seats around the oblong bar, which is definitely where you want to be.

name: Carrie Nation Cocktail Club
review: The cocktail menu is limited, but what we ordered was good. The appetisers were the highlight of the meal. Cannot pick a fave out of the patatas bravas, garlic broccolini or burrata with confit tomatoes. The service was great - our server Sophie was attentive without being intrusive. The atmosphere My name is Carrie and I approve of Carrie Nation!  We saw the window front while on a night tour of Boston and my girls decided that we needed to go, since their bestie is me, Carrie!  We popped into the lounge after finishing our tour of the Freedom Trail- pretty sure we were their first customers came here with one of my girlfriends for a drink. i ordered a cosmo and it wasn‚Äôt very good, i didn‚Äôt finish my drink. we got patatas bravas to share, they were pretty good and had chorizo. the wings were interesting flavor, im not sure id order again. we did see a mouse when we were sitting at the Carrie Nation Cocktail Club is a vibe! Love the decor & speakeasy atmosphere. We realized we were a bit underdressed once we sat at the bar, but didn't feel judged at all. The staff were very welcoming. Carrie Nation has a great cocktail menu. Highly recommend!This place is a whole vibe! The secret room was dark & cozy-great atmosphere! Drinks/bartenders were great! Chicken tenders (Asian style/flavored) were great! Loved!

name: Lucky's Lounge
review:
Very cool!  Loved the vibe,  service,  food. Order the pork belly bao buns, cauliflower, mac & cheese and pork dumplings! Thanks Julian for the great service.  Our team were exhausted from our first day conference and starving!  We were energized by the wonderful dinner, your attention to detail andLucky's is such a great place. Been going here for years. Manny was super helpful with me and my group made us all feel welcome, great vibes at this place and atmosphere! One of the best "dive bars" in Boston. good layout, live music, hospitality and bouncers all super nice.
Thanks for another greatI live about a 3 minute walk from this place. Lucky's is a fun place. They have a Comedy show and Trivia. I hadn't eaten there until a few weeks ago. The Calamari was good. I only eat Seafood and Poultry so I was surprised at the quality. Now..... Now... Ok, for, me, this place; I would frequent at Made a reservation for a table for drinks since it was an option, but turns out the host apparently didn‚Äôt come into work Saturday so there was no need for a reservation üòÜ

Regardless, had a really great experience. Bartender Rich was friendly and attentive. Singer was also really good.We went here for a night cap after visiting the holiday market in Seaport and ended up staying for 3 drinks! The vibe with the red lighting, the old photos, being partially underground, it was all very neat.
location: 355 Congress St, Boston, MA 02210, USA

name: 89 Charles
review:
A new bar in Beacon Hill ‚Äî I really love the vibe here! It‚Äôs super cozy and chill. ü©µ
Drinks are great, and the food is surprisingly good too. The cookie was amazing! üç™

Normally I‚Äôm not a big fan of bourbon, but the Fall Favors was a good one to try. This bar also has a lot of interesting drinks ‚Äî IAs a Beacon Hill resident, this neighborhood needed a place like this. The space is the right amount of cozy and sexy. So perfect for yapping with your friends and enjoying DELICIOUS cocktails. Could not be more excited to go back and visit again. üíñ‚ú®This place is one of the best speakeasy bars I've ever seen. Bar is solid. Highly recommended!Great start to what can become an amazing cocktail spot! The decor and vibes are great. The space is small but not loud or overcrowded. Drinks were very well balanced. We came as walkins shortly after they opened on a thursday and waited about 40 mins so resys are definitely recommended .

Overall aWe happened upon here looking for a drink prior to a dinner reservation and im glad we did! The drinks were amazing, and atmosphere and service were all great! I loved the small cozy vibes.  I would definitely make a reservation in the future since there is very limited seating.
location: 89 Charles St, Boston, MA 02114, USA

name: Cheers
review:
It‚Äôs cheers what can you say? If you are visiting Boston and are a  Cheers show fan then this place is definitely for you. We did have to wait a little over an hour for a table in the original cheers bar.  The experience was definitely worth the wait. We were able to visit the gift shop while waitinUnfortunately not everybody knew my name but we still had a great visit... Staff was friendly as the place was packed.. beer glasses we're very cool and the beer in them was even better. We shared an appetizer sampler which had all the basic bar foods. Decent but not great.  Unfortunately the replicMy husband and I were so excited to experience "the bar" from Cheers! I was a little nervous as we had planned to stop mid-afternoon to miss the lunch rush, but plans went more quickly. We landed there right at noon. Going in, it seemed like a huge wait, but don't turn back! The place is huge! As a I really liked my experience here. Atmosphere was very cozy and cute. It looks just like the show, 2 bar areas to sit which is where we sat. Pretty busy place, but you can wait around while looking at gift shop which helps time go fast. I would go around opening at 11 am for quicker times.
Food was Super cool place! Amazing food! Atmosphere is cozy and nostalgic! Not handicap accessible, skip it if u are claustrophobic, tight, spiral steps to get upstairs to our seats...seniors in our group had a hard time walking up and down the stairs.
location: 84 Beacon St, Boston, MA 02108, USA

name: The Greatest Bar
review:
Went to the Survivor watch party and had dinner at the bar while there. To start, we have never been The Greatest Bar, so I‚Äôm just rating this on the Survivor portion of the place.

The menu was pretty cool and themed very well for the event. Wife got the tacos and I got the burger. The bartenders wAustin is hands down the most epic server ever! From the moment we sat down, he had the best energy ‚Äî friendly, funny, and so on top of everything. He made the whole night feel effortless and genuinely fun. You can tell he actually enjoys what he does, and it completely rubs off on everyone around hThe Greatest Jumbo Wings, Mushroom Swiss Burger, and California BLT.

Food/Value: A
Service/Wait Time: A
Decor/Environment: A
Parking: N/A - Boston

Cash/Credit Cards: Yes

We did the survivor theme bar and he totally played the part - 10/10!Great experience at the Survivor Fan Pop Up at The Greatest Bar. The decor was incredible, and activities were thoughtful and fun. Our server Cam was excellent, personable and helped contribute to a great experience.

name: Spy Bar
review:
Dropped by Spybar for some after-dinner drinks and loved the overall vibe. My partner really enjoyed the Lime Wire, and I went for the honey-based cocktail ‚Äî fantastic! The atmosphere was perfect for a relaxed night out, with soothing music at just the right volume so you can chat comfortably.

The Spy Bar is such a hidden gem! It‚Äôs located right near Cosmica, and once you step inside, it really gives off a cool speakeasy vibe; with its chill lighting, great atmosphere, and an inviting energy. I went on a Friday night, and they had a live DJ playing smooth, laid-back tracks that set the mood pI love the decor and the live music.  The place is perfect size and has extremely clean modern bathrooms. This is a place for late night vibes for drinks and small plates. Short rib tacos are amazing.

My waitress could have been better. She forgot a drink order, and on the bill already pre selectedCame here for drinks and dessert. The food was okay and the drinks were unique. It gives off a 70s vibe with a disco ball, dim lighting and a great dj spinning some classics. Will come again, for only drinks and the vibe.Absolutely love this place! It's really quite an experience to walk into a place that has been thoughtfully created around the acoustics. We got there early before it was too busy so we could really hear the clarity of the quality speakers, appreciate all the sound dampening, and the vibe was super
location: 40 Berkeley St, Boston, MA 02116, USA

name: Corinne Denver
review:
Here in Denver for work, and so dined solo. Alissa, server, was friendly and gracious to a solo diner. And the food was outrageously good. This is a pic of the spicy tuna bruschetta. It was such a creative, unusual mix of flavors. My taste buds enjoyed every bite of my meal!Jaimee was an awesome and welcoming server. She made us feel like she cared about our experience. The French onion soup was awesome (see photo). They gladly honored my request for my salmon cooked rare and it came out very good. The key lime pie was delicious. Highly recommended and great to find inAbsolutely amazing experience at Corinne in Denver! From the moment we sat down, the service was top-notch. Our waiter didn‚Äôt just take our order‚Äîhe walked us through some of his favorite dishes, explaining where they were sourced and how the flavors came together.

I went with the steak and eggs, wI was very pleasantly surprised by my experience at Corinne. I knew it was attached to a hotel (Le Meridien) and I‚Äôd ordinarily venture towards an independent cafe for breakfast.
The ambiance was calming and relaxing. My server Mauricio was so kind and made me feel so welcome. All of the staff were Awesome place for our anniversary dinner. Our server, Jaymee helped make it a special night. Her recommendations were spot on, and her chill presence added to the vibe. Their old fashioned was a nice spin with the black walnut - great rich flavor that complimented the burrata appetizer - which was s
location: 1455 California St, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: Wildflower
review:
Inside the Gravity Haus Hotel, this restaurant was a pleasant surprise. One of the best we've ever eaten at in Denver. Absolutely breathtaking dishes, one right after another. Beautiful presentation. Jackie was our server and she was delightful as well. Very knowledgeable with all of the dishes andWow wow wow! I was lucky enough to come here for my birthday and we were blown away by the food and service. We went for the bouquet which I highly recommend as we were able to try a big part of the menu. From the cutlery to the plates, everything was carefully and perfectly selected and you can feeThis is our second visit to Wildflower, and it was just as fantastic as our first. Staff were warm and friendly, as well as attentive and aware of guests and staff walking. They remembered it was our anniversary celebration and offered congratulations and complements multiple times. Our waitress kepEvery dish was beautifully carved and delicious. Chef Eden is creating  tasty dishes that are Michelin star caliber. The service and atmosphere was so romantic. We highly recommend this restaurant to everyone. It has vegan, vegetarian and gluten-free options as well. ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏èMy husband made reservations for us at your Michelin-recommended restaurant to celebrate our anniversary an intimate occasion. Unfortunately, from arrival to departure, the experience was profoundly disappointing and did not live up to the restaurant's reputation.
Upon arrival, the hostess was immed
location: 3638 Navajo St, Denver, CO 80211, USA

name: Mercantile
review:
Where do ya start? This place was top notch.
Tried the lunch prefix menu
That comes with a starter and an entree for $35...
Tried the autumn brussels and the broccoli caesar. Both did not miss. Perfect amounts of acidity on the brussels!

Main course did the millers chicken and the kewpie burger.

TWe were here for the happy hour while in Denver one afternoon. It‚Äôs located inside Union station. We sat at the bar and got the Mercantile High-five, a couple non alcoholic beet mocktails along with the peach and arugula salad. Everything was delicious! Our server was wonderful. Their menu options fLoved this place. Food was fantastic- loved the eggplant, the octopus was tender, the endive salad was delish. I did not love the risotto - I found the corn added too much sweetness. (I have less sweet and salt tolerance than the average person). The bread basket of Hawaiian buns was also perfect! WI visited during lunch time on a weekday to take a customer out to lunch. As it was a business meal I was looking for a place where a conversation is possible, food is good, ambiance is nice, and service leaves nothing to desire. I am glad I landed on Mercantile.

First off, the ambiance is perfect The wife and I were celebrating 21st wedding anniversary.  We sat at the counter and had 4 courses served  by the manager.  The GM popped by to say hi as well.  I was very impressed, black cod was incredible,  gnocchi fluffy as a cloud.  We did order the wine pairing and that was a great compliment.
location: 1701 Wynkoop St #155, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: Ocean Prime
review: I was surprised with a trip to Denver for my birthday & this is the restaurant where I celebrated my birthday at. This restaurant did not disappoint it‚Äôs highly rated & it deserves the praise. The staff were welcoming. The atmosphere was elegant with a cozy romantic feeling to it. The food & drinks Had a very nice meal, very attentive service, comfortable atmosphere. Menu has good variety, some nice appetizers, you can easily order off menu for cocktails. Our entrees were very well cooked, and not over seasoned nor over salted, portions were generous for this type of restaurant. Nothing will bDinner was amazing, Elliott made our night out even better. His recommendations for the Bubbles & Berries drink hit on point. My husband had the Black Orchid and it was really good too. Scallop and Rib appetizer was very tasty. We loved the Lobster Bisque and were able to split a cup. Elliott also rThis definitely is a fine dining experience. I made reservations a few days ahead of time for my 36th wedding anniversary. We got there and they already had rose petals on the table reserved for us. The waiter, Tim, was top-notch. The other staff came by often to refill our drinks and take away unneCame here for a late dinner last night and it was delicious!! Food was beautifully presented and tasted amazing. We got the calamari, filet, the lamb along side of lobster Mac n cheese. Our server sold us on everything and was a joy to talk to.
location: 1465 Larimer St, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: Salt Water Social
review:
Me and my significant other went here after attending the ballet. The food was excellent and the service was great as well.. what I didn‚Äôt like was I was charged 24.00 for a mocktail of the siren‚Äôs kiss in which I ordered two with my second mocktail being made as a refill in the same cup with the saThis place is so fun! Upscale by the ocean feel! Really enjoyed my bday dinner of shrimp and steak! Live music was great and the dessert was amazing! Cheesecake cones:) PS the Seasonal ravioli was delicious! Danielle our server was attentive and fun! PSS Management gave us free champagne! How speciaI absolutely loved my time at the Salt Water Social! Our waitress, Danielle, was absolutely amazing. Very knowledgeable on the menu and each plate we got. Always hovering in case we needed anything else! I would definitely recommend this place for any event you‚Äôre celebrating, or for a weekend trip Absolutely one of the best dining experiences I‚Äôve ever had ‚Äî hands down. If you're anywhere near the area, don‚Äôt walk ‚Äî run to this restaurant. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the food is nothing short of phenomenal, and every dish is seasoned to perfection. We were celebrating a birthday, andVibrant, coastal Ambiance is was Salt Water Social is‚Ä¶

Looking for a place to take my mother in law for brunch after church we stepped into a beautiful curated space - blues, mirrors, tropical vibes that transported you to places like Aruba or Miami.

There was welcoming decor and amenities- from a

name: The Velvet Cellar
review:
Nice but pretty expensive. We went with the table servings that we shared between our group of 6. This was nice because several of our party were light eaters. Two table size entrees and two side portions could be shared between 3-4 people. Food was delicious. I missed taking photo of the cornbread,Highly recommended. A nice atmosphere with tremendous food and a great wine list. We had the baby back ribs and the parpadelle along with a red flight that included a few nice wines including a Chilean from Colchagua and an Italian Rosso. The Ube brulee was an unexpected take on this classic dessertWent here for the first time to celebrate my and my husband's wedding anniversary. The staff had reserved us a booth with a cute card informing that we were celebrating our anniversary. We were offered complimentary glasses of champagne to celebrate, and each staff member we interacted with were verBirthdays are wonderful, especially the one I just or perhaps am still celebrating. Came here to
discover a new spot before the rest of the celebration continued.

I suggest reservations since it‚Äôs popular being so central to Ball Arena (Tate McRae concert that night), ball games and just typical doEverything was very tasty. We had the calamari, bruschetta, steak and Marsala. Service was excellent and the white wine flight was also super delicious. The only small knock was that the calamari could have used more sauce.
location: 1500 Wynkoop St #101, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: Stout Street Social
review:
We stopped by for some appetizers and drinks. They were well worth it. We were sat down within a minute and attended to quickly in the next couple of minutes as well. So service was fast and friendly.
To start we had the giant pretzel was so soft and salty, to my liking but others may find it too saGreat food, service and atmosphere! Convenient location right across from the convention center. 2 dollar shuck fridays for oysters what a hell of a deal. Super fresh and well worth it. Also the baked goat cheese spread was delicous along with the fried green tomatoes. You don't see those that oftenService was great. Food was amazing. I had the fish n chips, the Thai Calamari. It was brought to me hot and perfectly cooked. My local ipa was flat.One of the best American Cuisine spots on this side of Denver. Solid cocktails and equally solid food! We asked for a dish of Mac&Cheese to share along side our entrees and was sold after the first bite!

Both our entrees were fantastic and left no room for complaintsüî•. I gave Service a ‚Äú4 Star‚Äù purWe all had lunch here in between meetings. Everything was cooked to order and the service was absolutely fantastic. Great place to sit back and relax.

name: ChoLon - Downtown
review:

The calamari is the best I've had, as well as the beef skewers. The peach leches dessert was refreshing aHad an absolutely wonderful happy hour experience here. We will definitely be coming back and we were happy for him to notify us of the new ish location near Sloan‚Äòs Lake. Service was the highlight of this place! The food was great as well, but just a little too greasy for us.

If you‚Äôre debating on a few things, the fried rice is the way to go! That butter that comes with it is insane!!! So yummy!!!!

Easy walk to location on the corner of 16th and Blake.

name: Crema Coffee House
review:
This place, is DIFFERENT. I can tell that they care about being unique but also having such an encouraging and uplifting atmosphere. The espresso tasted very handcrafted, the cinnamon roll was incredible and the cortado my fiance got was very tasty! She loved it! More coffee shops should post obviouCentral market is this great space with several food and beverage vendors. Inside is Crema coffee. I came for the matcha on my matcha tour. I am only reviewing the matcha. The matcha was not my favorite. I had the ube matcha and to be honest I couldn‚Äôt taste the ube. It just tasted like plain old maGreat coffee brews and light bites. Sistainanle, inclusive, cool, and cheery. Def worth a stopMy new favorite coffee house in Denver! Friday mid-morning was busy but there were still plenty of seats. Cinnamon roll was otherworldly, amazing what baking in house can do. This is also one of the few places in Denver that still does pour over coffee, but only on the weekdays!This place is the OG of coffee in the Denver area. I‚Äôve been coming here since 2010 and despite the changes in staff (as any place opened as long should have) the greatness has never lapsed.
The espresso is excellent‚Ä¶they use a combination of different roasters from all over the US. It is rare that
location: 2862 Larimer St, Denver, CO 80205, USA

name: Whittier Cafe
review:
An absolute gem! I stopped here purely because I needed to use the bathroom (and  fine, I'll admit that I didn't NOT need to get some coffee and a scone) and.I was nearby, and as luck would have it I stumbled upon this amazing place.

The coffee and scone were delicious, of course, but the atmospherWalking into Whittier Caf√© feels like stepping into a warm hug‚Äîcozy, cultural, and so beautifully put together. The vibe alone makes you want to stay awhile, but then the coffee hits: bold, smooth, and unforgettable. Their pastries are fresh and flavorful, and the customer service? Absolutely top-tiVisiting my son and found this gem cafe!! Black-Owned cafe!!! Love Love!!!

Super cute interior and vibe. The menu is straight forward with nothing to crazy. The have sweet breads and danishes. They also offer teas.

Indoor and outdoor seating. Several spots to set up and get your work on as you enjBusy neighborhood cafe with breakfast items including pastries. The raspberry scone was delicious and paired well with a latte.

Service was fast and friendly. The space is in an older building but was interesting. There are counter seats, tables and an outdoor seating area. They do have Wi-Fi availI can't recommend this cafe enough! This is one of the most authentic coffee shops I have been to in Denver. They always are playing the best music, the staff makes wonderful drinks and always have great attitudes, and the culture of the cafe is so unique and much needed in Denver's community.
location: 1710 E 25th Ave, Denver, CO 80205, USA

name: Little Owl Coffee
review:
Great coffee so yummy! We had the special maple miso latte and vanilla latte with oat milk! Delicious !!!!!
Also had butter croissant and homemade pop tart. Both were good.

Feel kinda bad for the barista having to cash and also serve at the same time.

We are visiting! Thanks for the good  coffeeLittle Owl Coffee is a cozy spot with a welcoming vibe. The staff gave great drink recommendations, and it turned out to be a perfect place to enjoy a morning coffeeOutstanding lattes.  Best I've had in downtown. Very light feel but plenty of caffeine.  Smooth, no bitterness. Entrance is on the north side of Blake just west of 16th Street.Was in Denver for 5 days and this was the only coffee shop I would go back to!! It was 10/10, got an iced mocha latte and a breve and both were great.We are massive espresso drinkers (home setup) and love trying different coffee shops.

This place had a decent latte (morning fresh dairy milk- which is amazing), but a watered down americano.

Overall, I would skip the americanos and in a pinch, the latte works.
location: 1555 Blake St, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: The Weathervane Cafe
review:
This place is a diamond in the rough! We were in town for our anniversary and needed coffee before taking on the day! One of the locals suggested the Banana fosters latte and it did not disappoint, it was liquid gold in a cup. I got it iced and still had all the flavor of an actual bananas foster! WI got the caramelized banana latte and the matcha lavender scone. LOVED the scone, the frosting balanced out the scone part very well imo. The banana latte wasn‚Äôt as sweet as I was expecting which was a plus.

There is plentiful outdoor patio seating for the size of the place. Not as much indoor seaAdorable coffee shop with tasty sandwiches and good coffee.  They have lots of seating on their outdoor balcony and patio as well as inside.  I tried their Cubano sandwich and a cold brew and wasn‚Äôt disappointed.  The service is great and they have some fun little Knick knacks to purchase. Check theHad a hankering for sandwiches and the Weathervane delivered.

A couple outdoor tables were open at 2pm on a Saturday. Quirky (but comfortable) environment on the inside. Was immediately intrigued by the one of a kind sandwiches on the menu.

Tried the Strawberry Rhubarb Melt, what a show stopper! RThe ambiance in this place is killer! It's very cozy inside with cute decor. Everyone working there was so nice, and they all seemed to be enjoying each other's company, which sweetened the experience. I also work in a front-facing customer service position, and I was grateful to be reminded of how

name: Caf√© Miriam- City Park
review:
We were in Denver just to go to a concert at Red Rocks Amphitheater to see Gregory. Alan Isakov. For morning coffee and breakfast, we stopped by this place and were so pleasantly surprised by the excellent crepes and coffee. It is owned by someone with Tunisian background and he named it after his dSmall, but very good neighborhood cafe near City Park. They have a selection of breakfast sandwiches and crepes with a few pastries. The ham & Swiss sandwich was excellent warmed so the cheese was melted. The potato side was very good too as was the coffee.

Service was fast & friendly. Even the cheFeels like an authentic French Cafe, good service and the food was tasty. They‚Äôre able to make Gluten Free Crepes and I got the Toscana which was very good. It felt a bit heavy as it was a big portion which left me more than satisfied. A bit pricey with a double espresso and one crepe plus tip cominThis place is cute and quaint.  Food was good. I had the Pommes, and my daughter ordered the jacobs sandwich.  Drinks are the strawberry Italian soda and I had a medium vanilla latte.  Food everything it cost about 40$Went today with 2 friends for all of our first times here and we had such a lovely experience! All of the employees were so kind and enjoyable and we also met the owner who was wonderful and generous! The food was delicious and we‚Äôll definitely be back!

name: Migas Coffee
review: This was my favorite coffee shop in Denver! Everyone was so nice and the drinks were delicious. My husband and I had a matcha and a latte off of their fall menu. So flavorful. The yam cold foam was like Thanksgiving in your mouth. Highly recommend!Incredible coffee. Incredible prices. Incredible people. What more could you want? I got a triple shot cappuccino for $4.23. I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve paid that little in YEARS. This was my first visit in and I was extremely pleased. We didn‚Äôt have to wait at all. Service was pretty fast. Most importantly,Miga‚Äôs coffee located in the Green Spaces building had the best coffee we‚Äôve had in Denver thus far. I came for the matcha on my matcha tour though and I tried the matcha mami. The matcha was great but I am not sure what flavor profile it was supposed to have. To me it tasted just like a LaLa Land mVery cute coffee shop! I love that they have yoga classes on Wednesdays! If I was local I‚Äôd definitely be back! I got a brown sugar lavender latte (with a splash vanilla) and a ‚Äúbaddies who book club‚Äù sticker from them!Me and my husband LOVE Migas! name: Coffeegraph
review:
Great coffee. I got a chance to meet the owner. It‚Äôs a small business who are specialized in making some good quality drinks. We had the coconut matcha with a pinch a vanilla syrup. it‚Äôs not too sweet and it‚Äôs very refreshing. Highly recommend it.A tasty and unique coffee shop. I had the Aren Five Spice Latte which was outstanding!  Flavors here I haven‚Äôt seen anywhere else. They also have a beautiful custom La Marzocco espresso machine if you‚Äôre into those types of details.This place is easily the best coffee i have ever tasted. It is also the most adventurous coffee I have ever tried. Im still dumbfounded that palisade peaches could mix so perfectly with ginger oolong and cold brew! The owners are extremely kind and had great conversations with us both times we've weIncredible espresso and coffee, but also creative fun options and lots of non coffee options too. Great vibes and I didn't have the pastries but they looked delicious.

The person behind the counter was willing to chat with you about options or if you had any questions.

Highly recommend!!One of the best matcha I‚Äôve had. The pandan syrup added was aromatic and delicious. We also got the spiced coffee and the croissant pastry which were both amazing as well. The owners are so lovely. Definitely recommend and will be returning frequently.

name: Scr3am & Sugar Coffee Co.
review:
This was a spur of the moment choice, as we were looking for a coffee shop that was nearby, and the name intrigued me. I checked out the place a little on Google and it looked fun - plus 5 star review level with reviews in the triple digits, which is so rare. It did not disappoint. The vibe of this Never knew this place even existed. The puffed bagel was awesome. They have a gift shop that was full of goo and gore. Great for Halloween all year round. They had pictures from famous horror movies as well as porcelain haunted dolls and also jewelry. It was quite amusing all.the stuff they had.As a horror movie buff, I had to check this place out. It did not disappoint! The atmosphere is spooky and welcoming with loads of horror art. Their coffee is to die for and they have more than just coffee but a variety of horror themed drinks and snacks. Definitely recommend this coffee shop if youA bit different experience in coffee in this horror themed coffee shop attached to a similar shop and theater. The coffees are good including the seasonal specials such as Samoa Kooky Latte. They have a small selection of pastries.

The service was fast and friendly. The space is effectively decoratPretty cool place, both drinks we got were pretty good. Wish they had a bigger selection of snacks but it was still great.

For sure might be coming back if I am in the area. The prices are pretty decent.

name: Side Pony Coffee & Cocktails
review:
What a fun little spot for a bite and cocktails! Clean, neat, and run by a very friendly and upbeat staff, the food was excellent and the drinks very creative - though I‚Äôll skip the lavender infused one - can you say ‚Äúlaundry detergent‚Äù? - but no judgments for those who go for it! Fantastic waffle wThe espresso and honey latte were so good. The avocado toast is one of the best I've tasted and would highly recommend. Laid back atmosphere and friendly staff.Happy hour was great! I had my first aperol spritz and it was delightful! Didn‚Äôt get the bartenders name but he was super sweet and chatted with us about the menu and drink selection. Our server was also helped us find some great wine, half priced bottles of wine all night on Wednesdays! Cute spot fFabulous cafe and vibrant atmosphere.  Loved the food, drinks, and decor.  The day I was the they had the Easter bunny taking pictures with the neighborhood dogs and rescue puppies for adoption.  It was so special! Will return,  highly recommend.Love! Friendly staff, very chill vibe at 8:30AM on a Friday morning. If you're here to work, there are no outlets under the black bench seating (which is very comfy btw) but there are a few under the bar at the front. WiFi speed is great - 490mbps download/86mbps upload. üë©üèª‚Äçüíª

name: 54thirty Rooftop
review:
Great location. Great view of the mountains and the city. Service was quick. Our server was very attentive, kept checkin on us, (i think her name was summer?)I forgot. Good vibes. Came on a Friday evening for our last night in denver heading back to nyc the next day. Started nice and chill, only a fMy wife and I did an anniversary weekend in Colorado and this place was highly recommend.  So glad we made it, great experience.  Drinks were great on a hot day, charcuterie board was perfect and the views were amazing. It was a little empty when we arrived but quickly filled up. And it's free accesThis bar has a great vibe ‚Äî good music, well-made cocktails, and a really nice view of the mountains.

I also appreciate that they don‚Äôt let it get overcrowded, which makes the experience much more enjoyable.

That said, the prices and the long wait times don‚Äôt really match the overall experience. IThe view is not okay at all because there are many tall buildings block the view.
Staffs are very attentive and very helpful.
Crab taco is very delicious.
Chicken satay is too sweet It‚Äôs not satay at all.
It is teriyaki chicken.
Love the drinks  üç∏The views from this rooftop bar are stunning.  I didn‚Äôt particularly like the cocktails.  I had the lavender sky and then switched to wine.  My friend has multiple old fashions and enjoyed thoroughly.   Plenty of seating and places to stand. Head here for sunset.

name: Union Lodge No.1
review:
Great selection of hand crafted cocktails. Drinks were well made and reasonably priced for the service and experience. I wanted to order the gin fizz but opted for one of the punches instead. Seems hard to go wrong no matter your preference. But order something that allows these bartenders‚Äô experienPassing through town and met one of my former co-workers here at this bar. She said that it always pops up on her list of best bars and places to go to. We got there just after 6:00 and the place was pretty packed and looks like the crowd turns over pretty quickly as the bartenders are really friendIf you are looking for a great tasting and unique cocktail, this place is a must. The atmosphere is awesome and the service was over the top (especially from Austin and Abby). I will definitely stop in again next time I am in Denver.Wow, what a great place! The vibe and atmosphere are just right. Rustic look, good music to set the tone and great drinks.

The menu pays homage to early century cocktails but has plenty of modern options as well. Drinks are fairly priced as most seem to be in the $1?.00‚Äôs.

The drinks in the picturThe bartender Eugene is one of the best bartenders my husband and I have ever met. His technique and detail was amazing. We truly enjoyed and appreciated watching him make cocktails for hours!
The Gin Fizz is my favorite - sort of like a delicious milk shake. The way Eugene blends the egg whites and

(Do the Voltaire for your fortune) also get the flowers shot!!‚ÄônnI was not pleased with my time here, we came for a bachelorette party and we had a guy following our group of girls and we told the bouncer. name: Tom's Watch Bar - Coors Field
review:
I stopped into Tom‚Äôs Watch Bar on a Wednesday night and found the place surprisingly empty. I ordered two beers and the Nashville hot chicken. The chicken was tasty with a huge portion size, but it wasn‚Äôt anything exceptional. The fries were pretty underwhelming. With the beers, the bill came to aboI had an amazing experience at Tom‚Äôs Bar, thanks to our fantastic server, Karen!!  They were attentive, friendly, and made sure our drinks and food arrived promptly. Karen went above and beyond, checking in just the right amount and offering great recommendations from the menu. Their warm personalitJust tried Tom's and honestly, I‚Äôm still thinking about those wings. They were perfectly crispy on the outside and juicy inside ‚Äî exactly how wings should be. The Buffalo flavor had the right amount of kick without being too spicy.

Bojana our waitress service was chill and friendly ‚Äî the kind of plWe saw the 7th game of the OKC/Pacers game here, so that is the context. Very busy, very noisy, but to be expected. There were a few available tables that needed to be cleaned but we were told nothing was available and they were not taking names for tables that became available. Made no sense - partHad a really nice Saturday at Tom‚Äôs. Oscar recommended the double dragon fruit Moscow mule and it was so scrumptious. We also got the nachos and a few beers/espresso martinis and those were great too. If you guys stop by Tom‚Äôs ask for Oscar and he will take great care of you.
