name: The Wild
review:
We went in the morning and got toast and jam, little latte, and a mimosa to start our day! We can tell the atmosphere here is really nice definitely during cocktail hours but we couldn‚Äôt make it. Easy to say that we had a good time though!Their happy hour deals are worth it - $8 espresso martinis! I don‚Äôt think there is any food on the happy hour but the couple small things I‚Äôve had here have been great. Bread and butter comes with flaky sea salt.

The location is perfect and their outside space is great.Craft cocktail bar serving house signature and classic cocktails as well as beer and wine.  Indoor and outdoor seating available.  Staff is friendly and knowledgeable about the menu items.  Ordered a Bemba Rosa and a Paper Star.  Both tasted as good as they looked.  Great presentation and flavors.  We just had some coffees and muffin, but cute place to go on dates and cocktail collection also seems pretty good.I stopped in for a drink and a snack on a Sunday afternoon & I loved this place! It‚Äôs so light and bright. The food was good and very well plated. Also, the servers are so kind. I would definitely just sit here and do some work or come for a drink later in the day.
location: 1660 Wynkoop St Suite 100, Denver, CO 80202, USA

name: Mockingbird
review:
Love this spot in Denver. Amazing drinks and service.  Really cool set up and little place to hang all over the venue.  They host music here and have a great crowd.  Definitely a vibe if you‚Äôre in the area.This is a very unique venue,  more of an art piece then your regular bar or club.  They have multiple themed rooms that have a different vibe then the others.  Go check it out!This is one of the coolest clubs in Denver! Great music, great vibes, super friendly staff, and the decorations are AMAZING! Very artsy and vibey. Lots of cool places to hang out if dancing isn't your vibe for the night.What an amazing environment‚Ä¶ definitely for the adult crowd, that likes to dance, have great drinks, and an atmosphere that takes you too another level‚Ä¶

Great bartender by Vic, really seems to engage with the guests and make sure that each drink is just the way you want itComing from NYC being reccomended to this as a safe space to exist in(similar to house of yes) I left in tears at the realization that this space is simply riding the wave of ‚Äúrave/plur culture‚Äù but not delivering in ANY WAY. I‚Äôve never left a space feeling so sad about our collective  future.

name: Coyote Ugly
review:
SO cool in here! Huge bar with tons of space, great music, and lots of games . We played pool and had a few drinks - bar tender was great & helpful, lots of good photos ops and stuff to look at all around the walls - they sell swag shirts and hats in the front store. Would be cool to come back on a NO food, NO service n here is the atmosphere
This establishment was less than enjoyable, during the floor game (musical squares) a female SHOVED my niece out of the spot and proceeded to push her again, not one security staff addressed this issue with the woman. Thats how trouble starts, they're HIRMy wife and I live across the street and came in for one drink on Monday as we‚Äôve never been to a coyote ugly before and honestly we probably won‚Äôt go back. It seems like a cool place for younger people wanting to party, but the insane overpricing for drinks made us not want to go back. My wife had It was our first time there and definitely not gonna be last!  We loved the bartender girls vibe and atmosphere was also nice. We danced on the bar with the bartender and the shots are also affordable and good though. I think weekdays are not super busy, but still they‚Äôre doing great.Country bar that‚Äôs typically not playing country music honestly. Most of the girls are very nice and super fun so service is great. They do water down their beers as well so ask for it in a can. Not the most recommend bar.

name: Lady Jane
review:
I can‚Äôt think of one note for the cocktails service, or atmosphere at Lady Jane.  Every sip was perfection.  The team are total pros.  The room is a delightful space that just feels good.

If you‚Äôre in Denver, make this your regular spot.  If you‚Äôre visiting Denver DEFINITELY make a trip to lady janIt was our first time at Lady Jane. We had a great time and the drinks were phenomenal. I think I got the Bussey? I don‚Äôt see it on their menu on the website but it was something like that. The cheese plate was simple and divine. Drinks are slightly expensive, but exceptional. I can‚Äôt wait to come bOver priced and overrated. My cocktail was a coffee passionfruit cardamom mix that was not good. I tried to drink it and sipped on it for an hour but could not finish it. I passed it to 8 other people at the table but no one liked it or wanted it so I couldnt even give it away. When it came time to My my my what a great experience at Lady Jane we had tonight! Ethan was our server and was extremely knowledgeable, we like some pretty adventurous libations and we weren‚Äôt disappointed one bit. One drink tasted like a Caesar salad and one tasted like a deviled egg, no joke. If that wild of a cocktaHad an amazing time here! My wife and I celebrated our 1st anniversary with some post-dinner drinks and it couldn't have been better. Our waitress was so nice and helpful with explaining the menu and suggestions on drinks. name: The Devil‚Äôs Drink
review:
Cool vibes, the smell is off putting upon entering. The bathroom was cute, but the sink hardware was loose. They had a room of 4 pool tables. Staff was friendly and the espresso martinis were to die for. Only downside of them was so much whip cream! But if you like that, it‚Äôs a must. They were some The Devil‚Äôs Drink has officially leveled up at their new Platte St. location. The cocktails are just as creative and delicious as ever, and now they serve food too (highly recommend the deviled eggs + oysters).

My favorite was Santa Maria‚Äôs Last Prayer ‚Äî smooth, horchata-like, and dangerously good.Staff was phenomenal we had two great servers who we did not get the names of but were amazing. Charlotte was funny and gorgeous and the drinks were delicious. Shout out to the guy from the kitchen who took a selfie after taking photos of usü§†Spooky vibes and delicious espresso martinis! Try the Lillith in White Lace. Ice cold and tastes just like a raspberry truffle. Will be coming back for dessert drinks whenever we're in Denver.Saw this spot just opened, and I was impressed! Cocktails were on point and creative, and the food was even better. It's like a high end michelin food experience without the insane price tag. If you haven't tried it yet, give this spot a shot. review:

I‚Äôm genuinely disappointed with how far this place has fallen. It used to be one of the best spots around for both vegan and regular food ‚Äî great quality, great service. Sadly, that‚Äôs no longer the case.
On my most recent visit, the food was bCool place to eat! Outdoor seating with heaters! Hand made chocolates are yummy! Food is great! A fancier restaurant with higher prices! Garlic knots with cheese and marina dips are great! Skillet cornbread with honey butter was good! Crab cakes and salmon were delicious!Food is great and fresh. I got the cheeseburger and fried okra.  My husband got the chicken fried steak meal with gravy, macaroni and cheese, green beans and a waffle.  No complaints.  All very good.  Andy was our waitress on both occasions and she was great. Ambience is very nice and bright. I woulThis unforgettable meal took place at Founding Farmers, a restaurant well-known in Washington, D.C. for its hearty American dishes and farm-to-table concept. I actually decided to come here because Adam recommended it to me‚Äîand I am so glad I followed his advice.

The experience was wonderful from tA downtown restaurant, very close to the White House. The place is large, spread over two floors, and well designed inside, featuring a piano bar and a central counter.

name: Old Ebbitt Grill
review:
First time here and wow‚Äîwhat a great experience! I was kind of bummed about missing the first UT game while in D.C., but to my surprise, they had it playing on the only TV in the back bar, right where I was sitting. Pretty sure my UT shirt had something to do with that. üòâ

The longer I stayed, the mAbsolutely incredible. This place was recommended to me, and I recommend it to everyone. I had the swordfish, and it was tasty. But that was nothing compared to the oysters that we got, as well as the scallops. Absolutely divine; it was clear that the food was fresh. I also cannot recommend the breaOld Ebbitt Grill in Washington, DC, is a classic dining spot that lives up to its reputation. The atmosphere is historic and charming, making it a perfect place to enjoy a memorable meal in the capital. I tried the crab dip and the fried calamari, and both were absolutely outstanding‚Äîthe crab dip waSat at the Main bar to have a bite to eat. Our bartender, Jake was great! Very attentive. Sent us a dessert for my birthday as well as the Fried Green Tomatoes (so delicious!). Oysters were nice and fresh and the broth the mussels were in was amazing. Definitely order more bread! Thanks for the tastGreat place to eat. Our tour guide suggested it and I‚Äôm glad we went.

Our server was excellent. He was knowledgeable about the menu items and continued to check on us especially after my boyfriend said he was cold and ordered a coffee.

I had the meat loaf and he had the famous crab cakes. Both dis

name: La Grande Boucherie DC
review:
We had an amazing experience. Everything was perfect ‚Äî the food, the atmosphere, and the service.
Mariana was our server, she was professional with a beautiful smile. She took care of us carefully.

Went in for a celebratory dinner with my sister tonight and everything went perfectly. Amine, our server, was incredibly attentive and friendly. All of his recommendations were fantastic. Got the wagyu carpaccio and salade cesar, as well as the prime bone-in ribeye with peppercorn sauce. Desserts weüí≤üí≤üí≤
This was a very sophisticated restaurant! I mean from the grand entrance to an amazing staircase that led us into an exquisite dining area! I could describe this over and over! It was breathtaking.

We were met by the charming host who walked us up to our table with a whole lot of enthusiasm andLa Grande Boucherie in Washington, D.C., is just a few blocks from the White House. It features an impressive Art Nouveau-style atmosphere and stunning architecture. It makes for a perfect spot for special occasions or romantic dinners. The food is exceptional and refined; salads, escargots, and scaAlex made the best spicy Bloody Mary , and we also had a pj breeze and Riley was very attentive and the service was fantastic.  The place is very spacious and bright, great music , even a piano was played. Felt like I was on vacation.  Definitely coming back - the steak and eggs was perfect. amazing

name: Le Diplomate
review:
Le Diplomate is an incredible spot for date night. It‚Äôs right on 14th Street and perfectly captures that classic European brasserie atmosphere. It‚Äôs definitely on the pricier side, but absolutely worth it for a special evening.

I highly recommend the steak frites, escargot, and duck. The duck, in pMy experience at this restaurant was excellent with the food and the service. The decor of the place was very pretty. The food was delicious. The coffee was super delicious, with an intense and tasty flavor. I loved it. The waiter who served us, I have to say this. We had a small incident with the cMy lunch at Le Diplomate in D.C. was truly exquisite. The atmosphere is authentically French and wonderfully charming. It is full of energy, conversation, and a fun vibe.

Since it was a gorgeous day in the 70s, I was especially grateful to sit outside on the covered patio and enjoy the afternoon.

Love the aesthetic and vibe of this place moreso than the food or drinks. The burger was good (not cooked as ordered = medium) and the scallops were good. Nothing phenomenal. Old fashioned was good. Just all around a very ok/good experience.First, it should be noted the atmosphere of the restaurant is beautiful and would be the perfect setting for an evening outing. The service was great, and our server was kind, attentive, and knowledgeable. But as far as food goes, it was underwhelming. Beautifully presented but in taste and flavor i
location: 1601 14th St NW, Washington, DC 20009, USA

name: Grazie Nonna
review:
First time here and I really enjoyed it! I got the Caesar salad, calamari, and the Drunken Love pizza, everything was delicious. The pizza was definitely my favorite, especially paired with the garlic sauce that came with the calamari. The vibe was great and everything tasted super fresh. My only smCozy Italian Vibes at Grazie Nonna in DC
I recently dined at Grazie Nonna in Washington, DC, and it was a charming spot for Italian-American comfort food. Nestled at 1100 15th St. NW, the restaurant boasts a lively, welcoming atmosphere with a fun breezeway setting‚Äîperfect for a casual meal with friI absolutely love this place! I came here recently for my best friend‚Äôs last meal in DC before moving out of state. Grazie Nonna was our top choice and it did not disappoint. Our server was incredibly kind, personable, and attentive from start to finish.

We started with the Caesar salad for the tabA true taste of Italy! All of the appetizers, entr√©es, and drinks were excellent‚Äîflavorful, fresh, and well-prepared. The service was friendly and attentive, which made the evening even better. The only downside was the dessert; the brownie fell short for us as it was a bit dry and lacked the cannolEverything was delicious. One of only 2 restaurants that I've been to that actually does al dente. Like spot on Italy authentic al dente. The Sunday sauce was as close to actual homemade. The service is second to none. Love, absolutely LOVE this place.

name: Unconventional Diner
review:
Fantastic experience at the Unconventional Diner! The menu lives up to the name with tons of different cuisines represented in the dishes (very unconventional‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve never eaten at a restaurant with this much variety). Everything we had was delicious. I loved the Lebanese fried rice and the meatloaf I found this gem when searching for the best brunch restaurants in DC before my visit. Everything on the menu sounds great, so it was hard to decide. We got the Lebanese Fried Rice with Falafel and the S"Eggs"y Sandwich - both were amazing! I almost didn‚Äôt get the fried rice because I was leaning toUnconventional Diner really lived up to the hype. The food was amazing and the staff was super friendly and welcoming throughout the whole visit. I tried the chicken and waffles for the first time and I wouldn‚Äôt regret that choice one bit. The chicken was juicy, flavorful, and tender, and the sauce The place looked swamped on a Saturday afternoon but to our surprise, we were seated almost right away. I ordered a matcha latte and it came so fast, my husband was not even back from the washroom. We ordered both French toast and pancake for our two picky kids, they offered to put topping on the siThis is a great brunch spot to start the day, for that much needed energy to explore the city.
Friendly, welcoming staff who go above and beyond! Reserved online and requested something special since it was our anniversary and they did not disappoint :)

name: SUCCOTASH
review:
I went last weekend on 8/9/25 with just me and my sister. The restaurant is in a great location, and the interior is lovely. My sister and I are big Chef Edward Lee fans Disclaimer: went here for Mother‚Äôs Day and I totally forgot to write my review so this is slightly late!

Nonetheless this place deserves a great review!

The restaurant is gorgeous from the moment you walk in, the high ceiling and elegant decor draws you in. You can get a breathtaking view from upsEnded up stopping by after visiting the American Art Museum and was pleasantly surprised by our meal here! It ended up being a late lunch (3:00) so the restaurant was not packed which allowed for a quiet, relaxing atmosphere. The host was friendly and waitress was quiet but sweet and informative. BaBeautiful restaurant. Delicious food. Great service, with a fun personality (Melka)! My friend and I shared the catfish entree, a long with sides of dirty rice and the collard greens with kimchi before going to Ford's Theatre. Just the right amount of food and very flavorful.After trying the national harbor location, we decided to try the downtown location because we really enjoyed our previous experience. Of course this time we were not disappointed also. I think the cornbread we had at the national harbor location was better, with more hot flavor. The chicken wings we
location: 915 F St NW, Washington, DC 20004, USA

name: Zaytinya
review:
Zaytinya is one of my favorite go to restaurants. I love their outdoor seating patio, which they have invested in since COVID. The patio has covered tents and actual fine dining chairs and tables that elevate the area. I‚Äôve eaten outdoors during temperate winter days as well and their heaters work wReally nice restaurant!
Great feel.
Busy but not too loud.
Terrific food.
We did Pre-theatre fix prix menu.
Four courses.
Generous portions.
Everything was great
Especially loved the Fattoush, lamb, chicken & brussel sprouts‚Ä¶
Tasty, light, but filling‚Ä¶!
Across from the Portrait Gallery.
Highly RecomMy husband and I went here for brunch and got their $70 special and I must say, I have never been to a spot where we‚Äôve enjoyed brussel sprouts as much as I have right here. Needless to say, their portions are good size (not too big), and their food is beautiful and delicious. Their bread is also veLove the location and outdoor patio. The food is outstanding. We love the shareable plates and the unique spins on traditional dishes. Even the bread is fun- the puffy bread shows up to the table and is then used for all the unique dips and spreads.
Love the chicken and even the garlic paste.My partner and I dined here during DC Restaurant Week. We each had a special four-course Mediterranean meal. We also ordered a unique drink, and the dishes were all things we'd never ordered or tried before, which was impressive. I really enjoyed my meal here; the food was delicious and the service

name: ala
review:
My wife and I went for our anniversary based off a recommendation from friends. The atmosphere was great both outside and in. The staff went above and beyond. If I could offer any advice, listen to their recommendations for food and drink. We had amazing cocktails, small plates, entrees and dessertsWe have been wanting to try this new Mediterranean place. We had an early dinner around 5 o‚Äôclock on a Sunday night.The food was delicious especially loved the beef kebab. Pita bread is hands down the best in the area. Everything is fresh and tasty. Service was great too. Outdoor seating is lovely.We came for restaurant week and had a great time. It was four courses and we added the four drinks to go with it. It was especially nice that they did regular menu items + regular sizes so you could get a sense of what it is usually like. The bread and dips were great, we really liked the potatoes aWe had an unforgettable dinner at ala in DuPont. Our server Jamie was a wonderful host and accommodating for our dietary restrictions. The food was some of the best we‚Äôve had in DC. Some favorites were the za‚Äôatar labneh, baba ghanoush, duck prosciutto, and chicken thigh kebab. Do not skip on the whThis place was good !! Couldn‚Äôt have been more content with what I ate. It is pricey, but we did have coupons through InKind app which was nice
The ambiance is beautiful and very cool.
Coffee was good and the little sweet was interesting.
The flat bread incredible, duck prosciutto was something new

name: DUA DC Coffee
review:
Dua Coffee DC is a cozy little gem right in the heart of Washington, DC, close to the embassy offices. We stopped by during the quiet morning hours, and even then it was bustling with people‚Äîwhich says a lot about its popularity.

The ambience was warm and inviting, with a nice vibe all around. I onI stopped by today and found out there was a special event happening in the back of the shop. Even with the event going on, everyone was still very welcoming. Tried their coffee. It was amazing! The Pour Over and Piccolo hit the spot. Although there weren‚Äôt any empty seats inside, I really enjoyed mHaving heard great reviews about this place, I decided to try out their mango matcha latte

I was very disappointed as it seems like I was just served a milkshake. The drink was overly sweet and I could barely taste the matcha in it. I understand the mango makes it sweet by default, but this seemed Stunning little coffee shop with clean restrooms and polite staff! I can say confidently that this is the best coffee shop in DC. Their coffee is rich and well flavored, it is not to sweet and not burnt. Definitely will return and recommend!!My partner recommended me this place and omg it was amazing. I got a latte and he got an espresso. It was the most earthy delicious coffee I‚Äôve had in a long time. I literally savored every sip. Inside was super calm and lovely music in the background. Definitely coming back when I visit D. C. Again

For my overall experience, I‚Äôd definitely give this Caf√© 5 stars, the great food, warm atmosphere, and excellent service.

name: Big Bear Cafe
review:
Nice cafe, lovely setting, nice people.

Friendly servers and smiley faces when you come in, lovely setting (vines on the outside of the building which made in look like an Italian place, and nice wooden tables inside and out), and nice atmosphere with a good soundtrack!

Coffee and drinks were surpI enjoyed a flat white and breakfast burrito here. The overall atmosphere was lovely to enjoy my breakfast and read for a bit. Lots of people were working from their laptops (they have wifi), chatting with one another, or grabbing something to-go. The staff was friendly, and there was ample seating Lovely little caf√©, and a lovely little neighborhood, they also have a farmers market outside on Sunday mornings, which makes for a full Sunday experience: cute latte, and baked goods and a stroll of the stands, what more could you ask for? ü•∞
I won‚Äôt claim it. It‚Äôs the best coffee I‚Äôve ever had, andWe hosted our 60-person wedding at Big Bear Cafe in May 2025, and we are so thrilled we did. From the start of our venue search, the event manager Bri was attentive and organized. On the day itself, the staff were so proactive, helpful and kind. Many guests told us that they loved the venue, and thaHad our wedding here and had a wonderful experience. They were easy to work with, the staff was great, and the food and drinks were delicious. I would highly recommend them if you are considering having your event here.

name: WARKA COFFEE
review:
Warka Coffee is not in the "heart of Capitol Hill," but it does offer up close views of the U.S. Capitol. Opened in August 2025, I popped into Warka Coffee since I love a new coffee shop. Here's my experience.

1) Coffee: I ordered a large latte and it was good. It's darker than I usually enjoy, butWe had the smoked caramel iced latte with the avocado toast and nutty banana toast. The coffee has such a nice flavor, and very smooth! Food tasted good as well and there wasn't much of a wait to get our order. We really loved the cozy and homey ambiance, lots of natural light and greenery. Cute, unIt was such a wonderful experience, the ambiance was so chill and homey. I love the aesthetic. The food and coffee is amazing and the staff were very welcoming. Will definitely recommend and will definitely come back soon!!Lovely coffee shop! Very knowledgeable & friendly staff. The variety of coffee is perfectly simple without a bunch of overwhelming choices, yet still enough variety to accommodate everyone‚Äôs tastes. The atmosphere is cozy & comforting. I will visit every time I‚Äôm in DC!Excellent coffee and food!
We had three types of coffee and everything was great. The avocado sandwich and the pastries were fresh and delicious. The team was very friendly.

name: Little Hat Coffee
review:
Finally got to try little hat! They have unique drinks available along with the standard coffee and tea options. I wanted to try a seasonal special so I went with the orange blossom latte. It was more on the floral side and didn‚Äôt have much of the orange flavor I was expecting, but it was still goodCoffee Shop No. 502
Little Hat Coffee
Washington, DC
April 24, 2025

Little Hat Coffee maybe small and sit quietly in the back corner of Streets Market, a neighborhood grocery store, but it‚Äôs serving up some mighty bold and big coffee!

The cortado was not only smooth with just the right balance of Little Hat Coffee is an absolute gem! The place has a warm, inviting vibe that makes you want to stay a while. The coffee is top-notch ‚Äî rich, smooth, and clearly made with care. The baristas are friendly and always up for a quick chat or a great recommendation. I tried their cappuccino and it was pA coffee shop inside a market is always a good idea and Little Hat Coffee is worth a visit. Step inside Streets Market and head to the very back near the registers. Here you'll find a little coffee shop with bar seating only. The menu is small, but mighty. They have lattes, espresso, cappuccino, andOver a five-day visit I tried six espresso bars in D.C., and Little Hat was the clear standout by a wide margin. It is run by a young, switched-on crew pulling consistently excellent shots. This is not the place for a Starbucks-style frappuccino. It is the place for a cappuccino or latte made proper

name: Yours Cafe
review:
We had a delicious breakfast out with family. The atmosphere felt like home and the food was phenomenal. We all tried something different. We could not pick and choose which dish was the best. I also can‚Äôt forget the coffee was excellent and the pastries were good. Thank you Yours cafe.Yours Coffee has an easygoing, calm vibe that makes it a great place to relax or get some work done. The atmosphere feels a little old-school in the best way ‚Äî cozy, inviting, and comfortable.

The food is excellent ‚Äî fresh, well-prepared, and presented beautifully. From hearty salads to comforting I had such a wonderful experience at Yours Coffee! From the moment we walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting. I ordered the Warm Cinnamon Roll Latte with almond milk, and it was absolutely divine ‚Äî perfectly balanced with cinnamon and white chocolate, smooth, and served piping hot in the cuAmazing breakfast spot! The food was fresh and delicious, portions were generous, and the coffee was perfect. The place is clean, cozy, and has a great vibe. Service was friendly and fast. Definitely one of the best breakfast places I‚Äôve been to‚Äîhighly recommend!I wish I could give more than 5 stars! ‚≠êÔ∏è This was such a wonderful experience from
The warmest greetings from the staff all the way to the owner. That made us feel like family. The food was absolutely delicious and one of favorite breakfast outside of our home in a long time.

name: The Alchemist DC
review: This is another speakeasy vibe bar with delicious and creative drinks. The place doesn‚Äôt serve food but has chips to buy! We went here for Happy hour and stayed on a bit longer to try other drinks on the menu. The menu had creative drinks were a fun treat for the eyes and the palette. I started off I stumbled upon The Alchemist while looking for speakeasy-style bars in DC, and I'm so glad we stopped by! The drinks had very creative names, and the presentation of them made the experience all the better! Not to mention the taste - every drink I tried was delicious! It was such a phenomenal find I didn't rate "food" because they only serve drinks. There is a Jumbo Slice pizza not far away, though. I don't drink alcohol often these days. HOWEVER, the drinks here are absolutely S-tier and worth it. Despite the theatrics, of which my cousin was obsessed with, I thoroughly enjoyed the drinks I The drinks are tasty and fun. The atmosphere was nice and I could see it being regular spot if the price wasn't so high. It feels predatory to have no prices on the menu when the drinks are $20+ each. We got 2 drinks and with the auto 20% gratuity our bill was $65...The staff were quick with the drinks, and each wad delivered with wonderful showmanship (in addition to the delicious smoke scent). A wonderful bar to entertain friends from near and far, I'd come again for sure!

name: Code Red
review:
A truly one-of-a-kind speakeasy! This hidden gem offers an unforgettable experience from the moment you walk in. The ambiance is captivating‚Äîmoody, stylish, and perfectly curated to transport you to another time. The vibe is effortlessly cool, with just the right balance of sophistication and edge. My friends and I visited on a Friday evening and nothing disappointed us. We were a group of 7 and got a section that everyone was able to enjoy and be comfortable in. Our waiter Emilio was amazing, he was attentive and friendly. The $1 oysters were a hit, briny and a good size. The food was quick tRED ALERT! CODE RED is a total VIBE and one of DC‚Äôs best hidden gems!

My friend and I hit up CODE RED in Adams Morgan to celebrate Mardi Gras‚Äîand WOW, what a night!

This speakeasy-style bar is tucked away behind an unassuming steel door, but trust me, what‚Äôs behind it is pure magic. From the momenAwesome spot!! Mark at the door was super welcoming even though I didn't have a reservation and took the time to explain how the menu worked, which I really appreciated. The bartender was personable, easy to chat with, and made wonderful drinks (both on and off the menu).  Lastly, the vibe of the plThis is such a fun place to eat dinner. The speak easy vibes are fun and even had live music. The food was pretty good. A little disappointed in the portion sizes, small portions at a higher price. The cr√®me br√ªl√©e was lacking flavor, not the best by far. Service was good.
location: 2440 18th St NW, Washington, DC 20009, USA

name: Lost & Found DC
review:
Come here for a private event. Even though the place was packed to the brim the bartenders did their very best and made everyone‚Äôs drinks quickly. I had the spritz which was very tasty and well made. I loved the license plate decor which was certainly a nice touch to give that dive bar feel for a grGreat drinks and an electric vibe. There are a number of bars in the Convention Center area worth checking out. Lost and Found is certainly one of them!Underwhelming bar...even though the drink list looks pretty good. Loud bar, somewhat divey. I was definitely served the wrong beer, although didn‚Äôt have time to question it because the bartenders are very inattentive. Had high hopes for this one because it looked cool from the outside, but they fellCool bar with underground pub feel. The patrons are a bit preppy and quirky. The bartender we had was short and not friendly. He was huffing and puffing when we asked to try a beer. Like...Bartender and manager are  absolutely horrible
They are not friendly. I told the manager her Bartender wasn't good and I was asked to leave.
The Bartender didn't ask me what was the issue.
There are plenty of places to drink. DONT DRINK
HERE. GO HERE SOMEWHERE ELSE.

name: Madhatter
review: Fantastic establishment. Warms my heart that Madhatter's still very much holdin' it down on this lil' drag of Dupont. I remember coming here on their soft opening (2010?) when they moved from their old M street location. Same comfortable place has only gotten better with age. Mindblowingly low priceIf you're looking for a low key kinda divey, nothing too fancy spot, then this is it. We came in for happy hour and thought the $6 bites was a good value, however, the food want all that great. The mac n cheese bites and chicken tenders were basically frozen meals. And the nachos were pretty basicInvited to a luncheon here for a group of 12. Great company and an even greater lunch! The servers were very attentive to our needs. Love the ceiling with the upside down dining table setting.Excellent service! Great spot to watch football. The brunch food was soooooo good. I would definitely eat here again!It‚Äôs tiny. But it‚Äôs a bunch of fun. Two levels, not terrible drink prices, and some very creative drinks. It‚Äôs simple but perfect. Places to sit, multiple dance floors. I‚Äôd definitely go again.
location: 1319 Connecticut Ave NW, Washington, DC 20036, USA

name: Service Bar DC
review: I think the server was having a bad day or had other personal things going on because they were pretty short and were not too helpful when we had questions. The establishment, however, probably had the best chicken tenders I've ever tasted with house made ranch, honey mustard, a Chipotle like sauce,This is going to be our new go to bar before going to see shows at DC9, The Atlantis, or 930 Club. Drinks here are amazing, the fried chicken is fantastic, and the happy hour deals aren‚Äôt bad. We really enjoyed the laid back vibe, and I was a huge fan or the mostly late aughts pop punk music playingTop notch. Chic bar with just enough grunge to know I don't need to be dressed to the nines to sit down for a unique drink one can't find elsewhere. It's not just about nuanced flavors of ingredients like mushroom butter and acorn liquer that seem like they shouldn't go together, but do. It's about Noisy but otherwise incredible. The cocktails are fantastic and well balanced. The fried chicken? Soooo good. Great sides and I'm not usually a Mac n cheese guy. Server took great care of us. Definitely will be back.An absolute gem. The welcoming nature coziness, and reasonable prices of a great neighborhood bar combined with a menu full of great cocktails - both solid classics as well as a number of unique creations with great flavors. The food was delicious and the staff was a blast.
location: 926-928 U St NW, Washington, DC 20001, USA

name: barmini
review:
A magical experience with some of the most creative cocktails I've found anywhere.

barmini's sample flight is absolutely worth it. When you enter, you're surrounded by an incredible space - bright with all sorts of unique decorations that will reveal new things on each visit. The service is top notSometimes you go somewhere and it is so good you know you want to stop by each time you are in town. Barmini was so phenomenal that from the moment we had our first sip we were planning a future trip solely around being able to come in and experience the magical drinks, service, and food once again.This place is a gem in all the ways - thoughtful, creative craft. Every drink is delicious and the little bites are so yummy and with an excellent presentation. The drink menu is inventive and unending in options. Try delicious things you‚Äôve never heard of or thought about.Wonderful experience! Foods were great. Wished there was one more main protein dish. Overall very good experience.Barmini Review: An Exceptional Cocktail Experience
Barmini isn‚Äôt your typical bar‚Äîit‚Äôs an immersive experience where cocktails meet theater. From the moment you sit down, you‚Äôre watching bartenders use techniques like liquid nitrogen and color-changing ingredients to create drinks that are as visual

name: The Golden Age
review: Golden Age is a fun old school DC restaurant with an almost speakeasy type vibe and fantastic cocktails.  Definitely take advantage of their happy hour.  I recommend having a reservation, but we arrived shortly after they opened at 5pm and were able to snag a table for two.  Their food menu is just Had a wonderful time at this bar. The cocktails were expertly crafted and the food was delicious. The live music created a charming and inviting atmosphere and the service was outstanding. We truly felt like we were among friends and familyGreat place for drinks and food, a good girls night or wine night or relaxing evening for 30s and up! Great ambience and darker lighting sets a good mood and atmosphere. Love it here and continue to bring friends to enjoy the gem close to DuPont!I just picked this bar because I could get to it quickly from where I was based, and I heard they served late night food. I'm so glad I did. Turns out they serve food all night! So even though it was after 10pm when I arrived, I could get a full delicious double patty burger. Unfortunately, I ate itI liked this place! Lovely decor and vibe, cozy with a vintage feel. We had a double date here. The menu is extensive, and both drinks I had (Paloma and Naked and Famous) were quite good. Prices are steep but not unreasonable. My chicken kebab with yogurt was alright, spicy and favorable but not sup

name: Gypsy Kitchen DC
review:
I came here to have lunch or brunch with my family around 1 p.m. The hostess told us there was a 30-minute wait, so we waited at the bar until our table was ready. The bartender was a super friendly guy. We immediately felt welcomed.

I had a wonderful experience at this restaurant! The food was absolutely delicious, with great flavors and quality that truly stood out. The prices were very reasonable, offering excellent value for the quality of the dishes.

A beautiful restaurant with delicious food! We always sit on the patio upstairs and the ambience is unmatched. A must have is the lamb hummus, which blows our minds every time. The sangria is delicious and we went during cherry blossom time and they had some delicious cherry blossom themed cocktailsFood is great, I especially like the Mussels, their soup base makes it so good and the mussels are fresh. They have lots of seats but still very busy. Our service was okay but for some reason, he seemed very unhappy and annoyed even though he barely stop by.For summer brunch, we recommend the lamb hummus (comes with seasoned pita), the tomato salad, the french toast and the shakshouka. Our server was very helpful for recommendations and the ambiance of the restaurant is warm and comfortable. Highly recommend!

name: The Bottom Line
review:
The staff were friendly and helpful. We shared the chicken wings and chicken strips. I'm from the south. I was not expecting the chicken strips to be grilled. However, it was a happy surprise. Both items were juicy, flavorful and delicious. I did find the wings a bit spicy for me. I'm not a huge fanYou‚Äôre clearly not coming for the food, which is pretty awful. You‚Äôre not coming for a quiet chat because you can barely hear your own voice. So, you‚Äôre probably coming for the atmosphere, which definitely transports you back into the 1990s. The service is friendly, the food is really bad and the amThe Bottom Line is such a fun hidden gem in DC! It has that classic dive bar feel‚Äînothing fancy, but super welcoming and full of personality. If you're looking for a laid-back spot with strong drinks, good vibes, and no pretentiousness, this is it.

Although the inside was not what I would call handicap friendly. My wife, kids, (who are too young to be out of their stroller)and I Chose this place. The inside resembled a bar but the outside had a nice atmosphere. In my opinion the food was excellent excellent. I ordered the wings which was seasoLunch grilled chicken salad was delicious, nutritious, attractively presented, and a good portion size. Service was efficient.
